{"type":"text","timestamp":1780738144549,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeuERCb2AlX2T5Je","part":{"id":"prt_e9c43a41c001XGhVm82kyFf5cj","messageID":"msg_e9c4396ec001Vvcu0wnewU9A9A","sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeuERCb2AlX2T5Je","type":"text","text":"The proposal centers on three new hardening items for child `015` plus amendments to `002` through `008`; I’m now reading the declared command, agent, and hook surfaces to map where each becomes automatic or visible.","time":{"start":1780738139164,"end":1780738144544},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0aedcfe7093f9903016a23e85b27fc8191a1560e54ea42a9a9","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780738144614,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeuERCb2AlX2T5Je","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_b5bzY3PAsabhGbQLcA73amud","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/implement.md","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/implement.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: description: Implementation workflow (9 steps): execute pre-planned work. Requires plan.md. Modes :auto, :confirm.\n3: argument-hint: \"<spec-folder> [:auto|:confirm] [--phase-folder=<path>] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\n4: allowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, memory_context, memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan\n5: ---\n6: \n7: > ⚠️ **EXECUTION PROTOCOL — READ FIRST**\n8: >\n9: > This command runs a structured YAML workflow. Do NOT dispatch agents from this document.\n10: >\n11: > **YOUR FIRST ACTION:**\n12: > 1. Determine execution mode from user input (`:auto` or `:confirm`)\n13: > 2. Load the corresponding YAML file from `assets/`:\n14: >    - Auto mode → `speckit_implement_auto.yaml`\n15: >    - Confirm mode → `speckit_implement_confirm.yaml`\n16: > 3. Execute the YAML workflow step by step\n17: >\n18: > All content below is reference context for the YAML workflow. Do not treat reference sections, routing tables, or dispatch templates as direct instructions to execute.\n19: \n20: ## CONSTRAINTS\n21: \n22: - **DO NOT** dispatch any agent (`@review`, `@debug`) from this document\n23: - **DO NOT** dispatch `@review` to review this workflow or command prompt\n24: - **DO NOT** dispatch `@debug` autonomously under any condition; the workflow surfaces a prompted offer when `failure_count >= 3` during Step 6 and the user dispatches via Task tool themselves\n25: - **ALL** agent dispatching is handled by the YAML workflow steps — this document is setup + reference only\n26: - **FIRST ACTION** is always: load the YAML file, then execute it step by step\n27: \n28: # SINGLE CONSOLIDATED PROMPT - ONE USER INTERACTION\n29: \n30: This workflow uses a SINGLE consolidated prompt to gather ALL required inputs in ONE user interaction.\n31: \n32: ---\n33: \n34: ## 0. UNIFIED SETUP PHASE\n35: \n36: **FIRST MESSAGE PROTOCOL**: For `:confirm` or no suffix, the consolidated setup prompt MUST be your FIRST response. No implementation or file-modifying tool calls before asking. Lightweight read-only discovery is allowed, then ask ALL questions immediately and wait.\n37: \n38: For `:auto`, do not emit the consolidated prompt by default. Resolve setup with the three-tier branch below, then load the auto YAML only after all required values are bound.\n39: \n40: ### `:auto` Setup Resolution\n41: \n42: Setup contract: see `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/auto_mode_contract.md`.\n43: \n44: Under `execution_mode = AUTONOMOUS` (from the `:auto` suffix), follow the three-tier flow:\n45: \n46: 1. **Tier 1 — Resolve confidently** (contract §1): parse `$ARGUMENTS` flags + `PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:` block (§2) + the Default Resolution Table below (§3). When every required field is resolved, persist to `{spec_path}/implement-config.json` (shape: `specPath`, `executionMode: \"auto\"`, `dispatchMode`, `memoryChoice`, `confirmChoice`, `resumeChoice`, `prerequisitesValid`), bind runtime YAML placeholders, set `STATUS: PASSED`, load `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_implement_auto.yaml`. End §0.\n47: \n48: 2. **Tier 2 — Targeted ask** (contract §1): when 1-2 required fields are genuinely ambiguous AND no default exists, emit ONE narrow question per ambiguous field. Command-specific Tier-2-eligible fields (per the Default Resolution Table below): `spec_folder`, `resume_choice`. **Ordering rule**: ask only for `spec_folder` first when folder detection is ambiguous — prerequisite and resume-session checks depend on it. Missing `spec_folder` with no viable candidates is absence, not ambiguity — go to Tier 3.\n49: \n50: 3. **Tier 3 — Fail fast** (contract §4): emit the named-missing-inputs error format with `/speckit:implement:auto` as the command name. Exit non-zero. Do not load YAML.\n51: \n52: `:confirm` path stays unchanged — see the consolidated setup prompt section below.\n53: \n54: ### PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS Schema (for `:auto` non-interactive dispatch)\n55: \n56: The dispatched prompt body may contain one structured marker block. Parse it before applying defaults. Grammar: see `auto_mode_contract.md` §2.\n57: \n58: ```yaml\n59: PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:\n60:   spec_folder: <spec-folder>  # explicit spec or phase folder path\n61:   phase_folder: \"\"  # optional explicit phase child path\n62:   confirm_choice: yes  # yes | different-folder | cancel\n63:   execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS  # from :auto suffix\n64:   dispatch_mode: single_agent  # single_agent | multi_small | multi_large\n65:   memory_choice: skip  # latest | recent3 | skip | n/a\n66:   resume_choice: resume  # resume | restart | cancel, only when prior incomplete session exists\n67:   prerequisites_valid: true  # auto-detected boolean\n68: ```\n69: \n70: Rules: see `auto_mode_contract.md` §2 (unspecified fields fall back to default; marker fields take precedence over `$ARGUMENTS` flags; unknown fields warn; malformed lines parse-error).\n71: \n72: ### Default Resolution Table\n73: \n74: | Field | Required | Resolves Via | Default | Tier-2 Candidate |\n75: |-------|----------|--------------|---------|------------------|\n76: | `spec_folder` | Y | `$ARGUMENTS` positional path, flag `--phase-folder`, marker `spec_folder` / `phase_folder`, or deterministic single-folder detection | none | Y, when detection returns multiple viable folders |\n77: | `phase_folder` | N | flag `--phase-folder`, marker `phase_folder`, or auto-detect phase child from `spec_folder` | none | N |\n78: | `confirm_choice` | Y | marker `confirm_choice` or default after prerequisite validation | `yes` when prerequisites are valid | N |\n79: | `execution_mode` | Y | attached suffix `:auto` or marker `execution_mode` | `AUTONOMOUS` under `:auto` | N |\n80: | `dispatch_mode` | Y | marker `dispatch_mode` or default recommended option | `single_agent` | N |\n81: | `memory_choice` | N | marker `memory_choice`, prior-continuity detection, or default | `skip` when no prior continuity records exist | N |\n82: | `resume_choice` | N | marker `resume_choice` or targeted question when prior incomplete session exists | none | Y, only when an incomplete-session warning is present |\n83: | `prerequisites_valid` | Y | auto-detect from `spec.md`, `plan.md`, `tasks.md`, and Level 2+ `checklist.md`; marker may only document expected state | auto-detect | N |\n84: \n85: **STATUS: BLOCKED**\n86: \n87: ```\n88: EXECUTE THIS SINGLE CONSOLIDATED PROMPT:\n89: \n90: 1. CHECK for mode suffix:\n91:    - \":auto\" -> execution_mode = \"AUTONOMOUS\" (omit Q2)\n92:    - \":confirm\" -> execution_mode = \"INTERACTIVE\" (omit Q2)\n93:    - No suffix -> execution_mode = \"ASK\" (include Q2)\n94: \n95: 2. CHECK $ARGUMENTS for spec folder path:\n96:    - IF has path -> spec_folder_input = $ARGUMENTS\n97:    - IF empty -> include Q0 with available folders\n98: \n99: 2b. CHECK --phase-folder flag OR auto-detect phase child:\n100:    - IF --phase-folder=<path> provided → auto-resolve spec_path to that child folder\n101:      Set spec_path = <path>, omit Q0/Q1\n102:      Validate path matches pattern: specs/[###]-*/[0-9][0-9][0-9]-*/\n103:    - IF spec_folder_input path contains /[0-9][0-9][0-9]-*/ → auto-detect as phase child\n104:      Show parent context: \"Phase child detected: <path> (parent: <parent-folder>)\"\n105:      Load parent spec.md for cross-reference context\n106:    - ELSE → continue normally\n107: \n108: 3. Search for available spec folders with plan.md:\n109:    $ ls -d specs/*/ 2>/dev/null | tail -10\n110:    Check each for: spec.md, plan.md (required), checklist.md (optional)\n111: \n112: 4. IF spec_folder_input provided, validate prerequisites:\n113:    - spec.md (REQUIRED), plan.md (REQUIRED)\n114:    - tasks.md (create if missing), checklist.md (REQUIRED Level 2+)\n115: \n116: 5. CHECK for prior incomplete sessions:\n117:    - Read handover.md / canonical packet docs for incomplete markers, unchecked tasks in tasks.md\n118:    - IF found -> Show warning with options:\n119:      A) Resume from where left off  B) Restart (archives prior)  C) Cancel\n120: \n121: 6. Check if handover.md or canonical packet docs exist for this spec folder\n122: \n123: 7. ASK user (include only applicable questions):\n124: \n125:    Q0. Spec Folder (if not provided):\n126:       Available folders with plan.md: [list with status]\n127:       Enter folder path or number\n128:       E) Phase folder — target a specific phase child (e.g., specs/NNN-name/001-phase/)\n129: \n130:    Q1. Confirm Spec Folder (if path provided):\n131:       Folder: [path] | spec.md [Y/N] | plan.md [Y/N] | checklist.md [Y/N/optional]\n132:       A) Yes, implement  B) Different folder  C) Cancel (plan first)\n133: \n134:    Q2. Execution Mode (if no suffix):\n135:       A) Autonomous - all 9 steps without approval\n136:       B) Interactive - pause at each step\n137: \n138:    Q3. Dispatch Mode (required):\n139:       A) Single Agent (Recommended)\n140:       B) Multi-Agent (1+2)\n141:       C) Multi-Agent (1+3)\n142: \n143:    Q4. Prior Work Context (when prior continuity records exist for this spec):\n144:       A) Load most recent spec-doc record  B) Load up to 3 most recent spec-doc records  C) Skip (fresh start)\n145: \n146:    Reply with answers, e.g.: \"A, A, A, B\" or \"specs/007-auth/, A, A, B\"\n147: \n148: 8. WAIT for user response (DO NOT PROCEED)\n149: \n150: 9. Parse and store:\n151:    - spec_path, confirm_choice, execution_mode, dispatch_mode, memory_choice\n152: \n153: 10. Handle redirects:\n154:     - confirm_choice == B -> Re-prompt folder selection\n155:     - confirm_choice == C -> Redirect to /speckit:plan\n156: \n157: 11. Execute background operations:\n158:     - memory_choice A: load most recent | B: load up to 3 | multi_*: note parallel dispatch\n159: \n160: 12. SET STATUS: PASSED\n161: \n162: HARD STOP: DO NOT proceed until user answers\n163: NEVER assume spec folder without confirmation\n164: NEVER auto-select execution mode without suffix or explicit choice\n165: NEVER split into multiple prompts\n166: ```\n167: \n168: **Phase Output:**\n169: - `spec_path` | `prerequisites_valid` | `execution_mode` | `dispatch_mode` | `memory_loaded`\n170: \n171: > **Cross-reference**: Implements AGENTS.md Section 2 \"Gate 3: Spec Folder Question\" and \"First Message Protocol\".\n172: \n173: ---\n174: \n175: # SpecKit Implement\n176: \n177: Execute implementation of a pre-planned feature. Requires existing spec.md and plan.md from a prior `/speckit:plan` workflow.\n178: \n179: > Standalone workflow (9 steps) that assumes spec.md and plan.md exist. Run `/speckit:plan` first if needed.\n180: \n181: ```yaml\n182: role: Expert Developer using Smart SpecKit for Implementation Phase\n183: purpose: Execute pre-planned feature implementation with mandatory checklist verification\n184: action: Run 9-step implementation workflow from plan review through completion summary\n185: \n186: operating_mode:\n187:   workflow: sequential_9_step\n188:   workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n189:   workflow_execution: autonomous_or_interactive\n190:   approvals: step_by_step_for_confirm_mode\n191:   tracking: progressive_task_completion\n192:   validation: checklist_verification_with_evidence\n193: ```\n194: \n195: ---\n196: \n197: ## 1. PURPOSE\n198: \n199: Run the 9-step implementation workflow: plan review, task breakdown, quality validation, development, completion summary, and workflow closeout. Picks up where `/speckit:plan` left off.\n200: \n201: ---\n202: \n203: ## 2. CONTRACT\n204: \n205: **Inputs:** `$ARGUMENTS` -- Spec folder path (REQUIRED) with optional parameters\n206: **Outputs:** Completed implementation + implementation-summary.md + nested changelog when applicable + `STATUS=<OK|FAIL|CANCELLED>`\n207: \n208: ### Prerequisites\n209: \n210: **REQUIRED (all levels):** spec.md, plan.md, tasks.md (created if missing)\n211: **REQUIRED Level 2+:** checklist.md\n212: \n213: Missing prerequisites -> guide user to `/speckit:plan` first.\n214: \n215: ### Completion Validation\n216: \n217: `validate.sh --strict` uses the current SpecKit exit taxonomy: 0 = success, 1 = user error, 2 = validation error, 3 = system error. Strict warnings exit as validation errors, so implementation cannot close on a warning-only packet without repairing or explicitly documenting the validation state.\n218: \n219: ---\n220: \n\n(Showing lines 1-220 of 414. Use offset=221 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: Implementation workflow (9 steps): execute pre-planned work. Requires plan.md. Modes :auto, :confirm.\nargument-hint: \"<spec-folder> [:auto|:confirm] [--phase-folder=<path>] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, memory_context, memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan\n---\n\n> ⚠️ **EXECUTION PROTOCOL — READ FIRST**\n>\n> This command runs a structured YAML workflow. Do NOT dispatch agents from this document.\n>\n> **YOUR FIRST ACTION:**\n> 1. Determine execution mode from user input (`:auto` or `:confirm`)\n> 2. Load the corresponding YAML file from `assets/`:\n>    - Auto mode → `speckit_implement_auto.yaml`\n>    - Confirm mode → `speckit_implement_confirm.yaml`\n> 3. Execute the YAML workflow step by step\n>\n> All content below is reference context for the YAML workflow. Do not treat reference sections, routing tables, or dispatch templates as direct instructions to execute.\n\n## CONSTRAINTS","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/implement.md","text":"---\ndescription: Implementation workflow (9 steps): execute pre-planned work. Requires plan.md. Modes :auto, :confirm.\nargument-hint: \"<spec-folder> [:auto|:confirm] [--phase-folder=<path>] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, memory_context, memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan\n---\n\n> ⚠️ **EXECUTION PROTOCOL — READ FIRST**\n>\n> This command runs a structured YAML workflow. Do NOT dispatch agents from this document.\n>\n> **YOUR FIRST ACTION:**\n> 1. Determine execution mode from user input (`:auto` or `:confirm`)\n> 2. Load the corresponding YAML file from `assets/`:\n>    - Auto mode → `speckit_implement_auto.yaml`\n>    - Confirm mode → `speckit_implement_confirm.yaml`\n> 3. Execute the YAML workflow step by step\n>\n> All content below is reference context for the YAML workflow. Do not treat reference sections, routing tables, or dispatch templates as direct instructions to execute.\n\n## CONSTRAINTS\n\n- **DO NOT** dispatch any agent (`@review`, `@debug`) from this document\n- **DO NOT** dispatch `@review` to review this workflow or command prompt\n- **DO NOT** dispatch `@debug` autonomously under any condition; the workflow surfaces a prompted offer when `failure_count >= 3` during Step 6 and the user dispatches via Task tool themselves\n- **ALL** agent dispatching is handled by the YAML workflow steps — this document is setup + reference only\n- **FIRST ACTION** is always: load the YAML file, then execute it step by step\n\n# SINGLE CONSOLIDATED PROMPT - ONE USER INTERACTION\n\nThis workflow uses a SINGLE consolidated prompt to gather ALL required inputs in ONE user interaction.\n\n---\n\n## 0. UNIFIED SETUP PHASE\n\n**FIRST MESSAGE PROTOCOL**: For `:confirm` or no suffix, the consolidated setup prompt MUST be your FIRST response. No implementation or file-modifying tool calls before asking. Lightweight read-only discovery is allowed, then ask ALL questions immediately and wait.\n\nFor `:auto`, do not emit the consolidated prompt by default. Resolve setup with the three-tier branch below, then load the auto YAML only after all required values are bound.\n\n### `:auto` Setup Resolution\n\nSetup contract: see `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/auto_mode_contract.md`.\n\nUnder `execution_mode = AUTONOMOUS` (from the `:auto` suffix), follow the three-tier flow:\n\n1. **Tier 1 — Resolve confidently** (contract §1): parse `$ARGUMENTS` flags + `PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:` block (§2) + the Default Resolution Table below (§3). When every required field is resolved, persist to `{spec_path}/implement-config.json` (shape: `specPath`, `executionMode: \"auto\"`, `dispatchMode`, `memoryChoice`, `confirmChoice`, `resumeChoice`, `prerequisitesValid`), bind runtime YAML placeholders, set `STATUS: PASSED`, load `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_implement_auto.yaml`. End §0.\n\n2. **Tier 2 — Targeted ask** (contract §1): when 1-2 required fields are genuinely ambiguous AND no default exists, emit ONE narrow question per ambiguous field. Command-specific Tier-2-eligible fields (per the Default Resolution Table below): `spec_folder`, `resume_choice`. **Ordering rule**: ask only for `spec_folder` first when folder detection is ambiguous — prerequisite and resume-session checks depend on it. Missing `spec_folder` with no viable candidates is absence, not ambiguity — go to Tier 3.\n\n3. **Tier 3 — Fail fast** (contract §4): emit the named-missing-inputs error format with `/speckit:implement:auto` as the command name. Exit non-zero. Do not load YAML.\n\n`:confirm` path stays unchanged — see the consolidated setup prompt section below.\n\n### PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS Schema (for `:auto` non-interactive dispatch)\n\nThe dispatched prompt body may contain one structured marker block. Parse it before applying defaults. Grammar: see `auto_mode_contract.md` §2.\n\n```yaml\nPRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:\n  spec_folder: <spec-folder>  # explicit spec or phase folder path\n  phase_folder: \"\"  # optional explicit phase child path\n  confirm_choice: yes  # yes | different-folder | cancel\n  execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS  # from :auto suffix\n  dispatch_mode: single_agent  # single_agent | multi_small | multi_large\n  memory_choice: skip  # latest | recent3 | skip | n/a\n  resume_choice: resume  # resume | restart | cancel, only when prior incomplete session exists\n  prerequisites_valid: true  # auto-detected boolean\n```\n\nRules: see `auto_mode_contract.md` §2 (unspecified fields fall back to default; marker fields take precedence over `$ARGUMENTS` flags; unknown fields warn; malformed lines parse-error).\n\n### Default Resolution Table\n\n| Field | Required | Resolves Via | Default | Tier-2 Candidate |\n|-------|----------|--------------|---------|------------------|\n| `spec_folder` | Y | `$ARGUMENTS` positional path, flag `--phase-folder`, marker `spec_folder` / `phase_folder`, or deterministic single-folder detection | none | Y, when detection returns multiple viable folders |\n| `phase_folder` | N | flag `--phase-folder`, marker `phase_folder`, or auto-detect phase child from `spec_folder` | none | N |\n| `confirm_choice` | Y | marker `confirm_choice` or default after prerequisite validation | `yes` when prerequisites are valid | N |\n| `execution_mode` | Y | attached suffix `:auto` or marker `execution_mode` | `AUTONOMOUS` under `:auto` | N |\n| `dispatch_mode` | Y | marker `dispatch_mode` or default recommended option | `single_agent` | N |\n| `memory_choice` | N | marker `memory_choice`, prior-continuity detection, or default | `skip` when no prior continuity records exist | N |\n| `resume_choice` | N | marker `resume_choice` or targeted question when prior incomplete session exists | none | Y, only when an incomplete-session warning is present |\n| `prerequisites_valid` | Y | auto-detect from `spec.md`, `plan.md`, `tasks.md`, and Level 2+ `checklist.md`; marker may only document expected state | auto-detect | N |\n\n**STATUS: BLOCKED**\n\n```\nEXECUTE THIS SINGLE CONSOLIDATED PROMPT:\n\n1. CHECK for mode suffix:\n   - \":auto\" -> execution_mode = \"AUTONOMOUS\" (omit Q2)\n   - \":confirm\" -> execution_mode = \"INTERACTIVE\" (omit Q2)\n   - No suffix -> execution_mode = \"ASK\" (include Q2)\n\n2. CHECK $ARGUMENTS for spec folder path:\n   - IF has path -> spec_folder_input = $ARGUMENTS\n   - IF empty -> include Q0 with available folders\n\n2b. CHECK --phase-folder flag OR auto-detect phase child:\n   - IF --phase-folder=<path> provided → auto-resolve spec_path to that child folder\n     Set spec_path = <path>, omit Q0/Q1\n     Validate path matches pattern: specs/[###]-*/[0-9][0-9][0-9]-*/\n   - IF spec_folder_input path contains /[0-9][0-9][0-9]-*/ → auto-detect as phase child\n     Show parent context: \"Phase child detected: <path> (parent: <parent-folder>)\"\n     Load parent spec.md for cross-reference context\n   - ELSE → continue normally\n\n3. Search for available spec folders with plan.md:\n   $ ls -d specs/*/ 2>/dev/null | tail -10\n   Check each for: spec.md, plan.md (required), checklist.md (optional)\n\n4. IF spec_folder_input provided, validate prerequisites:\n   - spec.md (REQUIRED), plan.md (REQUIRED)\n   - tasks.md (create if missing), checklist.md (REQUIRED Level 2+)\n\n5. CHECK for prior incomplete sessions:\n   - Read handover.md / canonical packet docs for incomplete markers, unchecked tasks in tasks.md\n   - IF found -> Show warning with options:\n     A) Resume from where left off  B) Restart (archives prior)  C) Cancel\n\n6. Check if handover.md or canonical packet docs exist for this spec folder\n\n7. ASK user (include only applicable questions):\n\n   Q0. Spec Folder (if not provided):\n      Available folders with plan.md: [list with status]\n      Enter folder path or number\n      E) Phase folder — target a specific phase child (e.g., specs/NNN-name/001-phase/)\n\n   Q1. Confirm Spec Folder (if path provided):\n      Folder: [path] | spec.md [Y/N] | plan.md [Y/N] | checklist.md [Y/N/optional]\n      A) Yes, implement  B) Different folder  C) Cancel (plan first)\n\n   Q2. Execution Mode (if no suffix):\n      A) Autonomous - all 9 steps without approval\n      B) Interactive - pause at each step\n\n   Q3. Dispatch Mode (required):\n      A) Single Agent (Recommended)\n      B) Multi-Agent (1+2)\n      C) Multi-Agent (1+3)\n\n   Q4. Prior Work Context (when prior continuity records exist for this spec):\n      A) Load most recent spec-doc record  B) Load up to 3 most recent spec-doc records  C) Skip (fresh start)\n\n   Reply with answers, e.g.: \"A, A, A, B\" or \"specs/007-auth/, A, A, B\"\n\n8. WAIT for user response (DO NOT PROCEED)\n\n9. Parse and store:\n   - spec_path, confirm_choice, execution_mode, dispatch_mode, memory_choice\n\n10. Handle redirects:\n    - confirm_choice == B -> Re-prompt folder selection\n    - confirm_choice == C -> Redirect to /speckit:plan\n\n11. Execute background operations:\n    - memory_choice A: load most recent | B: load up to 3 | multi_*: note parallel dispatch\n\n12. SET STATUS: PASSED\n\nHARD STOP: DO NOT proceed until user answers\nNEVER assume spec folder without confirmation\nNEVER auto-select execution mode without suffix or explicit choice\nNEVER split into multiple prompts\n```\n\n**Phase Output:**\n- `spec_path` | `prerequisites_valid` | `execution_mode` | `dispatch_mode` | `memory_loaded`\n\n> **Cross-reference**: Implements AGENTS.md Section 2 \"Gate 3: Spec Folder Question\" and \"First Message Protocol\".\n\n---\n\n# SpecKit Implement\n\nExecute implementation of a pre-planned feature. Requires existing spec.md and plan.md from a prior `/speckit:plan` workflow.\n\n> Standalone workflow (9 steps) that assumes spec.md and plan.md exist. Run `/speckit:plan` first if needed.\n\n```yaml\nrole: Expert Developer using Smart SpecKit for Implementation Phase\npurpose: Execute pre-planned feature implementation with mandatory checklist verification\naction: Run 9-step implementation workflow from plan review through completion summary\n\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: sequential_9_step\n  workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n  workflow_execution: autonomous_or_interactive\n  approvals: step_by_step_for_confirm_mode\n  tracking: progressive_task_completion\n  validation: checklist_verification_with_evidence\n```\n\n---\n\n## 1. PURPOSE\n\nRun the 9-step implementation workflow: plan review, task breakdown, quality validation, development, completion summary, and workflow closeout. Picks up where `/speckit:plan` left off.\n\n---\n\n## 2. CONTRACT\n\n**Inputs:** `$ARGUMENTS` -- Spec folder path (REQUIRED) with optional parameters\n**Outputs:** Completed implementation + implementation-summary.md + nested changelog when applicable + `STATUS=<OK|FAIL|CANCELLED>`\n\n### Prerequisites\n\n**REQUIRED (all levels):** spec.md, plan.md, tasks.md (created if missing)\n**REQUIRED Level 2+:** checklist.md\n\nMissing prerequisites -> guide user to `/speckit:plan` first.\n\n### Completion Validation\n\n`validate.sh --strict` uses the current SpecKit exit taxonomy: 0 = success, 1 = user error, 2 = validation error, 3 = system error. Strict warnings exit as validation errors, so implementation cannot close on a warning-only packet without repairing or explicitly documenting the validation state.\n\n---\n","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":220,"totalLines":414,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/speckit/implement.md","time":{"start":1780738144594,"end":1780738144606}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0aedcfe7093f9903016a23e8608468819194f5adb2f947c190"}},"id":"prt_e9c43b951001BLuXrRWCD1DVbb","sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeuERCb2AlX2T5Je","messageID":"msg_e9c4396ec001Vvcu0wnewU9A9A"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780738144614,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeuERCb2AlX2T5Je","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_1kyi1faVbqQSVWIFE16ymCgB","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/plan.md","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/plan.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: description: Planning workflow (8 steps): spec through plan only. Modes :auto, :confirm, :with-phases.\n3: argument-hint: \"<feature-description> [:auto|:confirm] [:with-phases] [--intake-only] [--phases N] [--phase-names list] [--phase-folder=<path>] [--spec-folder=PATH] [--level=1|2|3|3+] [--start-state=STATE] [--repair-mode=MODE] [--record-relationships=yes|no] [--depends-on=IDs] [--related-to=IDs] [--supersedes=IDs] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\n4: allowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, memory_context, memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan\n5: ---\n6: \n7: > ⚠️ **EXECUTION PROTOCOL — READ FIRST**\n8: >\n9: > This command runs a structured YAML workflow. Do NOT dispatch agents from this document.\n10: >\n11: > **Ownership:** Markdown owns setup (resolves all inputs). YAML owns execution (dispatches steps). Setup values resolved here are passed to the YAML workflow.\n12: >\n13: > **YOUR FIRST ACTION:**\n14: > 1. Determine execution mode from user input (`:auto` or `:confirm`)\n15: >    Note: `:with-phases` is a feature flag, not an execution mode. It modifies the workflow but does not change the base execution mode.\n16: > 2. Load the corresponding YAML file from `assets/`:\n17: >    - Auto mode → `speckit_plan_auto.yaml`\n18: >    - Confirm mode → `speckit_plan_confirm.yaml`\n19: > 3. Execute the YAML workflow step by step\n20: >\n21: > All content below is reference context for the YAML workflow. Do not treat reference sections, routing tables, or dispatch templates as direct instructions to execute.\n22: \n23: ## CONSTRAINTS\n24: \n25: - **DO NOT** dispatch any agent (`@deep-research`, `@context`) from this document\n26: - **DO NOT** dispatch `@deep-research` unless confidence < 60% during planning (Step 5)\n27: - **ALL** agent dispatching is handled by the YAML workflow steps — this document is setup + reference only\n28: - **FIRST ACTION** is always: load the YAML file, then execute it step by step\n29: \n30: # SINGLE CONSOLIDATED PROMPT - ONE USER INTERACTION\n31: \n32: This workflow gathers ALL inputs in ONE prompt. Round-trip: 1 user interaction.\n33: \n34: ---\n35: \n36: ## 0. UNIFIED SETUP PHASE\n37: \n38: **FIRST MESSAGE PROTOCOL**: For `:confirm` or no suffix, the consolidated setup prompt MUST be your FIRST response. No analysis, no tool calls — ask ALL questions immediately, then wait.\n39: \n40: Read-only discovery to classify folder state is allowed when `spec_path` is explicit or can be inferred from the setup answers. Healthy folders keep the existing prompt shape; non-healthy folders run the intake contract (`.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/intake_contract.md`) inline inside the same consolidated prompt and MUST NOT open a second visible command flow. When `--intake-only` is present, execution halts after the Emit phase without proceeding to planning Steps 2–8.\n41: \n42: For `:auto`, do not emit the consolidated prompt by default. Resolve setup with the three-tier branch below, then load the auto YAML only after all required values are bound.\n43: \n44: ### `:auto` Setup Resolution\n45: \n46: Setup contract: see `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/auto_mode_contract.md`.\n47: \n48: Under `execution_mode = AUTONOMOUS` (from the `:auto` suffix), follow the three-tier flow:\n49: \n50: 1. **Tier 1 — Resolve confidently** (contract §1): parse `$ARGUMENTS` flags + `PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:` block (§2) + the Default Resolution Table below (§3). When every required field is resolved, persist to `{spec_path}/plan-config.json` (shape: `featureDescription`, `specPath`, `executionMode: \"auto\"`, `dispatchMode`, `memoryChoice`, `researchIntent`, `phaseDecomposition`, `phaseCount`, `phaseNames`, `intakeOnly`, `intake.*`), bind runtime YAML placeholders, set `STATUS: PASSED`, load `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_plan_auto.yaml`. End §0.\n51: \n52: 2. **Tier 2 — Targeted ask** (contract §1): when 1-2 required fields are genuinely ambiguous AND no default exists, emit ONE narrow question per ambiguous field. Command-specific Tier-2-eligible fields (per the Default Resolution Table below): `spec_folder`, `research_intent`. **Ordering rule**: none needed. Missing `feature_description` is absence, not ambiguity — go to Tier 3.\n53: \n54: 3. **Tier 3 — Fail fast** (contract §4): emit the named-missing-inputs error format with `/speckit:plan:auto` as the command name. Exit non-zero. Do not load YAML.\n55: \n56: `:confirm` path stays unchanged — see the consolidated setup prompt section below.\n57: \n58: ### PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS Schema (for `:auto` non-interactive dispatch)\n59: \n60: The dispatched prompt body may contain one structured marker block. Parse it before applying defaults. Grammar: see `auto_mode_contract.md` §2.\n61: \n62: ```yaml\n63: PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:\n64:   feature_description: Add passwordless login  # string\n65:   spec_folder: <spec-folder>  # existing | new | update-related | skip | phase-folder | explicit path\n66:   execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS  # from :auto suffix\n67:   dispatch_mode: single_agent  # single_agent | multi_small | multi_large\n68:   memory_choice: skip  # latest | recent3 | skip | n/a\n69:   research_intent: add_feature  # add_feature | fix_bug | refactor | understand\n70:   phase_decomposition: false  # boolean, true when :with-phases present\n71:   phase_count: 3  # positive integer\n72:   phase_names: \"\"  # optional comma-separated names\n73:   phase_folder: \"\"  # optional explicit phase child path\n74:   intake_only: false  # boolean, true when --intake-only present\n75:   selected_level: \"\"  # optional intake level: 1 | 2 | 3 | 3+\n76:   start_state: \"\"  # optional intake folder state\n77:   repair_mode: \"\"  # optional intake repair mode\n78:   record_relationships: false  # boolean\n79:   depends_on: \"\"  # optional comma-separated packet ids\n80:   related_to: \"\"  # optional comma-separated packet ids\n81:   supersedes: \"\"  # optional comma-separated packet ids\n82: ```\n83: \n84: Rules: see `auto_mode_contract.md` §2 (unspecified fields fall back to default; marker fields take precedence over `$ARGUMENTS` flags; unknown fields warn; malformed lines parse-error).\n85: \n86: ### Default Resolution Table\n87: \n88: | Field | Required | Resolves Via | Default | Tier-2 Candidate |\n89: |-------|----------|--------------|---------|------------------|\n90: | `feature_description` | Y | `$ARGUMENTS` positional feature description, or marker `feature_description` | none | N |\n91: | `spec_folder` | Y | flag `--spec-folder`, flag `--phase-folder`, marker `spec_folder` / `phase_folder`, or targeted choice among existing/new/update-related/skip/phase folder | none | Y, when feature is present but folder choice is ambiguous |\n92: | `execution_mode` | Y | attached suffix `:auto` or marker `execution_mode` | `AUTONOMOUS` under `:auto` | N |\n93: | `dispatch_mode` | Y | marker `dispatch_mode` or default recommended option | `single_agent` | N |\n94: | `memory_choice` | N | marker `memory_choice`, prior-work detection, or default | `skip` when no prior continuity records exist | N |\n95: | `research_intent` | Y | marker `research_intent` or targeted classification question | none | Y |\n96: | `phase_decomposition` | Y | suffix `:with-phases`, marker `phase_decomposition`, or default | `false` | N |\n97: | `phase_count` | N | flag `--phases`, marker `phase_count`, or default | `3` | N |\n98: | `phase_names` | N | flag `--phase-names`, marker `phase_names`, or auto-generate | none | N |\n99: | `phase_folder` | N | flag `--phase-folder`, marker `phase_folder`, or default | none | N |\n100: | `intake_only` | N | flag `--intake-only`, marker `intake_only`, or default | `false` | N |\n101: | `selected_level` | N | flag `--level`, marker `selected_level`, or inline intake contract when required | none | N |\n102: | `start_state` | N | flag `--start-state`, marker `start_state`, folder-state classification, or inline intake contract when required | auto-detect | N |\n103: | `repair_mode` | N | flag `--repair-mode`, marker `repair_mode`, or inline intake contract when required | none | N |\n104: | `record_relationships` | N | flag `--record-relationships`, marker `record_relationships`, or inline intake contract when required | `false` | N |\n105: | `depends_on` | N | flag `--depends-on`, marker `depends_on`, or inline intake relationship capture | none | N |\n106: | `related_to` | N | flag `--related-to`, marker `related_to`, or inline intake relationship capture | none | N |\n107: | `supersedes` | N | flag `--supersedes`, marker `supersedes`, or inline intake relationship capture | none | N |\n108: \n109: **STATUS: BLOCKED**\n110: \n111: ```\n112: EXECUTE THIS SINGLE CONSOLIDATED PROMPT:\n113: \n114: 1. CHECK mode suffix:\n115:    ├─ \":auto\"    → execution_mode = \"AUTONOMOUS\" (omit Q2)\n116:    ├─ \":confirm\" → execution_mode = \"INTERACTIVE\" (omit Q2)\n117:    └─ No suffix  → execution_mode = \"ASK\" (include Q2)\n118: \n119: 1a. CHECK :with-phases flag:\n120:    ├─ \":with-phases\" present → phase_decomposition = TRUE (omit Q6)\n121:    │   Parse additional flags: --phases N (default 3), --phase-names \"a,b,c\" (optional)\n122:    │   Include Q7 (Phase Count) and Q8 (Phase Names) if not provided via flags\n123:    └─ Not present → phase_decomposition = \"ASK\" (include Q6)\n124: \n125: 1a-b. CHECK --intake-only flag:\n126:    ├─ present → intake_only = TRUE; workflow halts after Emit phase, does not proceed to planning Steps 2–8\n127:    └─ absent → intake_only = FALSE\n128: \n129: 1a-c. PARSE intake contract flags (see .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/intake_contract.md §1):\n130:    ├─ --spec-folder=PATH → spec_path = PATH (bypass auto-discovery)\n131:    ├─ --level=N → selected_level = N\n132:    ├─ --start-state=STATE → requested_start_state = STATE\n133:    ├─ --repair-mode=MODE → repair_mode = MODE\n134:    ├─ --record-relationships=yes|no → collect_relationships = [true|false]\n135:    ├─ --depends-on=PACKET_ID[...] → seed manual_relationships.depends_on[]\n136:    ├─ --related-to=PACKET_ID[...] → seed manual_relationships.related_to[]\n137:    └─ --supersedes=PACKET_ID[...] → seed manual_relationships.supersedes[]\n138: \n139: 1b. CHECK --phase-folder flag:\n140:    ├─ --phase-folder=<path> provided → auto-resolve spec_path to that child folder path\n141:    │   Set spec_choice = \"E\", spec_path = <path>, omit Q1\n142:    │   Validate path matches pattern: specs/[###]-*/[0-9][0-9][0-9]-*/\n143:    │   Show parent context: \"Phase folder: <path> (parent: <parent-folder>)\"\n144:    └─ Not provided → continue normally\n145: \n146: 2. CHECK $ARGUMENTS for feature description:\n147:    ├─ Has content (ignoring :auto/:confirm) → feature_description = $ARGUMENTS, omit Q0\n148:    └─ Empty → include Q0\n149: \n150: 3. Search for related spec folders:\n151:    $ ls -d specs/*/ 2>/dev/null | tail -10\n152: \n153: 4. Search for prior work (background):\n154:    - memory_context({ input: feature_description OR \"planning\", mode: \"focused\", includeContent: true })\n155:    > Gate 1 trigger matching handled at agent level (AGENTS.md).\n156:    > Gate 3 spec-folder trigger classification is typed: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/gate-3-classifier.ts` (`classifyPrompt()`). Invocations of `/speckit:plan` are already inside a write flow, so Gate 3 is pre-answered by command dispatch — no extra inference needed here.\n157:    - Store: prior_work_found = [yes/no], prior_work_count = [N]\n158: \n159: 5. Prior-work loading question needed ONLY if user selects A or C for spec folder AND prior continuity records exist for this spec.\n160: \n161: 5a. CHECK intake contract requirement when `spec_path` is explicit or can be derived from Q1 / `--phase-folder`:\n162:    ├─ Inspect `{spec_path}` for `spec.md`, `description.json`, `graph-metadata.json`, and tracked placeholder markers per intake_contract.md §3 Folder State Classification\n163:    ├─ Normalize `folder_state` to one of: `empty-folder` | `partial-folder` | `repair-mode` | `placeholder-upgrade` | `populated-folder`\n164:    ├─ `folder_state == populated-folder` AND `intake_only == FALSE` → `intake_required = FALSE` and preserve the current prompt unchanged\n165:    ├─ `folder_state == populated-folder` AND `intake_only == TRUE` → no-op exit with informational message\n166:    └─ Otherwise → `intake_required = TRUE`, inherit the parent `execution_mode`, and run the intake contract inline before Step 1 continues (or halt after Emit phase if `intake_only == TRUE`)\n167: \n168: 6. ASK with SINGLE prompt (include only applicable questions):\n169: \n170:    Q0. Feature Description (if not in command): What feature to plan?\n171: \n172:    Q1. Spec Folder (required):\n173:      A) Use existing [suggest if found]  B) Create new: specs/[###]-[slug]/\n174:      C) Update related [if match found]  D) Skip documentation\n175:      E) Phase folder — target a specific phase child (e.g., specs/NNN-name/001-phase/)\n176: \n177:    Q2. Execution Mode (if no suffix):\n178:      A) Autonomous - all 8 steps without approval\n179:      B) Interactive - pause at each step\n180: \n181:    Q3. Dispatch Mode (required):\n182:      A) Single Agent (Recommended)  B) Multi-Agent (1+2)  C) Multi-Agent (1+3)\n183: \n184:    Q4. Prior Work Context (when prior continuity records exist for this spec):\n185:      A) Load most recent spec-doc record  B) Load up to 3 most recent spec-doc records  C) Skip\n186: \n187:    Q5. Research Intent (required):\n188:      A) add_feature  B) fix_bug  C) refactor  D) understand\n189: \n190:    Q6. Phase Decomposition (if :with-phases not in command):\n191:      Create phased spec structure (parent + N child folders)?\n192:      A) No — single spec folder (default)\n193:      B) Yes — decompose into phases before planning\n194: \n195:    Q7. Phase Count (if phase_decomposition == TRUE and --phases not provided):\n196:      How many phases? (Default: 3)\n197: \n198:    Q8. Phase Names (if phase_decomposition == TRUE and --phase-names not provided):\n199:      Provide phase names? (Optional — auto-generated if skipped)\n200:      Example: \"data-model, api-layer, ui-components\"\n201: \n202:    **Intake contract block** (ONLY if `intake_required = TRUE`; keep this inside the SAME prompt, not a second command flow):\n203: \n204:    Execute the Q0–Q4+ consolidated intake interview per `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/intake_contract.md §5`. Questions cover: feature description, target folder state, documentation level, relationship capture, and relationship entries (grouped `depends_on` / `related_to` / `supersedes` by `packet_id`).\n205: \n206:    Reply format: \"B, A, A, C, A\" or \"Add auth, B, A, C, A\"\n207: \n208: 7. WAIT for user response (DO NOT PROCEED)\n209: \n210: 8. Parse response and store ALL results:\n211:    - feature_description = [from Q0 or $ARGUMENTS]\n212:    - spec_choice = [A/B/C/D/E from Q1]\n213:    - spec_path = [derived path or null if D]\n214:    - execution_mode = [AUTONOMOUS/INTERACTIVE from suffix or Q2]\n215:    - dispatch_mode = [single/multi_small/multi_large from Q3]\n216:    - memory_choice = [A/B/C from Q4, or N/A]\n217:    - research_intent = [add_feature/fix_bug/refactor/understand from Q5]\n218:    - IF `intake_required = TRUE`: bind `selected_level`, `start_state`, `repair_mode`, and `manual_relationships` from the inline intake-contract block (see intake_contract.md §6 for trio-publication semantics)\n219:    - IF intake contract adjusts the target: update `feature_description` and `spec_path` from the returned contract before Step 1\n220:    - IF `intake_only = TRUE`: halt here with STATUS=OK after intake Emit phase completes; do not proceed to Step 1\n\n(Showing lines 1-220 of 549. Use offset=221 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: Planning workflow (8 steps): spec through plan only. Modes :auto, :confirm, :with-phases.\nargument-hint: \"<feature-description> [:auto|:confirm] [:with-phases] [--intake-only] [--phases N] [--phase-names list] [--phase-folder=<path>] [--spec-folder=PATH] [--level=1|2|3|3+] [--start-state=STATE] [--repair-mode=MODE] [--record-relationships=yes|no] [--depends-on=IDs] [--related-to=IDs] [--supersedes=IDs] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, memory_context, memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan\n---\n\n> ⚠️ **EXECUTION PROTOCOL — READ FIRST**\n>\n> This command runs a structured YAML workflow. Do NOT dispatch agents from this document.\n>\n> **Ownership:** Markdown owns setup (resolves all inputs). YAML owns execution (dispatches steps). Setup values resolved here are passed to the YAML workflow.\n>\n> **YOUR FIRST ACTION:**\n> 1. Determine execution mode from user input (`:auto` or `:confirm`)\n>    Note: `:with-phases` is a feature flag, not an execution mode. It modifies the workflow but does not change the base execution mode.\n> 2. Load the corresponding YAML file from `assets/`:\n>    - Auto mode → `speckit_plan_auto.yaml`\n>    - Confirm mode → `speckit_plan_confirm.yaml`\n> 3. Execute the YAML workflow step by step\n>","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/plan.md","text":"---\ndescription: Planning workflow (8 steps): spec through plan only. Modes :auto, :confirm, :with-phases.\nargument-hint: \"<feature-description> [:auto|:confirm] [:with-phases] [--intake-only] [--phases N] [--phase-names list] [--phase-folder=<path>] [--spec-folder=PATH] [--level=1|2|3|3+] [--start-state=STATE] [--repair-mode=MODE] [--record-relationships=yes|no] [--depends-on=IDs] [--related-to=IDs] [--supersedes=IDs] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, memory_context, memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan\n---\n\n> ⚠️ **EXECUTION PROTOCOL — READ FIRST**\n>\n> This command runs a structured YAML workflow. Do NOT dispatch agents from this document.\n>\n> **Ownership:** Markdown owns setup (resolves all inputs). YAML owns execution (dispatches steps). Setup values resolved here are passed to the YAML workflow.\n>\n> **YOUR FIRST ACTION:**\n> 1. Determine execution mode from user input (`:auto` or `:confirm`)\n>    Note: `:with-phases` is a feature flag, not an execution mode. It modifies the workflow but does not change the base execution mode.\n> 2. Load the corresponding YAML file from `assets/`:\n>    - Auto mode → `speckit_plan_auto.yaml`\n>    - Confirm mode → `speckit_plan_confirm.yaml`\n> 3. Execute the YAML workflow step by step\n>\n> All content below is reference context for the YAML workflow. Do not treat reference sections, routing tables, or dispatch templates as direct instructions to execute.\n\n## CONSTRAINTS\n\n- **DO NOT** dispatch any agent (`@deep-research`, `@context`) from this document\n- **DO NOT** dispatch `@deep-research` unless confidence < 60% during planning (Step 5)\n- **ALL** agent dispatching is handled by the YAML workflow steps — this document is setup + reference only\n- **FIRST ACTION** is always: load the YAML file, then execute it step by step\n\n# SINGLE CONSOLIDATED PROMPT - ONE USER INTERACTION\n\nThis workflow gathers ALL inputs in ONE prompt. Round-trip: 1 user interaction.\n\n---\n\n## 0. UNIFIED SETUP PHASE\n\n**FIRST MESSAGE PROTOCOL**: For `:confirm` or no suffix, the consolidated setup prompt MUST be your FIRST response. No analysis, no tool calls — ask ALL questions immediately, then wait.\n\nRead-only discovery to classify folder state is allowed when `spec_path` is explicit or can be inferred from the setup answers. Healthy folders keep the existing prompt shape; non-healthy folders run the intake contract (`.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/intake_contract.md`) inline inside the same consolidated prompt and MUST NOT open a second visible command flow. When `--intake-only` is present, execution halts after the Emit phase without proceeding to planning Steps 2–8.\n\nFor `:auto`, do not emit the consolidated prompt by default. Resolve setup with the three-tier branch below, then load the auto YAML only after all required values are bound.\n\n### `:auto` Setup Resolution\n\nSetup contract: see `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/auto_mode_contract.md`.\n\nUnder `execution_mode = AUTONOMOUS` (from the `:auto` suffix), follow the three-tier flow:\n\n1. **Tier 1 — Resolve confidently** (contract §1): parse `$ARGUMENTS` flags + `PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:` block (§2) + the Default Resolution Table below (§3). When every required field is resolved, persist to `{spec_path}/plan-config.json` (shape: `featureDescription`, `specPath`, `executionMode: \"auto\"`, `dispatchMode`, `memoryChoice`, `researchIntent`, `phaseDecomposition`, `phaseCount`, `phaseNames`, `intakeOnly`, `intake.*`), bind runtime YAML placeholders, set `STATUS: PASSED`, load `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_plan_auto.yaml`. End §0.\n\n2. **Tier 2 — Targeted ask** (contract §1): when 1-2 required fields are genuinely ambiguous AND no default exists, emit ONE narrow question per ambiguous field. Command-specific Tier-2-eligible fields (per the Default Resolution Table below): `spec_folder`, `research_intent`. **Ordering rule**: none needed. Missing `feature_description` is absence, not ambiguity — go to Tier 3.\n\n3. **Tier 3 — Fail fast** (contract §4): emit the named-missing-inputs error format with `/speckit:plan:auto` as the command name. Exit non-zero. Do not load YAML.\n\n`:confirm` path stays unchanged — see the consolidated setup prompt section below.\n\n### PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS Schema (for `:auto` non-interactive dispatch)\n\nThe dispatched prompt body may contain one structured marker block. Parse it before applying defaults. Grammar: see `auto_mode_contract.md` §2.\n\n```yaml\nPRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:\n  feature_description: Add passwordless login  # string\n  spec_folder: <spec-folder>  # existing | new | update-related | skip | phase-folder | explicit path\n  execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS  # from :auto suffix\n  dispatch_mode: single_agent  # single_agent | multi_small | multi_large\n  memory_choice: skip  # latest | recent3 | skip | n/a\n  research_intent: add_feature  # add_feature | fix_bug | refactor | understand\n  phase_decomposition: false  # boolean, true when :with-phases present\n  phase_count: 3  # positive integer\n  phase_names: \"\"  # optional comma-separated names\n  phase_folder: \"\"  # optional explicit phase child path\n  intake_only: false  # boolean, true when --intake-only present\n  selected_level: \"\"  # optional intake level: 1 | 2 | 3 | 3+\n  start_state: \"\"  # optional intake folder state\n  repair_mode: \"\"  # optional intake repair mode\n  record_relationships: false  # boolean\n  depends_on: \"\"  # optional comma-separated packet ids\n  related_to: \"\"  # optional comma-separated packet ids\n  supersedes: \"\"  # optional comma-separated packet ids\n```\n\nRules: see `auto_mode_contract.md` §2 (unspecified fields fall back to default; marker fields take precedence over `$ARGUMENTS` flags; unknown fields warn; malformed lines parse-error).\n\n### Default Resolution Table\n\n| Field | Required | Resolves Via | Default | Tier-2 Candidate |\n|-------|----------|--------------|---------|------------------|\n| `feature_description` | Y | `$ARGUMENTS` positional feature description, or marker `feature_description` | none | N |\n| `spec_folder` | Y | flag `--spec-folder`, flag `--phase-folder`, marker `spec_folder` / `phase_folder`, or targeted choice among existing/new/update-related/skip/phase folder | none | Y, when feature is present but folder choice is ambiguous |\n| `execution_mode` | Y | attached suffix `:auto` or marker `execution_mode` | `AUTONOMOUS` under `:auto` | N |\n| `dispatch_mode` | Y | marker `dispatch_mode` or default recommended option | `single_agent` | N |\n| `memory_choice` | N | marker `memory_choice`, prior-work detection, or default | `skip` when no prior continuity records exist | N |\n| `research_intent` | Y | marker `research_intent` or targeted classification question | none | Y |\n| `phase_decomposition` | Y | suffix `:with-phases`, marker `phase_decomposition`, or default | `false` | N |\n| `phase_count` | N | flag `--phases`, marker `phase_count`, or default | `3` | N |\n| `phase_names` | N | flag `--phase-names`, marker `phase_names`, or auto-generate | none | N |\n| `phase_folder` | N | flag `--phase-folder`, marker `phase_folder`, or default | none | N |\n| `intake_only` | N | flag `--intake-only`, marker `intake_only`, or default | `false` | N |\n| `selected_level` | N | flag `--level`, marker `selected_level`, or inline intake contract when required | none | N |\n| `start_state` | N | flag `--start-state`, marker `start_state`, folder-state classification, or inline intake contract when required | auto-detect | N |\n| `repair_mode` | N | flag `--repair-mode`, marker `repair_mode`, or inline intake contract when required | none | N |\n| `record_relationships` | N | flag `--record-relationships`, marker `record_relationships`, or inline intake contract when required | `false` | N |\n| `depends_on` | N | flag `--depends-on`, marker `depends_on`, or inline intake relationship capture | none | N |\n| `related_to` | N | flag `--related-to`, marker `related_to`, or inline intake relationship capture | none | N |\n| `supersedes` | N | flag `--supersedes`, marker `supersedes`, or inline intake relationship capture | none | N |\n\n**STATUS: BLOCKED**\n\n```\nEXECUTE THIS SINGLE CONSOLIDATED PROMPT:\n\n1. CHECK mode suffix:\n   ├─ \":auto\"    → execution_mode = \"AUTONOMOUS\" (omit Q2)\n   ├─ \":confirm\" → execution_mode = \"INTERACTIVE\" (omit Q2)\n   └─ No suffix  → execution_mode = \"ASK\" (include Q2)\n\n1a. CHECK :with-phases flag:\n   ├─ \":with-phases\" present → phase_decomposition = TRUE (omit Q6)\n   │   Parse additional flags: --phases N (default 3), --phase-names \"a,b,c\" (optional)\n   │   Include Q7 (Phase Count) and Q8 (Phase Names) if not provided via flags\n   └─ Not present → phase_decomposition = \"ASK\" (include Q6)\n\n1a-b. CHECK --intake-only flag:\n   ├─ present → intake_only = TRUE; workflow halts after Emit phase, does not proceed to planning Steps 2–8\n   └─ absent → intake_only = FALSE\n\n1a-c. PARSE intake contract flags (see .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/intake_contract.md §1):\n   ├─ --spec-folder=PATH → spec_path = PATH (bypass auto-discovery)\n   ├─ --level=N → selected_level = N\n   ├─ --start-state=STATE → requested_start_state = STATE\n   ├─ --repair-mode=MODE → repair_mode = MODE\n   ├─ --record-relationships=yes|no → collect_relationships = [true|false]\n   ├─ --depends-on=PACKET_ID[...] → seed manual_relationships.depends_on[]\n   ├─ --related-to=PACKET_ID[...] → seed manual_relationships.related_to[]\n   └─ --supersedes=PACKET_ID[...] → seed manual_relationships.supersedes[]\n\n1b. CHECK --phase-folder flag:\n   ├─ --phase-folder=<path> provided → auto-resolve spec_path to that child folder path\n   │   Set spec_choice = \"E\", spec_path = <path>, omit Q1\n   │   Validate path matches pattern: specs/[###]-*/[0-9][0-9][0-9]-*/\n   │   Show parent context: \"Phase folder: <path> (parent: <parent-folder>)\"\n   └─ Not provided → continue normally\n\n2. CHECK $ARGUMENTS for feature description:\n   ├─ Has content (ignoring :auto/:confirm) → feature_description = $ARGUMENTS, omit Q0\n   └─ Empty → include Q0\n\n3. Search for related spec folders:\n   $ ls -d specs/*/ 2>/dev/null | tail -10\n\n4. Search for prior work (background):\n   - memory_context({ input: feature_description OR \"planning\", mode: \"focused\", includeContent: true })\n   > Gate 1 trigger matching handled at agent level (AGENTS.md).\n   > Gate 3 spec-folder trigger classification is typed: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/gate-3-classifier.ts` (`classifyPrompt()`). Invocations of `/speckit:plan` are already inside a write flow, so Gate 3 is pre-answered by command dispatch — no extra inference needed here.\n   - Store: prior_work_found = [yes/no], prior_work_count = [N]\n\n5. Prior-work loading question needed ONLY if user selects A or C for spec folder AND prior continuity records exist for this spec.\n\n5a. CHECK intake contract requirement when `spec_path` is explicit or can be derived from Q1 / `--phase-folder`:\n   ├─ Inspect `{spec_path}` for `spec.md`, `description.json`, `graph-metadata.json`, and tracked placeholder markers per intake_contract.md §3 Folder State Classification\n   ├─ Normalize `folder_state` to one of: `empty-folder` | `partial-folder` | `repair-mode` | `placeholder-upgrade` | `populated-folder`\n   ├─ `folder_state == populated-folder` AND `intake_only == FALSE` → `intake_required = FALSE` and preserve the current prompt unchanged\n   ├─ `folder_state == populated-folder` AND `intake_only == TRUE` → no-op exit with informational message\n   └─ Otherwise → `intake_required = TRUE`, inherit the parent `execution_mode`, and run the intake contract inline before Step 1 continues (or halt after Emit phase if `intake_only == TRUE`)\n\n6. ASK with SINGLE prompt (include only applicable questions):\n\n   Q0. Feature Description (if not in command): What feature to plan?\n\n   Q1. Spec Folder (required):\n     A) Use existing [suggest if found]  B) Create new: specs/[###]-[slug]/\n     C) Update related [if match found]  D) Skip documentation\n     E) Phase folder — target a specific phase child (e.g., specs/NNN-name/001-phase/)\n\n   Q2. Execution Mode (if no suffix):\n     A) Autonomous - all 8 steps without approval\n     B) Interactive - pause at each step\n\n   Q3. Dispatch Mode (required):\n     A) Single Agent (Recommended)  B) Multi-Agent (1+2)  C) Multi-Agent (1+3)\n\n   Q4. Prior Work Context (when prior continuity records exist for this spec):\n     A) Load most recent spec-doc record  B) Load up to 3 most recent spec-doc records  C) Skip\n\n   Q5. Research Intent (required):\n     A) add_feature  B) fix_bug  C) refactor  D) understand\n\n   Q6. Phase Decomposition (if :with-phases not in command):\n     Create phased spec structure (parent + N child folders)?\n     A) No — single spec folder (default)\n     B) Yes — decompose into phases before planning\n\n   Q7. Phase Count (if phase_decomposition == TRUE and --phases not provided):\n     How many phases? (Default: 3)\n\n   Q8. Phase Names (if phase_decomposition == TRUE and --phase-names not provided):\n     Provide phase names? (Optional — auto-generated if skipped)\n     Example: \"data-model, api-layer, ui-components\"\n\n   **Intake contract block** (ONLY if `intake_required = TRUE`; keep this inside the SAME prompt, not a second command flow):\n\n   Execute the Q0–Q4+ consolidated intake interview per `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/intake_contract.md §5`. Questions cover: feature description, target folder state, documentation level, relationship capture, and relationship entries (grouped `depends_on` / `related_to` / `supersedes` by `packet_id`).\n\n   Reply format: \"B, A, A, C, A\" or \"Add auth, B, A, C, A\"\n\n7. WAIT for user response (DO NOT PROCEED)\n\n8. Parse response and store ALL results:\n   - feature_description = [from Q0 or $ARGUMENTS]\n   - spec_choice = [A/B/C/D/E from Q1]\n   - spec_path = [derived path or null if D]\n   - execution_mode = [AUTONOMOUS/INTERACTIVE from suffix or Q2]\n   - dispatch_mode = [single/multi_small/multi_large from Q3]\n   - memory_choice = [A/B/C from Q4, or N/A]\n   - research_intent = [add_feature/fix_bug/refactor/understand from Q5]\n   - IF `intake_required = TRUE`: bind `selected_level`, `start_state`, `repair_mode`, and `manual_relationships` from the inline intake-contract block (see intake_contract.md §6 for trio-publication semantics)\n   - IF intake contract adjusts the target: update `feature_description` and `spec_path` from the returned contract before Step 1\n   - IF `intake_only = TRUE`: halt here with STATUS=OK after intake Emit phase completes; do not proceed to Step 1","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":220,"totalLines":549,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/speckit/plan.md","time":{"start":1780738144593,"end":1780738144607}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0aedcfe7093f9903016a23e860846081918b2c20c23f3fba24"}},"id":"prt_e9c43b950001u7VhPV5s6tOrc3","sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeuERCb2AlX2T5Je","messageID":"msg_e9c4396ec001Vvcu0wnewU9A9A"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780738144614,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeuERCb2AlX2T5Je","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_DmwioCY0An5YtS2mheWeEPlY","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/learn.md","offset":1,"limit":240},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/learn.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: description: Create and manage constitutional rules — always-surface entries that appear at the top of every search result.\n3: argument-hint: \"[rule-description] | list | edit <filename> | remove <filename> | budget\"\n4: allowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Glob, Bash, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_list, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan\n5: ---\n6: \n7: # 🚨 MANDATORY FIRST ACTION - DO NOT SKIP\n8: \n9: **BEFORE READING ANYTHING ELSE IN THIS FILE, CHECK `$ARGUMENTS`:**\n10: \n11: ```text\n12: IF $ARGUMENTS is empty, undefined, or contains only whitespace:\n13:     → SHOW OVERVIEW DASHBOARD (Section 6)\n14:     → Dashboard includes action hints at the bottom\n15:     → WAIT for user to type a follow-up action\n16:     → Only THEN route to the appropriate section\n17: \n18: IF $ARGUMENTS starts with \"edit\" and has NO <filename>:\n19:     → STOP IMMEDIATELY\n20:     → Run Glob(\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/constitutional/*.md\")\n21:     → Present available files (exclude README.md)\n22:     → WAIT for user selection\n23: \n24: IF $ARGUMENTS starts with \"remove\" and has NO <filename>:\n25:     → STOP IMMEDIATELY\n26:     → Run Glob(\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/constitutional/*.md\")\n27:     → Present available files (exclude README.md)\n28:     → WAIT for user selection\n29: \n30: IF $ARGUMENTS contains recognized input:\n31:     → Continue reading this file and route per Section 4\n32: ```\n33: \n34: **CRITICAL RULES:**\n35: - **DO NOT** infer rule content from conversation context when creating\n36: - **DO NOT** assume what the user wants based on screenshots or open files\n37: - When no arguments: show the dashboard, do NOT ask a question\n38: \n39: > SECURITY: Constitutional rules are high-impact global rules. In multi-agent or shared environments, create/edit/remove operations should verify actor identity and require owner or admin role before proceeding.\n40: \n41: ---\n42: \n43: # /memory:learn — Constitutional Rule Manager\n44: \n45: Create, list, edit, and remove **constitutional rules**, the highest-tier entries that surface at the top of every search result, never decay, and carry a 3.0x search boost.\n46: \n47: ---\n48: \n49: ## 1. PURPOSE\n50: \n51: Provide a dedicated command for managing constitutional rules, the most powerful tier in the Spec Kit Memory system. Constitutional rules always appear at the top of every `memory_search()` result and never decay. This command handles the full lifecycle: creation with proper frontmatter and ANCHOR format, budget validation, editing, and removal.\n52: \n53: **Key difference from `/memory:save`:**\n54: - `/memory:save` = Session context routed into canonical packet continuity surfaces\n55: - `/memory:learn` = Constitutional rules saved to `constitutional/` (always-surface tier)\n56: \n57: ### Constitutional Tier Reference\n58: \n59: | Property | Constitutional | Critical | Normal |\n60: |----------|---------------|----------|--------|\n61: | Surfaces in | EVERY search | Relevant only | Relevant only |\n62: | Search boost | 3.0x | 2.0x | 1.0x |\n63: | Decays | Never | Never | Yes (90-day) |\n64: | Token budget | ~2000 total | Unlimited | Unlimited |\n65: | Location | `constitutional/` | Canonical packet continuity surfaces | Canonical packet continuity surfaces |\n66: \n67: **When NOT constitutional** (suggest `/memory:save` instead):\n68: - Session-specific context\n69: - Rules for one project area only\n70: - Temporary notes or implementation details\n71: \n72: ---\n73: \n74: ## 2. CONTRACT\n75: \n76: ```yaml\n77: role: Constitutional Rule Manager\n78: purpose: Create and manage always-surface constitutional rules in the constitutional tier\n79: destination: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/constitutional/\n80: ```\n81: \n82: **Inputs:** `$ARGUMENTS`: Rule description, or subcommand (list, edit, remove, budget)\n83: **Outputs:** `STATUS=<OK|FAIL|CANCELLED> ACTION=<overview|created|listed|edited|removed|budget>`\n84: \n85: ---\n86: \n87: ## 3. QUICK REFERENCE\n88: \n89: | Command | Result |\n90: |---------|--------|\n91: | `/memory:learn Never commit API keys` | Create constitutional rule |\n92: | `/memory:learn list` | Show all constitutional rules + budget |\n93: | `/memory:learn edit never-commit-secrets.md` | Edit existing constitutional rule |\n94: | `/memory:learn remove never-commit-secrets.md` | Remove constitutional rule (destructive) |\n95: | `/memory:learn budget` | Token budget status (~2000 max) |\n96: \n97: ---\n98: \n99: ## 4. ARGUMENT ROUTING\n100: \n101: ```text\n102: $ARGUMENTS\n103:     │\n104:     ├─► Empty (no args)\n105:     │   └─► OVERVIEW DASHBOARD (Section 6)\n106:     │\n107:     ├─► First word matches ACTION KEYWORD (case-insensitive)\n108:     │   ├─► \"list\"                → LIST DASHBOARD (Section 7)\n109:     │   ├─► \"edit <filename>\"     → EDIT MODE (Section 8)\n110:     │   ├─► \"remove <filename>\"   → REMOVE MODE (Section 9) [destructive]\n111:     │   └─► \"budget\"              → BUDGET DASHBOARD (Section 10)\n112:     │\n113:     └─► Any other text (natural language rule)\n114:         └─► CREATE (Section 5) with $ARGUMENTS as rule description\n115: ```\n116: \n117: ---\n118: \n119: ## 5. CREATE MODE\n120: \n121: ### Step 1: Extract Rule\n122: \n123: Use rule text from `$ARGUMENTS` (or user's answer to mandatory gate prompt).\n124: \n125: ### Step 2: Qualify\n126: \n127: Verify this rule belongs in the constitutional tier:\n128: \n129: ```text\n130: Self-check (do NOT prompt user unless one or more answers are \"no\"):\n131:   □ Does this rule apply to EVERY interaction? (not just one domain)\n132:   □ Would forgetting it cause significant problems?\n133:   □ Is it a safety constraint or hard requirement?\n134: \n135: IF all yes → PROCEED to Step 3\n136: IF any no → Display:\n137: \n138: MEMORY:LEARN\n139: ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n140: \n141:   ⚠ This rule may not need constitutional tier.\n142:   Constitutional rules appear in EVERY search\n143:   and consume shared budget (~2000 tokens).\n144: \n145: ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n146: [y] proceed anyway    [s] use /memory:save instead    [n] cancel\n147: ```\n148: \n149: ### Step 3: Structure the Memory\n150: \n151: Generate a properly formatted constitutional rule document:\n152: \n153: ```markdown\n154: ---\n155: title: \"<RULE_TITLE>\"\n156: importanceTier: constitutional\n157: contextType: <decision|implementation|discovery>\n158: triggerPhrases:\n159:   - <keyword1>\n160:   - <keyword2>\n161:   - <keyword3>\n162: ---\n163: \n164: # <RULE_TITLE>\n165: \n166: > <One-line description of what this rule enforces.>\n167: \n168: <!-- ANCHOR:rule -->\n169: ## Rule\n170: \n171: **TRIGGER:** <When this rule activates>\n172: \n173: **ACTION:**\n174: 1. <Step 1>\n175: 2. <Step 2>\n176: 3. <Step 3>\n177: \n178: **RATIONALE:** <Why this rule exists>\n179: <!-- /ANCHOR:rule -->\n180: \n181: *Constitutional Memory — Always surfaces at top of search results*\n182: ```\n183: \n184: **Structuring guidelines:**\n185: - Title: ALL CAPS descriptor, max 60 chars\n186: - Filename: `kebab-case.md` (e.g., `never-commit-secrets.md`)\n187: - Trigger phrases: 5-20 specific action words. No common words (\"the\", \"a\")\n188: - Content: Concise, each file should be <200 tokens\n189: - ANCHOR tags: Wrap main sections for section-level retrieval\n190: \n191: **SHOW the generated file to user and WAIT for approval before writing.**\n192: \n193: ### Step 4: Budget Check\n194: \n195: ```text\n196: 1. Glob(\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/constitutional/*.md\")\n197:    → Exclude README.md\n198: \n199: 2. Read each file, estimate token count (~4 chars per token)\n200: \n201: 3. Estimate new file token count\n202: \n203: 4. IF (existing + new) > 2000 tokens:\n204:      Display budget warning (see dashboard below)\n205:      Options: [t]rim existing | [s]horten new | [c]ancel\n206:      WAIT for user decision\n207: \n208: 5. IF within budget → PROCEED\n209: ```\n210: \n211: ### Step 5: Write, Index, Verify\n212: \n213: ```text\n214: 1. WRITE file:\n215:    Write(\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/constitutional/<filename>.md\")\n216: \n217: 2. INDEX in indexed-continuity database:\n218:    memory_save({\n219:      filePath: \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/constitutional/<filename>.md\",\n220:      force: true\n221:    })\n222: \n223: 3. VERIFY it surfaces:\n224:    memory_search({ query: \"<one trigger phrase>\", limit: 3 })\n225:    → Confirm isConstitutional: true in results\n226: ```\n227: \n228: ### Step 6: Display Confirmation\n229: \n230: ```text\n231: MEMORY:LEARN\n232: ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n233: \n234:   Created     <filename>.md\n235:   Title       <rule_title>\n236:   Tier        constitutional (3.0x boost · no decay)\n237:   Location    .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/constitutional/\n238: \n239: → Triggers ──────────────────────────────────────────\n240:   <trigger1> · <trigger2> · <trigger3> · <trigger4>\n\n(Showing lines 1-240 of 522. Use offset=241 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: Create and manage constitutional rules — always-surface entries that appear at the top of every search result.\nargument-hint: \"[rule-description] | list | edit <filename> | remove <filename> | budget\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Glob, Bash, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_list, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan\n---\n\n# 🚨 MANDATORY FIRST ACTION - DO NOT SKIP\n\n**BEFORE READING ANYTHING ELSE IN THIS FILE, CHECK `$ARGUMENTS`:**\n\n```text\nIF $ARGUMENTS is empty, undefined, or contains only whitespace:\n    → SHOW OVERVIEW DASHBOARD (Section 6)\n    → Dashboard includes action hints at the bottom\n    → WAIT for user to type a follow-up action\n    → Only THEN route to the appropriate section\n\nIF $ARGUMENTS starts with \"edit\" and has NO <filename>:\n    → STOP IMMEDIATELY\n    → Run Glob(\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/constitutional/*.md\")","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/learn.md","text":"---\ndescription: Create and manage constitutional rules — always-surface entries that appear at the top of every search result.\nargument-hint: \"[rule-description] | list | edit <filename> | remove <filename> | budget\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Glob, Bash, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_list, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan\n---\n\n# 🚨 MANDATORY FIRST ACTION - DO NOT SKIP\n\n**BEFORE READING ANYTHING ELSE IN THIS FILE, CHECK `$ARGUMENTS`:**\n\n```text\nIF $ARGUMENTS is empty, undefined, or contains only whitespace:\n    → SHOW OVERVIEW DASHBOARD (Section 6)\n    → Dashboard includes action hints at the bottom\n    → WAIT for user to type a follow-up action\n    → Only THEN route to the appropriate section\n\nIF $ARGUMENTS starts with \"edit\" and has NO <filename>:\n    → STOP IMMEDIATELY\n    → Run Glob(\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/constitutional/*.md\")\n    → Present available files (exclude README.md)\n    → WAIT for user selection\n\nIF $ARGUMENTS starts with \"remove\" and has NO <filename>:\n    → STOP IMMEDIATELY\n    → Run Glob(\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/constitutional/*.md\")\n    → Present available files (exclude README.md)\n    → WAIT for user selection\n\nIF $ARGUMENTS contains recognized input:\n    → Continue reading this file and route per Section 4\n```\n\n**CRITICAL RULES:**\n- **DO NOT** infer rule content from conversation context when creating\n- **DO NOT** assume what the user wants based on screenshots or open files\n- When no arguments: show the dashboard, do NOT ask a question\n\n> SECURITY: Constitutional rules are high-impact global rules. In multi-agent or shared environments, create/edit/remove operations should verify actor identity and require owner or admin role before proceeding.\n\n---\n\n# /memory:learn — Constitutional Rule Manager\n\nCreate, list, edit, and remove **constitutional rules**, the highest-tier entries that surface at the top of every search result, never decay, and carry a 3.0x search boost.\n\n---\n\n## 1. PURPOSE\n\nProvide a dedicated command for managing constitutional rules, the most powerful tier in the Spec Kit Memory system. Constitutional rules always appear at the top of every `memory_search()` result and never decay. This command handles the full lifecycle: creation with proper frontmatter and ANCHOR format, budget validation, editing, and removal.\n\n**Key difference from `/memory:save`:**\n- `/memory:save` = Session context routed into canonical packet continuity surfaces\n- `/memory:learn` = Constitutional rules saved to `constitutional/` (always-surface tier)\n\n### Constitutional Tier Reference\n\n| Property | Constitutional | Critical | Normal |\n|----------|---------------|----------|--------|\n| Surfaces in | EVERY search | Relevant only | Relevant only |\n| Search boost | 3.0x | 2.0x | 1.0x |\n| Decays | Never | Never | Yes (90-day) |\n| Token budget | ~2000 total | Unlimited | Unlimited |\n| Location | `constitutional/` | Canonical packet continuity surfaces | Canonical packet continuity surfaces |\n\n**When NOT constitutional** (suggest `/memory:save` instead):\n- Session-specific context\n- Rules for one project area only\n- Temporary notes or implementation details\n\n---\n\n## 2. CONTRACT\n\n```yaml\nrole: Constitutional Rule Manager\npurpose: Create and manage always-surface constitutional rules in the constitutional tier\ndestination: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/constitutional/\n```\n\n**Inputs:** `$ARGUMENTS`: Rule description, or subcommand (list, edit, remove, budget)\n**Outputs:** `STATUS=<OK|FAIL|CANCELLED> ACTION=<overview|created|listed|edited|removed|budget>`\n\n---\n\n## 3. QUICK REFERENCE\n\n| Command | Result |\n|---------|--------|\n| `/memory:learn Never commit API keys` | Create constitutional rule |\n| `/memory:learn list` | Show all constitutional rules + budget |\n| `/memory:learn edit never-commit-secrets.md` | Edit existing constitutional rule |\n| `/memory:learn remove never-commit-secrets.md` | Remove constitutional rule (destructive) |\n| `/memory:learn budget` | Token budget status (~2000 max) |\n\n---\n\n## 4. ARGUMENT ROUTING\n\n```text\n$ARGUMENTS\n    │\n    ├─► Empty (no args)\n    │   └─► OVERVIEW DASHBOARD (Section 6)\n    │\n    ├─► First word matches ACTION KEYWORD (case-insensitive)\n    │   ├─► \"list\"                → LIST DASHBOARD (Section 7)\n    │   ├─► \"edit <filename>\"     → EDIT MODE (Section 8)\n    │   ├─► \"remove <filename>\"   → REMOVE MODE (Section 9) [destructive]\n    │   └─► \"budget\"              → BUDGET DASHBOARD (Section 10)\n    │\n    └─► Any other text (natural language rule)\n        └─► CREATE (Section 5) with $ARGUMENTS as rule description\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. CREATE MODE\n\n### Step 1: Extract Rule\n\nUse rule text from `$ARGUMENTS` (or user's answer to mandatory gate prompt).\n\n### Step 2: Qualify\n\nVerify this rule belongs in the constitutional tier:\n\n```text\nSelf-check (do NOT prompt user unless one or more answers are \"no\"):\n  □ Does this rule apply to EVERY interaction? (not just one domain)\n  □ Would forgetting it cause significant problems?\n  □ Is it a safety constraint or hard requirement?\n\nIF all yes → PROCEED to Step 3\nIF any no → Display:\n\nMEMORY:LEARN\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n\n  ⚠ This rule may not need constitutional tier.\n  Constitutional rules appear in EVERY search\n  and consume shared budget (~2000 tokens).\n\n─────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n[y] proceed anyway    [s] use /memory:save instead    [n] cancel\n```\n\n### Step 3: Structure the Memory\n\nGenerate a properly formatted constitutional rule document:\n\n```markdown\n---\ntitle: \"<RULE_TITLE>\"\nimportanceTier: constitutional\ncontextType: <decision|implementation|discovery>\ntriggerPhrases:\n  - <keyword1>\n  - <keyword2>\n  - <keyword3>\n---\n\n# <RULE_TITLE>\n\n> <One-line description of what this rule enforces.>\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:rule -->\n## Rule\n\n**TRIGGER:** <When this rule activates>\n\n**ACTION:**\n1. <Step 1>\n2. <Step 2>\n3. <Step 3>\n\n**RATIONALE:** <Why this rule exists>\n<!-- /ANCHOR:rule -->\n\n*Constitutional Memory — Always surfaces at top of search results*\n```\n\n**Structuring guidelines:**\n- Title: ALL CAPS descriptor, max 60 chars\n- Filename: `kebab-case.md` (e.g., `never-commit-secrets.md`)\n- Trigger phrases: 5-20 specific action words. No common words (\"the\", \"a\")\n- Content: Concise, each file should be <200 tokens\n- ANCHOR tags: Wrap main sections for section-level retrieval\n\n**SHOW the generated file to user and WAIT for approval before writing.**\n\n### Step 4: Budget Check\n\n```text\n1. Glob(\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/constitutional/*.md\")\n   → Exclude README.md\n\n2. Read each file, estimate token count (~4 chars per token)\n\n3. Estimate new file token count\n\n4. IF (existing + new) > 2000 tokens:\n     Display budget warning (see dashboard below)\n     Options: [t]rim existing | [s]horten new | [c]ancel\n     WAIT for user decision\n\n5. IF within budget → PROCEED\n```\n\n### Step 5: Write, Index, Verify\n\n```text\n1. WRITE file:\n   Write(\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/constitutional/<filename>.md\")\n\n2. INDEX in indexed-continuity database:\n   memory_save({\n     filePath: \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/constitutional/<filename>.md\",\n     force: true\n   })\n\n3. VERIFY it surfaces:\n   memory_search({ query: \"<one trigger phrase>\", limit: 3 })\n   → Confirm isConstitutional: true in results\n```\n\n### Step 6: Display Confirmation\n\n```text\nMEMORY:LEARN\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n\n  Created     <filename>.md\n  Title       <rule_title>\n  Tier        constitutional (3.0x boost · no decay)\n  Location    .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/constitutional/\n\n→ Triggers ──────────────────────────────────────────\n  <trigger1> · <trigger2> · <trigger3> · <trigger4>","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":240,"totalLines":522,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/memory/learn.md","time":{"start":1780738144591,"end":1780738144608}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0aedcfe7093f9903016a23e86084588191a1a0c074767fc73f"}},"id":"prt_e9c43b94e001lmet419v4ZoAwO","sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeuERCb2AlX2T5Je","messageID":"msg_e9c4396ec001Vvcu0wnewU9A9A"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780738144614,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeuERCb2AlX2T5Je","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_KLtwugkYmRQ1nnvwfgpcPhX7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/manage.md","offset":1,"limit":240},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/manage.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: description: Manage indexed-continuity DB: stats, scan, cleanup, retention, validate, checkpoint, ingest.\n3: argument-hint: \"[scan [--force]] | [cleanup] | [retention-sweep [--dry-run]] | [bulk-delete <tier> [--older-than <days>] [--folder <spec>]] | [tier <id> <tier>] | [triggers <id>] | [validate <id> <useful|not>] | [delete <id>] | [health] | [checkpoint <subcommand>] | [ingest <subcommand>]\"\n4: allowed-tools: Read, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_list, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_validate, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_update, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_bulk_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_retention_sweep, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_health, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_create, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_restore, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_list, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_ingest_start, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_ingest_status, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_ingest_cancel\n5: ---\n6: \n7: # 🚨 MANDATORY FIRST ACTION - DO NOT SKIP\n8: \n9: > **NEVER use Bash to query the database directly. NEVER run `sqlite3` commands.**\n10: > All database access MUST go through the `mk_spec_memory_*` MCP tools listed in `allowed-tools`.\n11: > If an MCP tool returns an error, report the error to the user: do NOT fall back to raw SQL via Bash.\n12: \n13: **STATUS: BLOCKED** (until argument is parsed)\n14: \n15: ```text\n16: BEFORE executing ANY workflow:\n17: \n18: 1. PARSE $ARGUMENTS to determine mode\n19: 2. VALIDATE mode is recognized (stats, scan, cleanup, retention-sweep, bulk-delete, tier, triggers, validate, delete, health, checkpoint, ingest)\n20:    - IF $ARGUMENTS is empty → mode = \"stats\" (default)\n21: 3. For modes requiring <id>: VERIFY id is provided and numeric\n22: 4. For modes requiring <name>: VERIFY name is provided\n23: \n24: IF mode unrecognized:\n25:   → STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"Unknown mode: <mode>. Valid: scan, cleanup, retention-sweep, bulk-delete, tier, triggers, validate, delete, health, checkpoint, ingest\"\n26: \n27: IF required parameter missing:\n28:   → STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"Missing required parameter for <mode>\"\n29: ```\n30: \n31: ---\n32: \n33: # Memory Management Command\n34: \n35: Unified management interface for the indexed-continuity database: scan for new files, cleanup old spec-doc records, bulk-delete by tier, change tiers, edit triggers, validate usefulness, delete entries, check health, manage checkpoints, run async ingest jobs.\n36: \n37: ```yaml\n38: role: Memory Database Administrator\n39: purpose: Unified management interface for indexed-continuity database maintenance, checkpoint operations, and async ingest management\n40: action: Route through scan, cleanup, retention-sweep, bulk-delete, tier, triggers, validate, delete, health, checkpoint, or ingest based on arguments\n41: operating_mode:\n42:   workflow: interactive_management\n43:   approvals: cleanup_delete_restore_require_confirmation\n44: ```\n45: \n46: This is a markdown-owned command contract. `/memory:*` commands intentionally do\n47: not have external YAML assets; validators and reviewers should check the inline\n48: operating-mode block and markdown workflow steps.\n49: \n50: ---\n51: \n52: ## 0. INSTRUCTIONS\n53: \n54: Parse the requested mode first, then execute only the matching management workflow. Canonical spec docs are the only active continuity source; the retired `spec-doc/*.md` surface is no longer accepted by the runtime. Retention cleanup uses `memory_retention_sweep` (`tool-schemas.ts:330`)\n55: \n56: ---\n57: \n58: ## 1. PURPOSE\n59: \n60: Provide a unified interface for the indexed-continuity database **management** operations:\n61: - Indexing new files and scanning for updates\n62: - Cleanup of old or deprecated spec-doc records\n63: - Retention sweep of expired governed records\n64: - Tier management and trigger editing\n65: - Validation feedback and deletion\n66: - Health checks and diagnostics\n67: - Checkpoint creation, restoration, listing, and deletion\n68: \n69: **Separation from `/memory:search`:**\n70: - `/memory:search` = RETRIEVAL + ANALYSIS (intent-aware search, epistemic baselines, causal graph, evaluation)\n71: - `/memory:manage` = MANAGEMENT LIFECYCLE (modify, delete, maintain, checkpoint, ingest)\n72: \n73: ---\n74: \n75: ## 2. CONTRACT\n76: \n77: **Inputs:** `$ARGUMENTS`: Mode keyword with optional parameters\n78: **Outputs:** `STATUS=<OK|FAIL>` with mode-specific output\n79: \n80: ### Argument Patterns\n81: \n82: | Pattern                                  | Mode              | Example                                                |\n83: | ---------------------------------------- | ----------------- | ------------------------------------------------------ |\n84: | (empty)                                  | Stats             | `/memory:manage`                                       |\n85: | `scan`                                   | Scan              | `/memory:manage scan`                                  |\n86: | `scan --force`                           | Force Scan        | `/memory:manage scan --force`                          |\n87: | `cleanup`                                | Cleanup           | `/memory:manage cleanup`                               |\n88: | `retention-sweep --dry-run`              | Retention Sweep   | `/memory:manage retention-sweep --dry-run`             |\n89: | `bulk-delete <tier>`                     | Bulk Delete       | `/memory:manage bulk-delete deprecated`                |\n90: | `bulk-delete <tier> --older-than <days>` | Bulk Delete       | `/memory:manage bulk-delete temporary --older-than 30` |\n91: | `bulk-delete <tier> --folder <spec>`     | Bulk Delete       | `/memory:manage bulk-delete normal --folder 007-auth`  |\n92: | `tier <id> <tier>`                       | Tier Change       | `/memory:manage tier 42 critical`                      |\n93: | `triggers <id>`                          | Edit Triggers     | `/memory:manage triggers 42`                           |\n94: | `validate <id> useful`                   | Validate          | `/memory:manage validate 42 useful`                    |\n95: | `validate <id> not`                      | Validate          | `/memory:manage validate 42 not`                       |\n96: | `delete <id>`                            | Delete            | `/memory:manage delete 42`                             |\n97: | `health`                                 | Health            | `/memory:manage health`                                |\n98: | `checkpoint create <name>`               | Create Checkpoint | `/memory:manage checkpoint create before-refactor`     |\n99: | `checkpoint restore <name>`              | Restore           | `/memory:manage checkpoint restore before-refactor`    |\n100: | `checkpoint list`                        | List Checkpoints  | `/memory:manage checkpoint list`                       |\n101: | `checkpoint delete <name>`               | Delete Checkpoint | `/memory:manage checkpoint delete old-checkpoint`      |\n102: | `ingest start <path1> [path2 ...]`       | Start Ingest      | `/memory:manage ingest start /path/file.md`            |\n103: | `ingest status <jobId>`                  | Ingest Status     | `/memory:manage ingest status abc-123`                 |\n104: | `ingest cancel <jobId>`                  | Cancel Ingest     | `/memory:manage ingest cancel abc-123`                 |\n105: \n106: ### Importance Tiers\n107: \n108: | Tier           | Description                        |\n109: | -------------- | ---------------------------------- |\n110: | constitutional | Universal rules (~2000 tokens max) |\n111: | critical       | Architecture, core patterns        |\n112: | important      | Key implementations                |\n113: | normal         | General context                    |\n114: | temporary      | Short-term, WIP                    |\n115: | deprecated     | Mark as outdated                   |\n116: \n117: ---\n118: \n119: ## 3. QUICK REFERENCE\n120: \n121: | Command                                                | Result                    |\n122: | ------------------------------------------------------ | ------------------------- |\n123: | `/memory:manage`                                       | Stats dashboard           |\n124: | `/memory:manage scan`                                  | Index new files           |\n125: | `/memory:manage scan --force`                          | Re-index all files        |\n126: | `/memory:manage cleanup`                               | Cleanup old memories      |\n127: | `/memory:manage bulk-delete deprecated`                | Delete all deprecated     |\n128: | `/memory:manage bulk-delete temporary --older-than 30` | Delete temporary >30 days |\n129: | `/memory:manage tier 42 critical`                      | Change tier               |\n130: | `/memory:manage triggers 42`                           | Edit triggers             |\n131: | `/memory:manage validate 42 useful`                    | Mark as useful            |\n132: | `/memory:manage validate 42 not`                       | Mark as not useful        |\n133: | `/memory:manage delete 42`                             | Delete memory             |\n134: | `/memory:manage health`                                | System health check       |\n135: | `/memory:manage checkpoint create \"name\"`              | Save indexed-continuity state |\n136: | `/memory:manage checkpoint restore \"name\"`             | Restore to saved state    |\n137: | `/memory:manage checkpoint list`                       | Show all checkpoints      |\n138: | `/memory:manage checkpoint delete \"name\"`              | Remove checkpoint         |\n139: | `/memory:manage ingest start /path/file.md`            | Start async ingest job    |\n140: | `/memory:manage ingest status abc-123`                 | Check ingest progress     |\n141: | `/memory:manage ingest cancel abc-123`                 | Cancel ingest job         |\n142: \n143: ---\n144: \n145: ## 4. ARGUMENT ROUTING\n146: \n147: ```text\n148: $ARGUMENTS\n149:     │\n150:     ├─ Empty (no args)       → STATS DASHBOARD (Section 5)\n151:     ├─ \"scan [--force]\"      → SCAN MODE (Section 6)\n152:     ├─ \"cleanup\"             → CLEANUP MODE (Section 7)\n153:     ├─ \"bulk-delete <tier>\"  → BULK DELETE MODE (Section 8)\n154:     ├─ \"tier <id> <tier>\"    → TIER MANAGEMENT (Section 9)\n155:     ├─ \"triggers <id>\"       → TRIGGER EDIT (Section 10)\n156:     ├─ \"validate <id> <u|n>\" → VALIDATE MODE (Section 11)\n157:     ├─ \"delete <id>\"         → DELETE MODE (Section 12)\n158:     ├─ \"health\"              → HEALTH CHECK (Section 13)\n159:     ├─ \"checkpoint <sub>\"    → CHECKPOINT OPERATIONS (Section 14)\n160:     │   ├─ \"create <name>\"   → Create snapshot\n161:     │   ├─ \"restore <name>\"  → Restore (confirmation required)\n162:     │   ├─ \"list\"            → List snapshots\n163:     │   └─ \"delete <name>\"   → Delete snapshot\n164:     ├─ \"ingest <sub>\"       → INGEST MODE (Section 15)\n165:     │   ├─ \"start <paths>\"   → Start async job\n166:     │   ├─ \"status <jobId>\"  → Check progress\n167:     │   └─ \"cancel <jobId>\"  → Cancel running job\n168: ```\n169: \n170: ---\n171: \n172: ## 5. STATS DASHBOARD\n173: \n174: **Trigger:** `/memory:manage` with no arguments\n175: \n176: Call `memory_stats()` and `memory_list({ limit: 10, sortBy: \"updated_at\" })` in parallel. Display:\n177: \n178: ```text\n179: MEMORY:STATS\n180: ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n181: \n182:   Total       <N>\n183:   Size        <size>\n184:   Indexed     <date>\n185: \n186: → Tier Distribution ────────────────────────────────\n187:   constitutional  ██░░░░░░░░  <N>\n188:   critical        ████░░░░░░  <N>\n189:   important       ██████░░░░  <N>\n190:   normal          █████████░  <N>\n191:   temporary       ██░░░░░░░░  <N>\n192:   deprecated      █░░░░░░░░░  <N>\n193: \n194: → Top Folders ──────────────────────────────────────\n195:   <folder-1>  █████████░  <N>\n196:   <folder-2>  ██████░░░░  <N>\n197:   <folder-3>  ████░░░░░░  <N>\n198: \n199: ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n200: [scan] index    [cleanup] remove    [health] check    [checkpoint] ops\n201: \n202: STATUS=OK\n203: ```\n204: \n205: User Input: Type action name (scan, cleanup, health, checkpoint, quit) to proceed\n206: \n207: > **Retrieval Metrics (P2):** Additional internal retrieval metrics are tracked by the search pipeline; dashboard exposure remains deferred until handler wiring is completed.\n208: \n209: ---\n210: \n211: ## 6. SCAN MODE\n212: \n213: **Trigger:** `/memory:manage scan` or `/memory:manage scan --force`\n214: \n215: Normal scan skips unchanged files (mtime check). Force scan re-indexes all files regardless.\n216: \n217: ### Confirmation Gate\n218: \n219: **⚠️ Confirmation required before every scan.**\n220: \n221: Before running `memory_index_scan`, ask:\n222: \n223: ```text\n224: MEMORY:SCAN\n225: ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n226: \n227: → Scan Mode ────────────────────────────────────────\n228:   [n] normal  incremental scan (default)\n229:   [f] force   full re-index\n230:   [b] back    cancel\n231: ```\n232: \n233: Map selection to `force` for this run. **WAIT for user selection** before calling `memory_index_scan`.\n234: \n235: ### Frontmatter Normalization Prerequisite (For Corpus Rebuilds)\n236: \n237: Before bulk re-index operations after documentation/template changes, run normalization first:\n238: \n239: ```bash\n240: # 1) Dry-run normalization\n\n(Showing lines 1-240 of 1061. Use offset=241 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: Manage indexed-continuity DB: stats, scan, cleanup, retention, validate, checkpoint, ingest.\nargument-hint: \"[scan [--force]] | [cleanup] | [retention-sweep [--dry-run]] | [bulk-delete <tier> [--older-than <days>] [--folder <spec>]] | [tier <id> <tier>] | [triggers <id>] | [validate <id> <useful|not>] | [delete <id>] | [health] | [checkpoint <subcommand>] | [ingest <subcommand>]\"\nallowed-tools: Read, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_list, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_validate, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_update, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_bulk_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_retention_sweep, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_health, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_create, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_restore, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_list, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_ingest_start, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_ingest_status, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_ingest_cancel\n---\n\n# 🚨 MANDATORY FIRST ACTION - DO NOT SKIP\n\n> **NEVER use Bash to query the database directly. NEVER run `sqlite3` commands.**\n> All database access MUST go through the `mk_spec_memory_*` MCP tools listed in `allowed-tools`.\n> If an MCP tool returns an error, report the error to the user: do NOT fall back to raw SQL via Bash.\n\n**STATUS: BLOCKED** (until argument is parsed)\n\n```text\nBEFORE executing ANY workflow:\n\n1. PARSE $ARGUMENTS to determine mode\n2. VALIDATE mode is recognized (stats, scan, cleanup, retention-sweep, bulk-delete, tier, triggers, validate, delete, health, checkpoint, ingest)\n   - IF $ARGUMENTS is empty → mode = \"stats\" (default)","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/manage.md","text":"---\ndescription: Manage indexed-continuity DB: stats, scan, cleanup, retention, validate, checkpoint, ingest.\nargument-hint: \"[scan [--force]] | [cleanup] | [retention-sweep [--dry-run]] | [bulk-delete <tier> [--older-than <days>] [--folder <spec>]] | [tier <id> <tier>] | [triggers <id>] | [validate <id> <useful|not>] | [delete <id>] | [health] | [checkpoint <subcommand>] | [ingest <subcommand>]\"\nallowed-tools: Read, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_list, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_validate, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_update, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_bulk_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_retention_sweep, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_health, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_create, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_restore, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_list, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_ingest_start, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_ingest_status, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_ingest_cancel\n---\n\n# 🚨 MANDATORY FIRST ACTION - DO NOT SKIP\n\n> **NEVER use Bash to query the database directly. NEVER run `sqlite3` commands.**\n> All database access MUST go through the `mk_spec_memory_*` MCP tools listed in `allowed-tools`.\n> If an MCP tool returns an error, report the error to the user: do NOT fall back to raw SQL via Bash.\n\n**STATUS: BLOCKED** (until argument is parsed)\n\n```text\nBEFORE executing ANY workflow:\n\n1. PARSE $ARGUMENTS to determine mode\n2. VALIDATE mode is recognized (stats, scan, cleanup, retention-sweep, bulk-delete, tier, triggers, validate, delete, health, checkpoint, ingest)\n   - IF $ARGUMENTS is empty → mode = \"stats\" (default)\n3. For modes requiring <id>: VERIFY id is provided and numeric\n4. For modes requiring <name>: VERIFY name is provided\n\nIF mode unrecognized:\n  → STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"Unknown mode: <mode>. Valid: scan, cleanup, retention-sweep, bulk-delete, tier, triggers, validate, delete, health, checkpoint, ingest\"\n\nIF required parameter missing:\n  → STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"Missing required parameter for <mode>\"\n```\n\n---\n\n# Memory Management Command\n\nUnified management interface for the indexed-continuity database: scan for new files, cleanup old spec-doc records, bulk-delete by tier, change tiers, edit triggers, validate usefulness, delete entries, check health, manage checkpoints, run async ingest jobs.\n\n```yaml\nrole: Memory Database Administrator\npurpose: Unified management interface for indexed-continuity database maintenance, checkpoint operations, and async ingest management\naction: Route through scan, cleanup, retention-sweep, bulk-delete, tier, triggers, validate, delete, health, checkpoint, or ingest based on arguments\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: interactive_management\n  approvals: cleanup_delete_restore_require_confirmation\n```\n\nThis is a markdown-owned command contract. `/memory:*` commands intentionally do\nnot have external YAML assets; validators and reviewers should check the inline\noperating-mode block and markdown workflow steps.\n\n---\n\n## 0. INSTRUCTIONS\n\nParse the requested mode first, then execute only the matching management workflow. Canonical spec docs are the only active continuity source; the retired `spec-doc/*.md` surface is no longer accepted by the runtime. Retention cleanup uses `memory_retention_sweep` (`tool-schemas.ts:330`)\n\n---\n\n## 1. PURPOSE\n\nProvide a unified interface for the indexed-continuity database **management** operations:\n- Indexing new files and scanning for updates\n- Cleanup of old or deprecated spec-doc records\n- Retention sweep of expired governed records\n- Tier management and trigger editing\n- Validation feedback and deletion\n- Health checks and diagnostics\n- Checkpoint creation, restoration, listing, and deletion\n\n**Separation from `/memory:search`:**\n- `/memory:search` = RETRIEVAL + ANALYSIS (intent-aware search, epistemic baselines, causal graph, evaluation)\n- `/memory:manage` = MANAGEMENT LIFECYCLE (modify, delete, maintain, checkpoint, ingest)\n\n---\n\n## 2. CONTRACT\n\n**Inputs:** `$ARGUMENTS`: Mode keyword with optional parameters\n**Outputs:** `STATUS=<OK|FAIL>` with mode-specific output\n\n### Argument Patterns\n\n| Pattern                                  | Mode              | Example                                                |\n| ---------------------------------------- | ----------------- | ------------------------------------------------------ |\n| (empty)                                  | Stats             | `/memory:manage`                                       |\n| `scan`                                   | Scan              | `/memory:manage scan`                                  |\n| `scan --force`                           | Force Scan        | `/memory:manage scan --force`                          |\n| `cleanup`                                | Cleanup           | `/memory:manage cleanup`                               |\n| `retention-sweep --dry-run`              | Retention Sweep   | `/memory:manage retention-sweep --dry-run`             |\n| `bulk-delete <tier>`                     | Bulk Delete       | `/memory:manage bulk-delete deprecated`                |\n| `bulk-delete <tier> --older-than <days>` | Bulk Delete       | `/memory:manage bulk-delete temporary --older-than 30` |\n| `bulk-delete <tier> --folder <spec>`     | Bulk Delete       | `/memory:manage bulk-delete normal --folder 007-auth`  |\n| `tier <id> <tier>`                       | Tier Change       | `/memory:manage tier 42 critical`                      |\n| `triggers <id>`                          | Edit Triggers     | `/memory:manage triggers 42`                           |\n| `validate <id> useful`                   | Validate          | `/memory:manage validate 42 useful`                    |\n| `validate <id> not`                      | Validate          | `/memory:manage validate 42 not`                       |\n| `delete <id>`                            | Delete            | `/memory:manage delete 42`                             |\n| `health`                                 | Health            | `/memory:manage health`                                |\n| `checkpoint create <name>`               | Create Checkpoint | `/memory:manage checkpoint create before-refactor`     |\n| `checkpoint restore <name>`              | Restore           | `/memory:manage checkpoint restore before-refactor`    |\n| `checkpoint list`                        | List Checkpoints  | `/memory:manage checkpoint list`                       |\n| `checkpoint delete <name>`               | Delete Checkpoint | `/memory:manage checkpoint delete old-checkpoint`      |\n| `ingest start <path1> [path2 ...]`       | Start Ingest      | `/memory:manage ingest start /path/file.md`            |\n| `ingest status <jobId>`                  | Ingest Status     | `/memory:manage ingest status abc-123`                 |\n| `ingest cancel <jobId>`                  | Cancel Ingest     | `/memory:manage ingest cancel abc-123`                 |\n\n### Importance Tiers\n\n| Tier           | Description                        |\n| -------------- | ---------------------------------- |\n| constitutional | Universal rules (~2000 tokens max) |\n| critical       | Architecture, core patterns        |\n| important      | Key implementations                |\n| normal         | General context                    |\n| temporary      | Short-term, WIP                    |\n| deprecated     | Mark as outdated                   |\n\n---\n\n## 3. QUICK REFERENCE\n\n| Command                                                | Result                    |\n| ------------------------------------------------------ | ------------------------- |\n| `/memory:manage`                                       | Stats dashboard           |\n| `/memory:manage scan`                                  | Index new files           |\n| `/memory:manage scan --force`                          | Re-index all files        |\n| `/memory:manage cleanup`                               | Cleanup old memories      |\n| `/memory:manage bulk-delete deprecated`                | Delete all deprecated     |\n| `/memory:manage bulk-delete temporary --older-than 30` | Delete temporary >30 days |\n| `/memory:manage tier 42 critical`                      | Change tier               |\n| `/memory:manage triggers 42`                           | Edit triggers             |\n| `/memory:manage validate 42 useful`                    | Mark as useful            |\n| `/memory:manage validate 42 not`                       | Mark as not useful        |\n| `/memory:manage delete 42`                             | Delete memory             |\n| `/memory:manage health`                                | System health check       |\n| `/memory:manage checkpoint create \"name\"`              | Save indexed-continuity state |\n| `/memory:manage checkpoint restore \"name\"`             | Restore to saved state    |\n| `/memory:manage checkpoint list`                       | Show all checkpoints      |\n| `/memory:manage checkpoint delete \"name\"`              | Remove checkpoint         |\n| `/memory:manage ingest start /path/file.md`            | Start async ingest job    |\n| `/memory:manage ingest status abc-123`                 | Check ingest progress     |\n| `/memory:manage ingest cancel abc-123`                 | Cancel ingest job         |\n\n---\n\n## 4. ARGUMENT ROUTING\n\n```text\n$ARGUMENTS\n    │\n    ├─ Empty (no args)       → STATS DASHBOARD (Section 5)\n    ├─ \"scan [--force]\"      → SCAN MODE (Section 6)\n    ├─ \"cleanup\"             → CLEANUP MODE (Section 7)\n    ├─ \"bulk-delete <tier>\"  → BULK DELETE MODE (Section 8)\n    ├─ \"tier <id> <tier>\"    → TIER MANAGEMENT (Section 9)\n    ├─ \"triggers <id>\"       → TRIGGER EDIT (Section 10)\n    ├─ \"validate <id> <u|n>\" → VALIDATE MODE (Section 11)\n    ├─ \"delete <id>\"         → DELETE MODE (Section 12)\n    ├─ \"health\"              → HEALTH CHECK (Section 13)\n    ├─ \"checkpoint <sub>\"    → CHECKPOINT OPERATIONS (Section 14)\n    │   ├─ \"create <name>\"   → Create snapshot\n    │   ├─ \"restore <name>\"  → Restore (confirmation required)\n    │   ├─ \"list\"            → List snapshots\n    │   └─ \"delete <name>\"   → Delete snapshot\n    ├─ \"ingest <sub>\"       → INGEST MODE (Section 15)\n    │   ├─ \"start <paths>\"   → Start async job\n    │   ├─ \"status <jobId>\"  → Check progress\n    │   └─ \"cancel <jobId>\"  → Cancel running job\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. STATS DASHBOARD\n\n**Trigger:** `/memory:manage` with no arguments\n\nCall `memory_stats()` and `memory_list({ limit: 10, sortBy: \"updated_at\" })` in parallel. Display:\n\n```text\nMEMORY:STATS\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n\n  Total       <N>\n  Size        <size>\n  Indexed     <date>\n\n→ Tier Distribution ────────────────────────────────\n  constitutional  ██░░░░░░░░  <N>\n  critical        ████░░░░░░  <N>\n  important       ██████░░░░  <N>\n  normal          █████████░  <N>\n  temporary       ██░░░░░░░░  <N>\n  deprecated      █░░░░░░░░░  <N>\n\n→ Top Folders ──────────────────────────────────────\n  <folder-1>  █████████░  <N>\n  <folder-2>  ██████░░░░  <N>\n  <folder-3>  ████░░░░░░  <N>\n\n─────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n[scan] index    [cleanup] remove    [health] check    [checkpoint] ops\n\nSTATUS=OK\n```\n\nUser Input: Type action name (scan, cleanup, health, checkpoint, quit) to proceed\n\n> **Retrieval Metrics (P2):** Additional internal retrieval metrics are tracked by the search pipeline; dashboard exposure remains deferred until handler wiring is completed.\n\n---\n\n## 6. SCAN MODE\n\n**Trigger:** `/memory:manage scan` or `/memory:manage scan --force`\n\nNormal scan skips unchanged files (mtime check). Force scan re-indexes all files regardless.\n\n### Confirmation Gate\n\n**⚠️ Confirmation required before every scan.**\n\nBefore running `memory_index_scan`, ask:\n\n```text\nMEMORY:SCAN\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n\n→ Scan Mode ────────────────────────────────────────\n  [n] normal  incremental scan (default)\n  [f] force   full re-index\n  [b] back    cancel\n```\n\nMap selection to `force` for this run. **WAIT for user selection** before calling `memory_index_scan`.\n\n### Frontmatter Normalization Prerequisite (For Corpus Rebuilds)\n\nBefore bulk re-index operations after documentation/template changes, run normalization first:\n\n```bash\n# 1) Dry-run normalization","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":240,"totalLines":1061,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/memory/manage.md","time":{"start":1780738144573,"end":1780738144610}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0aedcfe7093f9903016a23e86084488191b3c3be5845261517"}},"id":"prt_e9c43b93b001T9YuXXxvOlWCnn","sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeuERCb2AlX2T5Je","messageID":"msg_e9c4396ec001Vvcu0wnewU9A9A"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780738144614,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeuERCb2AlX2T5Je","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_vJZKn9sgYO3KAuEzRToAVED0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/search.md","offset":1,"limit":240},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/search.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: description: Unified continuity retrieval: spec-doc search, baselines, memory causal graph, ablations, dashboards.\n3: argument-hint: \"<query> [--intent:<type>] | preflight <specFolder> <taskId> | postflight <specFolder> <taskId> | history <specFolder> | causal <memoryId> | link <sourceId> <targetId> <relation> | unlink <edgeId> | causal-stats | ablation | dashboard\"\n4: allowed-tools: Read, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_quick_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_match_triggers, mcp__mk_spec_memory__task_preflight, mcp__mk_spec_memory__task_postflight, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_drift_why, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_link, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_unlink, mcp__mk_spec_memory__eval_run_ablation, mcp__mk_spec_memory__eval_reporting_dashboard, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_get_learning_history\n5: ---\n6: \n7: > **Code Graph bridge:** Structural routing may call stable `code_graph_*` MCP tools; the code-graph implementation and docs are owned by `.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/`.\n8: \n9: # 🚨 MANDATORY FIRST ACTION - DO NOT SKIP\n10: \n11: **BEFORE READING ANYTHING ELSE IN THIS FILE, CHECK `$ARGUMENTS`:**\n12: \n13: ```text\n14: IF $ARGUMENTS is empty, undefined, or contains only whitespace:\n15:     → STOP IMMEDIATELY\n16:     → Present the user with this question:\n17:         question: \"What would you like to retrieve context for?\"\n18:         options:\n19:           - label: \"Add feature\"\n20:             description: \"Context for implementing a new feature\"\n21:           - label: \"Fix bug\"\n22:             description: \"Context for debugging and fixing an issue\"\n23:           - label: \"Refactor\"\n24:             description: \"Context for code restructuring\"\n25:           - label: \"Security audit\"\n26:             description: \"Context for security review\"\n27:           - label: \"Understand\"\n28:             description: \"Context for learning existing code\"\n29:           - label: \"Find spec\"\n30:             description: \"Context for spec document retrieval\"\n31:           - label: \"Find decision\"\n32:             description: \"Context for decision rationale lookup\"\n33:           - label: \"Analysis tools\"\n34:             description: \"Epistemic baselines, memory causal graph, ablation, dashboards\"\n35:     → WAIT for user response\n36:     → If \"Analysis tools\" selected → Display ANALYSIS OVERVIEW (Section 8)\n37:     → Otherwise → Use their response to determine the intent and query\n38:     → If the AskUserQuestion response is a custom answer rather than one of the listed options,\n39:       treat that custom answer as the literal retrieval query and route it through RETRIEVAL MODE\n40:     → Only THEN continue with this workflow\n41: \n42: IF $ARGUMENTS starts with a KNOWN ANALYSIS SUBCOMMAND (Section 3):\n43:     → Route to ANALYSIS MODE (Section 5)\n44: \n45: IF $ARGUMENTS contains a query (any other text):\n46:     → Route to RETRIEVAL MODE (Section 4)\n47: ```\n48: \n49: **CRITICAL RULES:**\n50: - **DO NOT** infer query from conversation context\n51: - **DO NOT** assume the user's intent without explicit input\n52: - **DO NOT** proceed past this point without explicit query from user\n53: - The query and intent MUST come from `$ARGUMENTS` or user's answer above\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: # Memory Search Command\n58: \n59: Unified entry point for knowledge retrieval and analysis. Combines intent-aware context search (retrieval mode) with epistemic measurement, memory causal graph tools, and evaluation dashboards (analysis mode).\n60: \n61: ---\n62: \n63: ## 0. INSTRUCTIONS\n64: \n65: Start by classifying `$ARGUMENTS` into retrieval mode or analysis mode. Follow the routing contract below, prefer canonical packet sources in retrieval mode, and only invoke the analysis subcommands that match the user's explicit request.\n66: \n67: ---\n68: \n69: ```yaml\n70: role: Retrieval & Analysis Specialist\n71: purpose: Unified entry point combining intent-aware retrieval with epistemic measurement, memory causal graph, and evaluation tools\n72: action: Route through retrieval or analysis mode based on argument pattern\n73: \n74: operating_mode:\n75:   workflow: argument_routing\n76:   workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n77:   approvals: none_required\n78:   tracking: intent_classification\n79: ```\n80: \n81: This is a markdown-owned command contract. `/memory:*` commands intentionally do\n82: not have external YAML assets; validators and reviewers should check the inline\n83: operating-mode block and markdown workflow steps.\n84: \n85: ---\n86: \n87: ## 1. PURPOSE\n88: \n89: > **L1 Orchestration + L6 Analysis**: This command operates at both the L1 retrieval layer (orchestrating lower-level context-retrieval operations) and the L6 analysis layer (epistemic baselines, memory causal graph, evaluation). It provides a single entry point for all knowledge-related context-retrieval operations.\n90: \n91: Provide a unified entry point that:\n92: \n93: **Retrieval mode** (default):\n94: - Automatically detects task intent from the query\n95: - Applies task-specific weights for search optimization\n96: - Combines search + load in a single operation\n97: - Returns context with relevance explanation\n98: - Enforces L1 token budget constraints (target: ~2000 tokens per call)\n99: - Handles session deduplication for cross-session queries\n100: - Targets canonical packet sources first: `handover.md`, `_memory.continuity`, then the packet spec docs\n101: \n102: **Analysis mode** (subcommand-triggered):\n103: - Epistemic measurement: Capture knowledge baselines before and after tasks (`task_preflight`, `task_postflight`)\n104: - Memory causal graph: Trace decision lineage, create/remove causal links, view graph stats (`memory_drift_why`, `memory_causal_link`, `memory_causal_unlink`, `memory_causal_stats`)\n105: - Evaluation: Run channel ablation studies and view reporting dashboards (`eval_run_ablation`, `eval_reporting_dashboard`)\n106: - Learning history: View PREFLIGHT/POSTFLIGHT records and Learning Index trends (`memory_get_learning_history`)\n107: \n108: **Lifecycle note:** Retrieval does not delete expired records. Use `/memory:manage retention-sweep` for the `memory_retention_sweep` tool when governed records need retention cleanup (`tool-schemas.ts:330`).\n109: \n110: ### Hybrid Retrieval Runtime (Retrieval Mode)\n111: \n112: The unified context tool runs a hybrid retrieval pipeline with **graph-first routing** (026):\n113: \n114: - **Structural code graph channel has priority** in the fusion strategy: structural queries (callers, imports, dependencies) are routed to `code_graph_query` first, before semantic or lexical channels\n115: - Tri-channel retrieval (graph + vector/semantic + FTS5/BM25) with graph results given precedence in the fusion merge\n116: - Code Graph structural queries plus exact-text Grep integrates as the vector/semantic channel, providing natural-language code discovery alongside indexed-continuity vector search\n117: - When graph and semantic channels miss or return weak results, a 3-tier FTS fallback activates: FTS5 full-text → BM25 keyword scoring → Grep/Glob filesystem search. Post-026 FTS5 remediation improved BM25 tokenization and ranking accuracy\n118: - Intent-adaptive fusion and reranking (weights adapt when `SPECKIT_ADAPTIVE_FUSION` is enabled, including the internal continuity profile: semantic `0.52`, keyword `0.18`, recency `0.07`, graph `0.23`)\n119: - MMR diversity pruning to reduce redundant chunks, with continuity-oriented Stage 3 passes using a dedicated lambda of `0.65`\n120: - Stage 3 applies MMR diversity reranking plus MPAB chunk collapse; `applyLengthPenalty` remains on the API surface for compatibility but currently resolves to a neutral `1.0` multiplier for every document\n121: - Deep-mode query expansion for broader lexical coverage\n122: - Evidence-gap detection (026) to flag low-confidence retrievals with explicit gap warnings, enabling downstream reasoning to remain cautious and avoid acting on sparse evidence\n123: \n124: ### Canonical Retrieval Order\n125: \n126: - `/speckit:resume` is the recovery surface for session continuation.\n127: - Resume-oriented retrieval follows `handover.md -> _memory.continuity -> spec docs`.\n128: - Packet-oriented retrieval may additionally use indexed `document_type='graph_metadata'` rows for dependency, supersession, related-packet, and key-file signals.\n129: - `find_spec` and `find_decision` should resolve against canonical spec docs and anchors, not against standalone continuity artifacts.\n130: \n131: ---\n132: \n133: ## 2. CONTRACT\n134: \n135: **Inputs:** `$ARGUMENTS`: Query with optional intent override, OR analysis subcommand with parameters\n136: **Outputs:** Context with relevance scores and intent explanation, OR `STATUS=<OK|FAIL>` with subcommand-specific output\n137: \n138: ---\n139: \n140: ## 3. QUICK REFERENCE\n141: \n142: ### Retrieval Mode (default)\n143: \n144: | Command | Result |\n145: |---------|--------|\n146: | `/memory:search \"implement auth\"` | Auto-detect add_feature, apply weights |\n147: | `/memory:search \"auth bug\" --intent:fix_bug` | Explicit fix_bug intent |\n148: | `/memory:search \"how does auth work?\"` | Auto-detect understand intent |\n149: | `/memory:search \"optimize auth code\"` | Auto-detect refactor intent |\n150: | `/memory:search \"auth security review\"` | Auto-detect security_audit intent |\n151: | `/memory:search \"find the spec for auth\"` | Auto-detect find_spec intent |\n152: | `/memory:search \"why did we choose JWT\"` | Auto-detect find_decision intent |\n153: \n154: ### Analysis Mode (subcommand-triggered)\n155: \n156: | Command | Result |\n157: |---------|--------|\n158: | `/memory:search preflight specs/007-auth T1` | Capture epistemic baseline |\n159: | `/memory:search postflight specs/007-auth T1` | Calculate learning delta |\n160: | `/memory:search history specs/007-auth` | View learning history |\n161: | `/memory:search causal 42` | Trace causal chain for memory #42 |\n162: | `/memory:search link 42 43 caused` | Link memory #42 → #43 as caused |\n163: | `/memory:search unlink 5` | Remove causal edge #5 |\n164: | `/memory:search causal-stats` | View memory causal graph statistics |\n165: | `/memory:search ablation` | Run channel ablation study |\n166: | `/memory:search dashboard` | View reporting dashboard |\n167: \n168: ---\n169: \n170: ## 4. ARGUMENT ROUTING\n171: \n172: ```text\n173: $ARGUMENTS\n174:     │\n175:     ├─ Empty (no args)                        → INTERACTIVE PROMPT (see gate above)\n176:     │\n177:     ├─ ANALYSIS SUBCOMMAND DETECTED?\n178:     │   First token matches one of:\n179:     │   \"preflight\", \"postflight\", \"history\",\n180:     │   \"causal\", \"link\", \"unlink\",\n181:     │   \"causal-stats\", \"ablation\", \"dashboard\"\n182:     │   └─► YES → ANALYSIS MODE (Section 5)\n183:     │\n184:     └─ OTHERWISE (any other text)\n185:         └─► RETRIEVAL MODE (Section 4A)\n186:             Parse: <query> [--intent:<type>]\n187: ```\n188: \n189: **Routing logic:** If the first argument token exactly matches a known analysis subcommand keyword → route to analysis mode. Otherwise → treat entire input as a retrieval query (with optional `--intent:` flag).\n190: \n191: ---\n192: \n193: <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->\n194: <!-- SECTION 4A: RETRIEVAL MODE                                     -->\n195: <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->\n196: \n197: ## 4A. RETRIEVAL MODE\n198: \n199: ### Intent Types and Weights\n200: \n201: #### Intent Classification\n202: \n203: The system detects one of seven intent types:\n204: \n205: | Intent Type | Description | Weight Adjustments |\n206: |-------------|-------------|--------------------|\n207: | **add_feature** | Implementing new functionality | implementation: 1.5x, architecture: 1.3x, patterns: 1.2x |\n208: | **fix_bug** | Debugging and fixing issues | decisions: 1.4x, implementation: 1.3x, errors: 1.5x |\n209: | **refactor** | Code restructuring | architecture: 1.5x, patterns: 1.4x, decisions: 1.2x |\n210: | **security_audit** | Security review | decisions: 1.4x, implementation: 1.3x, security: 1.5x |\n211: | **understand** | Learning existing code | architecture: 1.4x, decisions: 1.3x, overview: 1.5x |\n212: | **find_spec** | Canonical spec document retrieval | spec-doc: 1.5x, architecture: 1.3x, overview: 1.2x |\n213: | **find_decision** | Decision rationale lookup from canonical docs | decisions: 1.5x, rationale: 1.4x, architecture: 1.2x |\n214: \n215: #### Detection Logic\n216: \n217: Intent is detected via keyword matching against the query. Keywords are phrase-based to avoid false positives:\n218: \n219: | Intent | Keywords |\n220: |--------|----------|\n221: | `add_feature` | 'implement', 'add feature', 'add new', 'add a', 'create new', 'build new' |\n222: | `fix_bug` | 'bug', 'error', 'fix', 'broken', 'issue', 'debug' |\n223: | `refactor` | 'refactor', 'restructure', 'improve', 'clean up', 'optimize' |\n224: | `security_audit` | 'security', 'vulnerability', 'auth', 'sanitize', 'xss', 'csrf' |\n225: | `understand` | 'how', 'why', 'what', 'explain', 'understand', 'learn' |\n226: | `find_spec` | 'spec', 'specification', 'spec folder', 'spec document', 'find spec' |\n227: | `find_decision` | 'decision', 'rationale', 'why did we', 'chose', 'decision record' |\n228: \n229: **Default fallback:** If no keywords match, defaults to `understand`.\n230: \n231: #### Anchor Mapping by Intent\n232: \n233: | Intent | Primary Anchors | Secondary Anchors | Why These? |\n234: |--------|----------------|-------------------|------------|\n235: | **add_feature** | implementation, architecture, patterns | decisions, code-examples | Need existing patterns + structure |\n236: | **fix_bug** | decisions, implementation, errors | debugging, troubleshooting | Need decision history + error context |\n237: | **refactor** | architecture, patterns, decisions | technical-specs, code-quality | Need structure understanding + rationale |\n238: | **security_audit** | decisions, implementation, security | validation, auth, sanitization | Need security decisions + validation patterns |\n239: | **understand** | architecture, decisions, summary | overview, context, background | Need high-level understanding first |\n240: | **find_spec** | spec-doc, architecture, overview | specification, structure | Need canonical spec document content + structure |\n\n(Showing lines 1-240 of 1036. Use offset=241 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: Unified continuity retrieval: spec-doc search, baselines, memory causal graph, ablations, dashboards.\nargument-hint: \"<query> [--intent:<type>] | preflight <specFolder> <taskId> | postflight <specFolder> <taskId> | history <specFolder> | causal <memoryId> | link <sourceId> <targetId> <relation> | unlink <edgeId> | causal-stats | ablation | dashboard\"\nallowed-tools: Read, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_quick_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_match_triggers, mcp__mk_spec_memory__task_preflight, mcp__mk_spec_memory__task_postflight, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_drift_why, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_link, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_unlink, mcp__mk_spec_memory__eval_run_ablation, mcp__mk_spec_memory__eval_reporting_dashboard, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_get_learning_history\n---\n\n> **Code Graph bridge:** Structural routing may call stable `code_graph_*` MCP tools; the code-graph implementation and docs are owned by `.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/`.\n\n# 🚨 MANDATORY FIRST ACTION - DO NOT SKIP\n\n**BEFORE READING ANYTHING ELSE IN THIS FILE, CHECK `$ARGUMENTS`:**\n\n```text\nIF $ARGUMENTS is empty, undefined, or contains only whitespace:\n    → STOP IMMEDIATELY\n    → Present the user with this question:\n        question: \"What would you like to retrieve context for?\"\n        options:\n          - label: \"Add feature\"\n            description: \"Context for implementing a new feature\"","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/search.md","text":"---\ndescription: Unified continuity retrieval: spec-doc search, baselines, memory causal graph, ablations, dashboards.\nargument-hint: \"<query> [--intent:<type>] | preflight <specFolder> <taskId> | postflight <specFolder> <taskId> | history <specFolder> | causal <memoryId> | link <sourceId> <targetId> <relation> | unlink <edgeId> | causal-stats | ablation | dashboard\"\nallowed-tools: Read, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_quick_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_match_triggers, mcp__mk_spec_memory__task_preflight, mcp__mk_spec_memory__task_postflight, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_drift_why, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_link, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_unlink, mcp__mk_spec_memory__eval_run_ablation, mcp__mk_spec_memory__eval_reporting_dashboard, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_get_learning_history\n---\n\n> **Code Graph bridge:** Structural routing may call stable `code_graph_*` MCP tools; the code-graph implementation and docs are owned by `.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/`.\n\n# 🚨 MANDATORY FIRST ACTION - DO NOT SKIP\n\n**BEFORE READING ANYTHING ELSE IN THIS FILE, CHECK `$ARGUMENTS`:**\n\n```text\nIF $ARGUMENTS is empty, undefined, or contains only whitespace:\n    → STOP IMMEDIATELY\n    → Present the user with this question:\n        question: \"What would you like to retrieve context for?\"\n        options:\n          - label: \"Add feature\"\n            description: \"Context for implementing a new feature\"\n          - label: \"Fix bug\"\n            description: \"Context for debugging and fixing an issue\"\n          - label: \"Refactor\"\n            description: \"Context for code restructuring\"\n          - label: \"Security audit\"\n            description: \"Context for security review\"\n          - label: \"Understand\"\n            description: \"Context for learning existing code\"\n          - label: \"Find spec\"\n            description: \"Context for spec document retrieval\"\n          - label: \"Find decision\"\n            description: \"Context for decision rationale lookup\"\n          - label: \"Analysis tools\"\n            description: \"Epistemic baselines, memory causal graph, ablation, dashboards\"\n    → WAIT for user response\n    → If \"Analysis tools\" selected → Display ANALYSIS OVERVIEW (Section 8)\n    → Otherwise → Use their response to determine the intent and query\n    → If the AskUserQuestion response is a custom answer rather than one of the listed options,\n      treat that custom answer as the literal retrieval query and route it through RETRIEVAL MODE\n    → Only THEN continue with this workflow\n\nIF $ARGUMENTS starts with a KNOWN ANALYSIS SUBCOMMAND (Section 3):\n    → Route to ANALYSIS MODE (Section 5)\n\nIF $ARGUMENTS contains a query (any other text):\n    → Route to RETRIEVAL MODE (Section 4)\n```\n\n**CRITICAL RULES:**\n- **DO NOT** infer query from conversation context\n- **DO NOT** assume the user's intent without explicit input\n- **DO NOT** proceed past this point without explicit query from user\n- The query and intent MUST come from `$ARGUMENTS` or user's answer above\n\n---\n\n# Memory Search Command\n\nUnified entry point for knowledge retrieval and analysis. Combines intent-aware context search (retrieval mode) with epistemic measurement, memory causal graph tools, and evaluation dashboards (analysis mode).\n\n---\n\n## 0. INSTRUCTIONS\n\nStart by classifying `$ARGUMENTS` into retrieval mode or analysis mode. Follow the routing contract below, prefer canonical packet sources in retrieval mode, and only invoke the analysis subcommands that match the user's explicit request.\n\n---\n\n```yaml\nrole: Retrieval & Analysis Specialist\npurpose: Unified entry point combining intent-aware retrieval with epistemic measurement, memory causal graph, and evaluation tools\naction: Route through retrieval or analysis mode based on argument pattern\n\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: argument_routing\n  workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n  approvals: none_required\n  tracking: intent_classification\n```\n\nThis is a markdown-owned command contract. `/memory:*` commands intentionally do\nnot have external YAML assets; validators and reviewers should check the inline\noperating-mode block and markdown workflow steps.\n\n---\n\n## 1. PURPOSE\n\n> **L1 Orchestration + L6 Analysis**: This command operates at both the L1 retrieval layer (orchestrating lower-level context-retrieval operations) and the L6 analysis layer (epistemic baselines, memory causal graph, evaluation). It provides a single entry point for all knowledge-related context-retrieval operations.\n\nProvide a unified entry point that:\n\n**Retrieval mode** (default):\n- Automatically detects task intent from the query\n- Applies task-specific weights for search optimization\n- Combines search + load in a single operation\n- Returns context with relevance explanation\n- Enforces L1 token budget constraints (target: ~2000 tokens per call)\n- Handles session deduplication for cross-session queries\n- Targets canonical packet sources first: `handover.md`, `_memory.continuity`, then the packet spec docs\n\n**Analysis mode** (subcommand-triggered):\n- Epistemic measurement: Capture knowledge baselines before and after tasks (`task_preflight`, `task_postflight`)\n- Memory causal graph: Trace decision lineage, create/remove causal links, view graph stats (`memory_drift_why`, `memory_causal_link`, `memory_causal_unlink`, `memory_causal_stats`)\n- Evaluation: Run channel ablation studies and view reporting dashboards (`eval_run_ablation`, `eval_reporting_dashboard`)\n- Learning history: View PREFLIGHT/POSTFLIGHT records and Learning Index trends (`memory_get_learning_history`)\n\n**Lifecycle note:** Retrieval does not delete expired records. Use `/memory:manage retention-sweep` for the `memory_retention_sweep` tool when governed records need retention cleanup (`tool-schemas.ts:330`).\n\n### Hybrid Retrieval Runtime (Retrieval Mode)\n\nThe unified context tool runs a hybrid retrieval pipeline with **graph-first routing** (026):\n\n- **Structural code graph channel has priority** in the fusion strategy: structural queries (callers, imports, dependencies) are routed to `code_graph_query` first, before semantic or lexical channels\n- Tri-channel retrieval (graph + vector/semantic + FTS5/BM25) with graph results given precedence in the fusion merge\n- Code Graph structural queries plus exact-text Grep integrates as the vector/semantic channel, providing natural-language code discovery alongside indexed-continuity vector search\n- When graph and semantic channels miss or return weak results, a 3-tier FTS fallback activates: FTS5 full-text → BM25 keyword scoring → Grep/Glob filesystem search. Post-026 FTS5 remediation improved BM25 tokenization and ranking accuracy\n- Intent-adaptive fusion and reranking (weights adapt when `SPECKIT_ADAPTIVE_FUSION` is enabled, including the internal continuity profile: semantic `0.52`, keyword `0.18`, recency `0.07`, graph `0.23`)\n- MMR diversity pruning to reduce redundant chunks, with continuity-oriented Stage 3 passes using a dedicated lambda of `0.65`\n- Stage 3 applies MMR diversity reranking plus MPAB chunk collapse; `applyLengthPenalty` remains on the API surface for compatibility but currently resolves to a neutral `1.0` multiplier for every document\n- Deep-mode query expansion for broader lexical coverage\n- Evidence-gap detection (026) to flag low-confidence retrievals with explicit gap warnings, enabling downstream reasoning to remain cautious and avoid acting on sparse evidence\n\n### Canonical Retrieval Order\n\n- `/speckit:resume` is the recovery surface for session continuation.\n- Resume-oriented retrieval follows `handover.md -> _memory.continuity -> spec docs`.\n- Packet-oriented retrieval may additionally use indexed `document_type='graph_metadata'` rows for dependency, supersession, related-packet, and key-file signals.\n- `find_spec` and `find_decision` should resolve against canonical spec docs and anchors, not against standalone continuity artifacts.\n\n---\n\n## 2. CONTRACT\n\n**Inputs:** `$ARGUMENTS`: Query with optional intent override, OR analysis subcommand with parameters\n**Outputs:** Context with relevance scores and intent explanation, OR `STATUS=<OK|FAIL>` with subcommand-specific output\n\n---\n\n## 3. QUICK REFERENCE\n\n### Retrieval Mode (default)\n\n| Command | Result |\n|---------|--------|\n| `/memory:search \"implement auth\"` | Auto-detect add_feature, apply weights |\n| `/memory:search \"auth bug\" --intent:fix_bug` | Explicit fix_bug intent |\n| `/memory:search \"how does auth work?\"` | Auto-detect understand intent |\n| `/memory:search \"optimize auth code\"` | Auto-detect refactor intent |\n| `/memory:search \"auth security review\"` | Auto-detect security_audit intent |\n| `/memory:search \"find the spec for auth\"` | Auto-detect find_spec intent |\n| `/memory:search \"why did we choose JWT\"` | Auto-detect find_decision intent |\n\n### Analysis Mode (subcommand-triggered)\n\n| Command | Result |\n|---------|--------|\n| `/memory:search preflight specs/007-auth T1` | Capture epistemic baseline |\n| `/memory:search postflight specs/007-auth T1` | Calculate learning delta |\n| `/memory:search history specs/007-auth` | View learning history |\n| `/memory:search causal 42` | Trace causal chain for memory #42 |\n| `/memory:search link 42 43 caused` | Link memory #42 → #43 as caused |\n| `/memory:search unlink 5` | Remove causal edge #5 |\n| `/memory:search causal-stats` | View memory causal graph statistics |\n| `/memory:search ablation` | Run channel ablation study |\n| `/memory:search dashboard` | View reporting dashboard |\n\n---\n\n## 4. ARGUMENT ROUTING\n\n```text\n$ARGUMENTS\n    │\n    ├─ Empty (no args)                        → INTERACTIVE PROMPT (see gate above)\n    │\n    ├─ ANALYSIS SUBCOMMAND DETECTED?\n    │   First token matches one of:\n    │   \"preflight\", \"postflight\", \"history\",\n    │   \"causal\", \"link\", \"unlink\",\n    │   \"causal-stats\", \"ablation\", \"dashboard\"\n    │   └─► YES → ANALYSIS MODE (Section 5)\n    │\n    └─ OTHERWISE (any other text)\n        └─► RETRIEVAL MODE (Section 4A)\n            Parse: <query> [--intent:<type>]\n```\n\n**Routing logic:** If the first argument token exactly matches a known analysis subcommand keyword → route to analysis mode. Otherwise → treat entire input as a retrieval query (with optional `--intent:` flag).\n\n---\n\n<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->\n<!-- SECTION 4A: RETRIEVAL MODE                                     -->\n<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->\n\n## 4A. RETRIEVAL MODE\n\n### Intent Types and Weights\n\n#### Intent Classification\n\nThe system detects one of seven intent types:\n\n| Intent Type | Description | Weight Adjustments |\n|-------------|-------------|--------------------|\n| **add_feature** | Implementing new functionality | implementation: 1.5x, architecture: 1.3x, patterns: 1.2x |\n| **fix_bug** | Debugging and fixing issues | decisions: 1.4x, implementation: 1.3x, errors: 1.5x |\n| **refactor** | Code restructuring | architecture: 1.5x, patterns: 1.4x, decisions: 1.2x |\n| **security_audit** | Security review | decisions: 1.4x, implementation: 1.3x, security: 1.5x |\n| **understand** | Learning existing code | architecture: 1.4x, decisions: 1.3x, overview: 1.5x |\n| **find_spec** | Canonical spec document retrieval | spec-doc: 1.5x, architecture: 1.3x, overview: 1.2x |\n| **find_decision** | Decision rationale lookup from canonical docs | decisions: 1.5x, rationale: 1.4x, architecture: 1.2x |\n\n#### Detection Logic\n\nIntent is detected via keyword matching against the query. Keywords are phrase-based to avoid false positives:\n\n| Intent | Keywords |\n|--------|----------|\n| `add_feature` | 'implement', 'add feature', 'add new', 'add a', 'create new', 'build new' |\n| `fix_bug` | 'bug', 'error', 'fix', 'broken', 'issue', 'debug' |\n| `refactor` | 'refactor', 'restructure', 'improve', 'clean up', 'optimize' |\n| `security_audit` | 'security', 'vulnerability', 'auth', 'sanitize', 'xss', 'csrf' |\n| `understand` | 'how', 'why', 'what', 'explain', 'understand', 'learn' |\n| `find_spec` | 'spec', 'specification', 'spec folder', 'spec document', 'find spec' |\n| `find_decision` | 'decision', 'rationale', 'why did we', 'chose', 'decision record' |\n\n**Default fallback:** If no keywords match, defaults to `understand`.\n\n#### Anchor Mapping by Intent\n\n| Intent | Primary Anchors | Secondary Anchors | Why These? |\n|--------|----------------|-------------------|------------|\n| **add_feature** | implementation, architecture, patterns | decisions, code-examples | Need existing patterns + structure |\n| **fix_bug** | decisions, implementation, errors | debugging, troubleshooting | Need decision history + error context |\n| **refactor** | architecture, patterns, decisions | technical-specs, code-quality | Need structure understanding + rationale |\n| **security_audit** | decisions, implementation, security | validation, auth, sanitization | Need security decisions + validation patterns |\n| **understand** | architecture, decisions, summary | overview, context, background | Need high-level understanding first |\n| **find_spec** | spec-doc, architecture, overview | specification, structure | Need canonical spec document content + structure |","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":240,"totalLines":1036,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/memory/search.md","time":{"start":1780738144587,"end":1780738144611}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0aedcfe7093f9903016a23e860845081918d914f30c224754f"}},"id":"prt_e9c43b93e001dIGOif2xJdpZjz","sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeuERCb2AlX2T5Je","messageID":"msg_e9c4396ec001Vvcu0wnewU9A9A"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780738144614,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeuERCb2AlX2T5Je","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_EVOyAMjL3xKWubkye6QhGALj","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/save.md","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/save.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: description: Save current conversation context into canonical spec-doc continuity surfaces with semantic indexing\n3: argument-hint: \"<spec-folder>\"\n4: allowed-tools: Read, Edit, Bash, Task, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_update\n5: ---\n6: \n7: # MANDATORY FIRST ACTION - SPEC FOLDER RESOLUTION\n8: \n9: **BEFORE READING ANYTHING ELSE IN THIS FILE, resolve `target_folder`:**\n10: \n11: ```text\n12: IF $ARGUMENTS contains a spec folder path:\n13:     → Validate folder exists\n14:     → Store as target_folder\n15:     → Continue reading this file\n16: \n17: IF $ARGUMENTS is empty, undefined, or contains only whitespace:\n18:     → Run AUTO-DETECTION (Tier 1 → Tier 2 → Tier 3):\n19: \n20:     TIER 1: Gate 3 Carry-Over (highest confidence - no confirmation needed)\n21:     - Check if a spec folder was established via Gate 3 earlier in this conversation\n22:     - If yes → use it directly as target_folder (per CLAUDE.md Memory Save Rule)\n23:     - Announce: \"Using active spec folder from this session: [folder]\"\n24: \n25:     TIER 2: Conversation Signal Analysis (high confidence - confirm)\n26:     - Scan files modified/read during this conversation\n27:     - Map file paths to spec folders:\n28:       * Files under specs/NNN-name/ or its children\n29:       * Files referenced in a spec folder's description.json\n30:       * Supporting docs (feature_catalog, manual_testing_playbook) linked via symlinks to a spec tree\n31:     - If ALL modified files map to a single spec folder (or one parent and its children):\n32:       → Propose: \"Based on this session's work, the target folder is [folder]. Saving there. [Y/n]\"\n33:       → If user confirms or does not object → store as target_folder\n34:     - If modified files span multiple unrelated spec folders → proceed to Tier 3\n35: \n36:     TIER 3: Guided Selection (fallback - must ask)\n37:     - List the spec folders touched in this conversation, ranked by file-edit count\n38:     - ASK: \"Multiple spec folders were touched. Which one should this context be saved to?\"\n39:     - If no spec folders detected at all → list recent/related spec folders and ask\n40:     - WAIT for user response → store as target_folder\n41: ```\n42: \n43: **CRITICAL RULES:**\n44: - Tier 1 (Gate 3 carry-over) proceeds without confirmation per CLAUDE.md Memory Save Rule\n45: - Tier 2 proposals MUST show the detected folder and ask for brief confirmation\n46: - Tier 3 MUST wait for explicit user response before proceeding\n47: - When ambiguous (files in multiple unrelated spec folders), ALWAYS ask - do not guess\n48: \n49: ---\n50: \n51: # /memory:save\n52: \n53: > Save current conversation context into the packet's canonical continuity surfaces with semantic indexing.\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ## 1. INSTRUCTIONS\n58: \n59: Resolve the target spec folder first, build structured JSON from the session evidence, then run the save workflow below. Prefer canonical packet docs and `_memory.continuity` over any legacy supporting artifacts.\n60: \n61: ---\n62: \n63: ## 2. PURPOSE\n64: \n65: Save the current conversation context, including session summary, key decisions, modified files, and trigger phrases, into the packet's canonical continuity surfaces so `/speckit:resume` and `/memory:search` read the same source of truth.\n66: \n67: **Key difference from `/memory:learn`:**\n68: - `/memory:save` = Session context routed into canonical packet docs and `_memory.continuity`\n69: - `/memory:learn` = Constitutional rules saved to `constitutional/` (always-surface tier)\n70: \n71: ### Canonical Routing Model\n72: \n73: - `handover.md` remains the top recovery document for active-session state and pending work.\n74: - `_memory.continuity` stores the compact continuity block used by `/speckit:resume`.\n75: - AI may directly edit `_memory.continuity` frontmatter blocks in `implementation-summary.md` when only those doc-local continuity hints need updating.\n76: - Canonical spec docs such as `implementation-summary.md` and `decision-record.md` receive the durable narrative content when the route applies.\n77: - `generate-context.js` remains the primary save mechanism when the workflow also needs DB indexing, embedding generation, `description.json` refresh, `graph-metadata.json` refresh, or anchor-managed compatibility output.\n78: - Canonical save requests now default to **planner-first** behavior: return the routed target, proposed edit summary, blockers, advisories, and follow-up actions before any mutation-first apply path is requested.\n79: - Explicit fallback remains available with `plannerMode: \"full-auto\"` or CLI `--full-auto` when an operator wants the legacy atomic writer behavior.\n80: - Standalone spec-doc markdown is not the primary operator-facing destination for this command.\n81: - Retention cleanup is outside save scope. When saved records expire under governance metadata, use `/memory:manage retention-sweep`, which routes to `memory_retention_sweep` (`tool-schemas.ts:330`).\n82: - `/memory:*` commands are markdown-owned contracts. They intentionally do not\n83:   have external YAML assets; validators and reviewers should check the inline\n84:   operating-mode blocks plus the markdown workflow steps.\n85: \n86: ### Handover Document Maintenance\n87: \n88: `/memory:save` is the canonical maintainer for `handover.md` through `handover_state` routing. When a packet does not already contain `handover.md`, create it from `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/handover.md`, then merge subsequent stop-state updates into `handover.md::session-log` while keeping `_memory.continuity` aligned for `/speckit:resume`.\n89: \n90: ### Routed Save Categories\n91: \n92: The canonical save router works with 8 categories:\n93: \n94: | Category | Typical target | Notes |\n95: | -------- | -------------- | ----- |\n96: | `narrative_progress` | `implementation-summary.md::what-built` | What changed in the system or packet |\n97: | `narrative_delivery` | `implementation-summary.md::how-delivered` | Sequencing, gating, rollout, and verification story |\n98: | `decision` | `decision-record.md::adr-NNN` on L3/L3+ or `implementation-summary.md::decisions` on L1/L2 | Choice, tradeoff, rationale |\n99: | `handover_state` | `handover.md::session-log` | Stop-state, blockers, recent action, next safe action. Use `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/handover.md` for initial creation when `handover.md` does not exist. |\n100: | `research_finding` | `research/research.md::findings` | Evidence, investigation result, cited upstream behavior |\n101: | `task_update` | `tasks.md::<phase-anchor>` | Checklist/task status mutation |\n102: | `metadata_only` | `_memory.continuity` in frontmatter | Machine-owned continuity payloads |\n103: | `drop` | `scratch/pending-route-<hash>.json` via refusal | Non-canonical transcript/tooling noise; never auto-merged |\n104: \n105: Routing tiers:\n106: \n107: - Tier 1 handles structured routes and strong heuristics.\n108: - Tier 2 uses prototype similarity against the frozen routing library.\n109: - Tier 3 is part of the live save handler by default. When `LLM_REFORMULATION_ENDPOINT` is reachable and returns a usable decision, it participates automatically; if that endpoint is unavailable or unusable, the save path falls back to Tier 2 with a confidence penalty when safe, otherwise it refuses the merge.\n110: \n111: Boundary rules:\n112: \n113: - Delivery cues are now stronger when the chunk mentions sequencing, gating, rollout, or verification.\n114: - Handover keeps state-first stop/resume notes even if they mention soft operational commands like `git diff`, `list spec-doc records`, or `force re-index`.\n115: - Hard transcript, telemetry, and wrapper scaffolding still route to `drop`.\n116: \n117: Override and context rules:\n118: \n119: - `routeAs` can force any of the 8 categories. The router preserves the natural decision for audit and warns if an override is accepted against a natural `drop`.\n120: - Router context passes `packet_kind` derived from spec metadata first (`type`, `title`, `description`), with parent-phase fallback only when the metadata is silent.\n121: \n122: ---\n123: \n124: ## 3. CONTRACT\n125: \n126: | Field   | Value                                                                                        |\n127: | ------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n128: | Input   | Spec folder path (from Gate 3 or `$ARGUMENTS`) + AI-composed JSON data                       |\n129: | Output  | Canonical spec-doc continuity updates + indexed continuity data. Also refreshes `graph-metadata.json` derived fields in the spec folder: `trigger_phrases` are deduplicated and capped at 12, `key_files` are sanitized before storage, `entities` are deduplicated with canonical-path preference, and `status` is checklist-aware and normalized to lowercase. |\n130: | Script  | `node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js`               |\n131: | Primary | **JSON mode:** `generate-context.js <json-data-path>` (e.g. a path under `$TMPDIR` or `/tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json`) or `--json '<data>'` |\n132: | Trigger | \"save context\", \"save memory\", `/memory:save`                                                |\n133: \n134: Planner behavior:\n135: - Default: `plan-only` for canonical save requests, with explicit follow-up actions such as `apply`, `refresh-graph`, and `reindex`\n136: - Fallback: `full-auto` restores the legacy mutation-first canonical writer\n137: - Deferred freshness actions: graph refresh and spec-doc reindex are surfaced as follow-ups instead of assumed default side effects\n138: \n139: ---\n140: \n141: ## 4. QUICK REFERENCE\n142: \n143: | Usage                                                  | Behavior                                                |\n144: | ------------------------------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------- |\n145: | `/memory:save`                                         | Auto-detect the active packet, confirm if needed, then route into canonical continuity targets |\n146: | `/memory:save 011-memory`                              | Save to a specific spec folder                          |\n147: | `/memory:save specs/006-semantic-memory/003-debugging` | Save to a nested spec folder                            |\n148: | `node .../generate-context.js --full-auto ...`         | Opt back into the legacy full-auto canonical apply path |\n149: \n150: ---\n151: \n152: ## 5. VALIDATION\n153: \n154: ### Pre-Flight Checks (Phase 0)\n155: \n156: Execute BEFORE folder validation to prevent data quality issues. All checks must pass.\n157: \n158: #### Check 1: Anchor Format Validation\n159: \n160: - Scan conversation for existing canonical spec-doc references\n161: - If any canonical spec documents (`decision-record.md`, `implementation-summary.md`, `handover.md`, `resource-map.md`) were read during the session, verify they contain BOTH opening AND closing ANCHOR tags\n162: - Pattern: `<!-- ANCHOR:id --> ... <!-- /ANCHOR:id -->`\n163: - If missing closing tags → WARN user before proceeding\n164: - Why: Broken anchors break section-specific retrieval (93% token waste)\n165: \n166: #### Check 2: Token Budget Validation\n167: \n168: - Estimate conversation size: `message_count * avg_tokens_per_message`\n169: - If estimated > 50,000 tokens:\n170:   - WARN: \"Large conversation detected\"\n171:   - OPTIONS: `[C]ontinue anyway | [S]plit save | [E]dit scope`\n172:   - WAIT for response\n173: \n174: #### Check 3: Spec Folder Existence\n175: \n176: - If `$ARGUMENTS` contains folder → validate exists, store as `pending_folder`\n177: - If `$ARGUMENTS` empty → defer to Phase 1\n178: \n179: #### Check 4: Stop Hook Awareness\n180: \n181: - Confirm whether recent hook-driven context preservation evidence exists for this session\n182: - Current limitation: no dedicated `pendingStopSave` field is shipped in the hook state, so `/memory:save` must not claim a guaranteed auto-save merge marker\n183: - If no recent hook-save evidence can be established: PASSED (proceed normally)\n184: \n185: **Phase 0 Output:**\n186: ```text\n187: anchor_validation: PASSED | WARNED\n188: token_budget:      PASSED | SPLIT_REQUESTED\n189: folder_existence:  PASSED\n190: stop_hook_check:   PASSED\n191: ```\n192: \n193: ### Spec Folder Validation (Phase 1)\n194: \n195: ```text\n196: IF target_folder already set (from $ARGUMENTS or Tier 1/2 auto-detection):\n197:   → Validate folder exists → Proceed to Content Alignment Check\n198: IF target_folder not yet set (Tier 3 pending):\n199:   → WAIT for user response → Validate → Proceed\n200: IF folder invalid:\n201:   → Show available folders → ASK user → WAIT\n202: ```\n203: \n204: **HARD STOP:** Do NOT proceed to save workflow until `target_folder` is set and validated.\n205: \n206: #### Content Alignment Check\n207: \n208: After Phase 1, validate the conversation topic matches the target folder:\n209: \n210: - Extract conversation topic (subject, files modified, problem being solved)\n211: - Compare to `target_folder` name\n212: - If clear match → PASS\n213: - If mismatch → WARN with alternatives:\n214:   - Show: \"Conversation topic: [topic]\" / \"Selected folder: [target_folder]\"\n215:   - Suggest top 3 alternative folders\n216:   - ASK: `[C]ontinue | [1][2][3] alternatives | [N]ew folder`\n217: \n218: ---\n219: \n220: ## 6. WORKFLOW\n\n(Showing lines 1-220 of 738. Use offset=221 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: Save current conversation context into canonical spec-doc continuity surfaces with semantic indexing\nargument-hint: \"<spec-folder>\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Edit, Bash, Task, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_update\n---\n\n# MANDATORY FIRST ACTION - SPEC FOLDER RESOLUTION\n\n**BEFORE READING ANYTHING ELSE IN THIS FILE, resolve `target_folder`:**\n\n```text\nIF $ARGUMENTS contains a spec folder path:\n    → Validate folder exists\n    → Store as target_folder\n    → Continue reading this file\n\nIF $ARGUMENTS is empty, undefined, or contains only whitespace:\n    → Run AUTO-DETECTION (Tier 1 → Tier 2 → Tier 3):\n\n    TIER 1: Gate 3 Carry-Over (highest confidence - no confirmation needed)","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/save.md","text":"---\ndescription: Save current conversation context into canonical spec-doc continuity surfaces with semantic indexing\nargument-hint: \"<spec-folder>\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Edit, Bash, Task, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_update\n---\n\n# MANDATORY FIRST ACTION - SPEC FOLDER RESOLUTION\n\n**BEFORE READING ANYTHING ELSE IN THIS FILE, resolve `target_folder`:**\n\n```text\nIF $ARGUMENTS contains a spec folder path:\n    → Validate folder exists\n    → Store as target_folder\n    → Continue reading this file\n\nIF $ARGUMENTS is empty, undefined, or contains only whitespace:\n    → Run AUTO-DETECTION (Tier 1 → Tier 2 → Tier 3):\n\n    TIER 1: Gate 3 Carry-Over (highest confidence - no confirmation needed)\n    - Check if a spec folder was established via Gate 3 earlier in this conversation\n    - If yes → use it directly as target_folder (per CLAUDE.md Memory Save Rule)\n    - Announce: \"Using active spec folder from this session: [folder]\"\n\n    TIER 2: Conversation Signal Analysis (high confidence - confirm)\n    - Scan files modified/read during this conversation\n    - Map file paths to spec folders:\n      * Files under specs/NNN-name/ or its children\n      * Files referenced in a spec folder's description.json\n      * Supporting docs (feature_catalog, manual_testing_playbook) linked via symlinks to a spec tree\n    - If ALL modified files map to a single spec folder (or one parent and its children):\n      → Propose: \"Based on this session's work, the target folder is [folder]. Saving there. [Y/n]\"\n      → If user confirms or does not object → store as target_folder\n    - If modified files span multiple unrelated spec folders → proceed to Tier 3\n\n    TIER 3: Guided Selection (fallback - must ask)\n    - List the spec folders touched in this conversation, ranked by file-edit count\n    - ASK: \"Multiple spec folders were touched. Which one should this context be saved to?\"\n    - If no spec folders detected at all → list recent/related spec folders and ask\n    - WAIT for user response → store as target_folder\n```\n\n**CRITICAL RULES:**\n- Tier 1 (Gate 3 carry-over) proceeds without confirmation per CLAUDE.md Memory Save Rule\n- Tier 2 proposals MUST show the detected folder and ask for brief confirmation\n- Tier 3 MUST wait for explicit user response before proceeding\n- When ambiguous (files in multiple unrelated spec folders), ALWAYS ask - do not guess\n\n---\n\n# /memory:save\n\n> Save current conversation context into the packet's canonical continuity surfaces with semantic indexing.\n\n---\n\n## 1. INSTRUCTIONS\n\nResolve the target spec folder first, build structured JSON from the session evidence, then run the save workflow below. Prefer canonical packet docs and `_memory.continuity` over any legacy supporting artifacts.\n\n---\n\n## 2. PURPOSE\n\nSave the current conversation context, including session summary, key decisions, modified files, and trigger phrases, into the packet's canonical continuity surfaces so `/speckit:resume` and `/memory:search` read the same source of truth.\n\n**Key difference from `/memory:learn`:**\n- `/memory:save` = Session context routed into canonical packet docs and `_memory.continuity`\n- `/memory:learn` = Constitutional rules saved to `constitutional/` (always-surface tier)\n\n### Canonical Routing Model\n\n- `handover.md` remains the top recovery document for active-session state and pending work.\n- `_memory.continuity` stores the compact continuity block used by `/speckit:resume`.\n- AI may directly edit `_memory.continuity` frontmatter blocks in `implementation-summary.md` when only those doc-local continuity hints need updating.\n- Canonical spec docs such as `implementation-summary.md` and `decision-record.md` receive the durable narrative content when the route applies.\n- `generate-context.js` remains the primary save mechanism when the workflow also needs DB indexing, embedding generation, `description.json` refresh, `graph-metadata.json` refresh, or anchor-managed compatibility output.\n- Canonical save requests now default to **planner-first** behavior: return the routed target, proposed edit summary, blockers, advisories, and follow-up actions before any mutation-first apply path is requested.\n- Explicit fallback remains available with `plannerMode: \"full-auto\"` or CLI `--full-auto` when an operator wants the legacy atomic writer behavior.\n- Standalone spec-doc markdown is not the primary operator-facing destination for this command.\n- Retention cleanup is outside save scope. When saved records expire under governance metadata, use `/memory:manage retention-sweep`, which routes to `memory_retention_sweep` (`tool-schemas.ts:330`).\n- `/memory:*` commands are markdown-owned contracts. They intentionally do not\n  have external YAML assets; validators and reviewers should check the inline\n  operating-mode blocks plus the markdown workflow steps.\n\n### Handover Document Maintenance\n\n`/memory:save` is the canonical maintainer for `handover.md` through `handover_state` routing. When a packet does not already contain `handover.md`, create it from `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/handover.md`, then merge subsequent stop-state updates into `handover.md::session-log` while keeping `_memory.continuity` aligned for `/speckit:resume`.\n\n### Routed Save Categories\n\nThe canonical save router works with 8 categories:\n\n| Category | Typical target | Notes |\n| -------- | -------------- | ----- |\n| `narrative_progress` | `implementation-summary.md::what-built` | What changed in the system or packet |\n| `narrative_delivery` | `implementation-summary.md::how-delivered` | Sequencing, gating, rollout, and verification story |\n| `decision` | `decision-record.md::adr-NNN` on L3/L3+ or `implementation-summary.md::decisions` on L1/L2 | Choice, tradeoff, rationale |\n| `handover_state` | `handover.md::session-log` | Stop-state, blockers, recent action, next safe action. Use `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/handover.md` for initial creation when `handover.md` does not exist. |\n| `research_finding` | `research/research.md::findings` | Evidence, investigation result, cited upstream behavior |\n| `task_update` | `tasks.md::<phase-anchor>` | Checklist/task status mutation |\n| `metadata_only` | `_memory.continuity` in frontmatter | Machine-owned continuity payloads |\n| `drop` | `scratch/pending-route-<hash>.json` via refusal | Non-canonical transcript/tooling noise; never auto-merged |\n\nRouting tiers:\n\n- Tier 1 handles structured routes and strong heuristics.\n- Tier 2 uses prototype similarity against the frozen routing library.\n- Tier 3 is part of the live save handler by default. When `LLM_REFORMULATION_ENDPOINT` is reachable and returns a usable decision, it participates automatically; if that endpoint is unavailable or unusable, the save path falls back to Tier 2 with a confidence penalty when safe, otherwise it refuses the merge.\n\nBoundary rules:\n\n- Delivery cues are now stronger when the chunk mentions sequencing, gating, rollout, or verification.\n- Handover keeps state-first stop/resume notes even if they mention soft operational commands like `git diff`, `list spec-doc records`, or `force re-index`.\n- Hard transcript, telemetry, and wrapper scaffolding still route to `drop`.\n\nOverride and context rules:\n\n- `routeAs` can force any of the 8 categories. The router preserves the natural decision for audit and warns if an override is accepted against a natural `drop`.\n- Router context passes `packet_kind` derived from spec metadata first (`type`, `title`, `description`), with parent-phase fallback only when the metadata is silent.\n\n---\n\n## 3. CONTRACT\n\n| Field   | Value                                                                                        |\n| ------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| Input   | Spec folder path (from Gate 3 or `$ARGUMENTS`) + AI-composed JSON data                       |\n| Output  | Canonical spec-doc continuity updates + indexed continuity data. Also refreshes `graph-metadata.json` derived fields in the spec folder: `trigger_phrases` are deduplicated and capped at 12, `key_files` are sanitized before storage, `entities` are deduplicated with canonical-path preference, and `status` is checklist-aware and normalized to lowercase. |\n| Script  | `node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js`               |\n| Primary | **JSON mode:** `generate-context.js <json-data-path>` (e.g. a path under `$TMPDIR` or `/tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json`) or `--json '<data>'` |\n| Trigger | \"save context\", \"save memory\", `/memory:save`                                                |\n\nPlanner behavior:\n- Default: `plan-only` for canonical save requests, with explicit follow-up actions such as `apply`, `refresh-graph`, and `reindex`\n- Fallback: `full-auto` restores the legacy mutation-first canonical writer\n- Deferred freshness actions: graph refresh and spec-doc reindex are surfaced as follow-ups instead of assumed default side effects\n\n---\n\n## 4. QUICK REFERENCE\n\n| Usage                                                  | Behavior                                                |\n| ------------------------------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------- |\n| `/memory:save`                                         | Auto-detect the active packet, confirm if needed, then route into canonical continuity targets |\n| `/memory:save 011-memory`                              | Save to a specific spec folder                          |\n| `/memory:save specs/006-semantic-memory/003-debugging` | Save to a nested spec folder                            |\n| `node .../generate-context.js --full-auto ...`         | Opt back into the legacy full-auto canonical apply path |\n\n---\n\n## 5. VALIDATION\n\n### Pre-Flight Checks (Phase 0)\n\nExecute BEFORE folder validation to prevent data quality issues. All checks must pass.\n\n#### Check 1: Anchor Format Validation\n\n- Scan conversation for existing canonical spec-doc references\n- If any canonical spec documents (`decision-record.md`, `implementation-summary.md`, `handover.md`, `resource-map.md`) were read during the session, verify they contain BOTH opening AND closing ANCHOR tags\n- Pattern: `<!-- ANCHOR:id --> ... <!-- /ANCHOR:id -->`\n- If missing closing tags → WARN user before proceeding\n- Why: Broken anchors break section-specific retrieval (93% token waste)\n\n#### Check 2: Token Budget Validation\n\n- Estimate conversation size: `message_count * avg_tokens_per_message`\n- If estimated > 50,000 tokens:\n  - WARN: \"Large conversation detected\"\n  - OPTIONS: `[C]ontinue anyway | [S]plit save | [E]dit scope`\n  - WAIT for response\n\n#### Check 3: Spec Folder Existence\n\n- If `$ARGUMENTS` contains folder → validate exists, store as `pending_folder`\n- If `$ARGUMENTS` empty → defer to Phase 1\n\n#### Check 4: Stop Hook Awareness\n\n- Confirm whether recent hook-driven context preservation evidence exists for this session\n- Current limitation: no dedicated `pendingStopSave` field is shipped in the hook state, so `/memory:save` must not claim a guaranteed auto-save merge marker\n- If no recent hook-save evidence can be established: PASSED (proceed normally)\n\n**Phase 0 Output:**\n```text\nanchor_validation: PASSED | WARNED\ntoken_budget:      PASSED | SPLIT_REQUESTED\nfolder_existence:  PASSED\nstop_hook_check:   PASSED\n```\n\n### Spec Folder Validation (Phase 1)\n\n```text\nIF target_folder already set (from $ARGUMENTS or Tier 1/2 auto-detection):\n  → Validate folder exists → Proceed to Content Alignment Check\nIF target_folder not yet set (Tier 3 pending):\n  → WAIT for user response → Validate → Proceed\nIF folder invalid:\n  → Show available folders → ASK user → WAIT\n```\n\n**HARD STOP:** Do NOT proceed to save workflow until `target_folder` is set and validated.\n\n#### Content Alignment Check\n\nAfter Phase 1, validate the conversation topic matches the target folder:\n\n- Extract conversation topic (subject, files modified, problem being solved)\n- Compare to `target_folder` name\n- If clear match → PASS\n- If mismatch → WARN with alternatives:\n  - Show: \"Conversation topic: [topic]\" / \"Selected folder: [target_folder]\"\n  - Suggest top 3 alternative folders\n  - ASK: `[C]ontinue | [1][2][3] alternatives | [N]ew folder`\n\n---\n\n## 6. WORKFLOW","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":220,"totalLines":738,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/memory/save.md","time":{"start":1780738144569,"end":1780738144612}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0aedcfe7093f9903016a23e860842c8191a4e28740e402459a"}},"id":"prt_e9c43b922001VoUESg2S6erBqc","sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeuERCb2AlX2T5Je","messageID":"msg_e9c4396ec001Vvcu0wnewU9A9A"}}
