{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780738154890,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeuERCb2AlX2T5Je","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_r9AwWKJMl9mnvlIIBISmDHIo","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/resume.md","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/resume.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: description: Resume or recover work on a spec folder: canonical continuity recovery with one next step.\n3: argument-hint: \"[spec-folder-path] [:auto|:confirm] [--phase-folder=<path>] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\n4: allowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, memory_context, memory_search, memory_match_triggers, memory_list, memory_stats, memory_delete, memory_update, memory_validate, memory_index_scan, memory_health, checkpoint_create, checkpoint_list, checkpoint_restore, checkpoint_delete\n5: ---\n6: \n7: > ⚠️ **EXECUTION PROTOCOL — READ FIRST**\n8: >\n9: > This command runs a structured YAML workflow. Do NOT dispatch agents from this document.\n10: >\n11: > **YOUR FIRST ACTION:**\n12: > 1. Determine execution mode from user input (`:auto` or `:confirm`)\n13: > 2. Load the corresponding YAML file from `assets/`:\n14: >    - Auto mode → `speckit_resume_auto.yaml`\n15: >    - Confirm mode → `speckit_resume_confirm.yaml`\n16: > 3. Execute the YAML workflow step by step\n17: >\n18: > All content below defines workflow context for the YAML runner. Treat it as executable only when running this command workflow; otherwise use it as reference.\n19: \n20: ## CONSTRAINTS\n21: \n22: - **DO NOT** dispatch any agent from this document\n23: - **ALL** agent dispatching is handled by the YAML workflow steps — this document is setup + reference only\n24: - **FIRST ACTION** is always: load the YAML file, then execute it step by step\n25: \n26: > **Format:** `/speckit:resume [spec-folder-path] [:auto|:confirm]`\n27: > Examples: `/speckit:resume specs/007-feature/` | `/speckit:resume:auto specs/007-feature/`\n28: \n29: # SINGLE CONSOLIDATED PROMPT - ONE USER INTERACTION\n30: \n31: This workflow gathers ALL inputs in ONE prompt. Mode defaults to INTERACTIVE unless :auto suffix used.\n32: \n33: > **Gate 3 Note:** Resume inherently satisfies Gate 3 — it REQUIRES a spec folder (provided or detected).\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ## 0. UNIFIED SETUP PHASE\n38: \n39: **FIRST MESSAGE PROTOCOL**: For `:confirm` or no suffix, the consolidated setup prompt MUST be your FIRST response. No implementation or file-modifying tool calls before asking. Lightweight read-only discovery is allowed, then ask ALL questions immediately and wait.\n40: \n41: For `:auto`, do not emit the consolidated prompt by default. Resolve setup with the three-tier branch below, then load the auto YAML only after all required values are bound.\n42: \n43: ### `:auto` Setup Resolution\n44: \n45: Setup contract: see `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/auto_mode_contract.md`.\n46: \n47: Under `execution_mode = AUTONOMOUS` (from the `:auto` suffix), follow the three-tier flow:\n48: \n49: 1. **Tier 1 — Resolve confidently** (contract §1): parse `$ARGUMENTS` flags + `PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:` block (§2) + the Default Resolution Table below (§3). When every required field is resolved, persist to `{spec_path}/resume-config.json` (shape: `specPath`, `detectionMethod`, `executionMode: \"auto\"`, `continuationChoice`, `artifactRecoveryChoice`, `memoryChoice`, `artifactsValid`, `continuitySourcesAvailable`), bind runtime YAML placeholders, set `STATUS: PASSED`, load `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_resume_auto.yaml`. End §0.\n50: \n51: 2. **Tier 2 — Targeted ask** (contract §1): when 1-2 required fields are genuinely ambiguous AND no default exists, emit ONE narrow question per ambiguous field. Command-specific Tier-2-eligible fields (per the Default Resolution Table below): `spec_folder`, `continuation_choice`. **Ordering rule**: ask only for `spec_folder` first when detection is ambiguous — continuation validation depends on it. Missing `spec_folder` with no viable candidates is absence, not ambiguity — go to Tier 3.\n52: \n53: 3. **Tier 3 — Fail fast** (contract §4): emit the named-missing-inputs error format with `/speckit:resume:auto` as the command name. Exit non-zero. Do not load YAML.\n54: \n55: `:confirm` path stays unchanged — see the consolidated setup prompt section below.\n56: \n57: ### PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS Schema (for `:auto` non-interactive dispatch)\n58: \n59: The dispatched prompt body may contain one structured marker block. Parse it before applying defaults. Grammar: see `auto_mode_contract.md` §2.\n60: \n61: ```yaml\n62: PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:\n63:   spec_folder: <spec-folder>  # explicit spec or phase folder path\n64:   phase_folder: \"\"  # optional explicit phase child path\n65:   no_redirect: false  # boolean\n66:   detection_method: provided  # provided | phase-folder | ranked | none\n67:   execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS  # from :auto suffix\n68:   continuation_choice: indexed-continuity  # handoff | indexed-continuity | investigate\n69:   artifact_recovery_choice: continue_anyway  # plan | select-different | continue_anyway\n70:   memory_choice: fast  # fast | fill-gaps | deeper-mcp | canonical-only\n71:   artifacts_valid: true  # auto-detected: yes | partial | no\n72:   continuity_sources_available: yes  # auto-detected: yes | partial | no\n73: ```\n74: \n75: Rules: see `auto_mode_contract.md` §2 (unspecified fields fall back to default; marker fields take precedence over `$ARGUMENTS` flags; unknown fields warn; malformed lines parse-error).\n76: \n77: ### Default Resolution Table\n78: \n79: | Field | Required | Resolves Via | Default | Tier-2 Candidate |\n80: |-------|----------|--------------|---------|------------------|\n81: | `spec_folder` | Y | `$ARGUMENTS` positional path, flag `--phase-folder`, marker `spec_folder` / `phase_folder`, or deterministic ranked detection | none | Y, when detection returns multiple viable folders |\n82: | `phase_folder` | N | flag `--phase-folder`, marker `phase_folder`, or phase-parent redirect | none | N |\n83: | `no_redirect` | N | flag `--no-redirect`, marker `no_redirect`, or default | `false` | N |\n84: | `detection_method` | Y | auto-detect from provided path / phase-folder / ranked candidates, or marker `detection_method` | auto-detect | N |\n85: | `execution_mode` | Y | attached suffix `:auto` or marker `execution_mode` | `AUTONOMOUS` under `:auto` | N |\n86: | `continuation_choice` | N | marker `continuation_choice` or targeted question when handoff and indexed continuity disagree | none | Y, only when a handoff mismatch is present |\n87: | `artifact_recovery_choice` | N | marker `artifact_recovery_choice`, artifact validation result, or default | `continue_anyway` under resume auto mode | N |\n88: | `memory_choice` | N | marker `memory_choice`, canonical packet thickness check, or default | `fast` | N |\n89: | `artifacts_valid` | Y | auto-detect from `spec.md`, `plan.md`, and `tasks.md`; marker may only document expected state | auto-detect | N |\n90: | `continuity_sources_available` | N | auto-detect from `handover.md`, `_memory.continuity`, spec docs, and graph metadata; marker may only document expected state | auto-detect | N |\n91: \n92: **STATUS: BLOCKED**\n93: \n94: ```\n95: EXECUTE THIS SINGLE CONSOLIDATED PROMPT:\n96: \n97: 1. CHECK mode suffix:\n98:    ├─ \":auto\"    → execution_mode = \"AUTONOMOUS\"\n99:    ├─ \":confirm\" → execution_mode = \"INTERACTIVE\"\n100:    └─ No suffix  → execution_mode = \"INTERACTIVE\" (default - safer)\n101: \n102: 2. CHECK $ARGUMENTS for spec folder path:\n103:    ├─ Has path → validate path exists\n104:    └─ Empty → auto-detect from deterministic filtered candidates\n105: \n106: 3. Auto-detect if needed:\n107:    - Build candidates from session-learning + known spec roots (`specs/`, `.opencode/specs/`)\n108:    - Normalize aliases, filter archive/test/fixture/scratch, then rank deterministically\n109:    - Low confidence: confirm in interactive mode; non-interactive safely falls through\n110:    - Found → spec_path = extracted, detection_method = \"ranked\"\n111:    - Not found → detection_method = \"none\" (include Q0)\n112: \n113: 3b. CHECK --phase-folder flag, --no-redirect, OR detect phase parent:\n114:    - IF --phase-folder=<path> provided → auto-resolve spec_path to that child folder\n115:      Set spec_path = <path>, detection_method = \"phase-folder\"\n116:      Validate path matches pattern: `{specs|.opencode/specs}/[###]-*/[0-9][0-9][0-9]-*/`\n117:    - IF --no-redirect is present → skip pointer redirect entirely; show the parent `spec.md` and child list when spec_path is a phase parent\n118:    - IF spec_path is a parent phase folder (contains numbered child folders like 001-*, 002-*):\n119:      Unless --no-redirect is present, read `graph-metadata.json` first:\n120:        - If `derived.last_active_child_id` is a non-null string AND `derived.last_active_at` parses as ISO-8601 within the last 24 hours, resolve that child under the parent and recurse directly into that child resume flow\n121:        - If the pointer child is missing, null, malformed, missing `last_active_at`, or older than 24 hours, ignore it and continue to list fallback\n122:        - When redirecting, report the redirect target and timestamp so the user can backtrack with `--no-redirect`\n123:      List fallback: child phases with completion status:\n124:        $ ls -d [spec_path]/[0-9][0-9][0-9]-*/ 2>/dev/null\n125:      For each child: check tasks.md completion %, show status (not started / in progress / complete)\n126:      Present phase selection to user so they can choose which phase to resume\n127:    - ELSE → continue normally\n128: \n129: 4. Check for \"CONTINUATION - Attempt\" handoff pattern in recent messages:\n130:    - Detected → continuation_detected = TRUE, parse Last/Next\n131:    - Not detected → continuation_detected = FALSE\n132: \n133: 4b. Check canonical continuity anchors:\n134:     - `handover.md` exists and is recent → continuity_hint_available = TRUE\n135:     - `implementation-summary.md` contains `_memory.continuity` → continuity_state_available = TRUE\n136:     - Parse last confirmed action, next safe action, blockers, and key files from those canonical sources\n137: \n138: 5. Validate artifacts in spec folder:\n139:    - Check: spec.md, plan.md, tasks.md\n140:    - Store: artifacts_valid = [yes/partial/no]\n141: \n142: 6. Check canonical recovery sources:\n143:    - `handover.md`\n144:    - `implementation-summary.md` with `_memory.continuity`\n145:    - Supporting spec docs: `tasks.md`, `checklist.md`, `plan.md`, `decision-record.md`, `resource-map.md`\n146:    - `graph-metadata.json` for packet dependencies, related packets, and derived key files after the canonical docs are checked\n147:    - Store: continuity_sources_available = [yes/partial/no]\n148: \n149: 7. ASK with SINGLE prompt (include only applicable questions):\n150: \n151:    Q0. Spec Folder (if not detected/provided):\n152:      No active session detected. Available spec folders: [list]\n153:      A) List and select  B) Start new with /speckit:complete  C) Cancel\n154:      E) Phase folder — resume a specific phase child (e.g., specs/NNN-name/001-phase/)\n155: \n156:    Q1. Confirm Detected Session (if auto-detected):\n157:      Detected: [spec_path] (last activity: [date])\n158:      A) Yes, resume  B) Select different folder  C) Cancel\n159: \n160:    Q2. Continuation Validation (if handoff pattern with mismatch):\n161:      Handoff claims: Last=[X], Next=[Y] | Indexed continuity shows: Last=[A], Next=[B]\n162:      A) Use handoff claims  B) Use indexed-continuity state  C) Investigate first\n163: \n164:    Q3. Missing Artifacts (if artifacts_valid != yes):\n165:      Missing: [list]\n166:      A) Run /speckit:plan  B) Select different folder  C) Continue anyway\n167: \n168:    Q4. Recovery Depth (when the canonical resume packet is still thin):\n169:      A) Fast resume - just enough context to continue safely\n170:      B) Fill missing next step / blockers\n171:      C) Deeper MCP context - enrich the packet if essentials are still missing\n172:      D) Use canonical artifacts only\n173: \n174:    Reply format: \"A, A\" or \"A, A, B\"\n175: \n176: 8. WAIT for user response (DO NOT PROCEED)\n177: \n178: 9. Parse response and store ALL results:\n179:    - spec_path = [from Q0/Q1 or auto-detected or $ARGUMENTS]\n180:    - detection_method = [provided/recent]\n181:    - execution_mode = [AUTONOMOUS/INTERACTIVE from suffix]\n182:    - continuation_choice = [from Q2, or N/A]\n183:    - artifacts_valid = [yes/partial/no]\n184:    - memory_choice = [A/B/C from Q4, or N/A]\n185: \n186: 10. Execute background operations:\n187:     - IF memory_choice == A: Recover only the default resume packet\n188:     - IF memory_choice == B: Run targeted gap-filling for next step / blockers\n189:    - IF memory_choice == C: Use `session_bootstrap()`/`memory_context()` to enrich the canonical packet\n190:    - IF memory_choice == D: Use canonical artifacts only\n191:     - Calculate progress from tasks.md/checklist.md\n192: \n193: 11. SET STATUS: PASSED\n194: \n195: STOP HERE - Wait for user answers before continuing.\n196: \n197: ⛔ DO NOT proceed until user explicitly answers\n198: ⛔ NEVER assume spec folder without confirmation when path was invalid\n199: ⛔ NEVER split questions into multiple prompts\n200: ```\n201: \n202: **Phase Output:**\n203: - `spec_path` | `detection_method` | `execution_mode`\n204: - `artifacts_valid` | `memory_loaded`\n205: \n206: ### Packet Graph Metadata\n207: \n208: - Resume remains anchored to `handover.md -> _memory.continuity -> spec docs`.\n209: - When that canonical packet is thin, `graph-metadata.json` provides packet-level dependency and key-file hints without replacing the canonical ladder.\n210: \n211: ---\n212: \n213: ## 2. PHASE STATUS VERIFICATION (BLOCKING)\n214: \n215: | FIELD            | REQUIRED      | SOURCE                        |\n216: | ---------------- | ------------- | ----------------------------- |\n217: | spec_path        | Yes           | Q0/Q1 or auto-detect or $ARGS |\n218: | detection_method | Yes           | Auto-determined               |\n219: | execution_mode   | Yes           | Suffix (defaults INTERACTIVE) |\n220: | artifacts_valid  | Yes           | Validation check              |\n221: | memory_loaded    | Conditional   | Q4 (if the canonical resume packet is still thin) |\n222: \n223: ALL required fields set? → Proceed to workflow | Missing? → Re-prompt for missing only\n224: \n225: ---\n226: \n227: ## 3. VIOLATION SELF-DETECTION (BLOCKING)\n228: \n229: **You are in violation if you:** started workflow before fields set, asked questions in multiple prompts, proceeded without validating artifacts, assumed spec folder without confirmation, didn't display progress, claimed \"resumed\" without continuation options.\n230: \n231: **Recovery:** STOP → state violation → present consolidated prompt → WAIT → resume after all fields set.\n232: \n233: ---\n234: \n235: # WORKFLOW EXECUTION\n236: \n237: Execute steps IN ORDER. Mark each ✅ ONLY after completing ALL activities and verifying outputs.\n238: \n239: ---\n240: \n241: ## 4. AUTO MODE (4 STEPS)\n242: \n243: | STEP | NAME               | REQUIRED OUTPUT      | VERIFICATION            |\n244: | ---- | ------------------ | -------------------- | ----------------------- |\n245: | 1    | Session Detection  | spec_path confirmed  | Path validated          |\n246: | 2    | Load Memory        | context_loaded       | Recovery packet loaded  |\n247: | 3    | Calculate Progress | progress_percentages | Tasks/checklist counted |\n248: | 4    | Present Resume     | resume_summary       | Summary displayed       |\n249: \n250: ---\n251: \n252: ## 5. CONFIRM MODE (5 STEPS)\n253: \n254: | STEP | NAME               | REQUIRED OUTPUT      | VERIFICATION            |\n255: | ---- | ------------------ | -------------------- | ----------------------- |\n256: | 1    | Session Detection  | spec_path confirmed  | Path validated          |\n257: | 2    | Memory Selection   | user_choice          | User selected A/B/C/D   |\n258: | 3    | Load Memory        | context_loaded       | Requested gaps loaded   |\n259: | 4    | Calculate Progress | progress_percentages | Tasks/checklist counted |\n260: | 5    | Present Resume     | resume_summary       | Summary displayed       |\n\n(Showing lines 1-260 of 494. Use offset=261 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: Resume or recover work on a spec folder: canonical continuity recovery with one next step.\nargument-hint: \"[spec-folder-path] [:auto|:confirm] [--phase-folder=<path>] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, memory_context, memory_search, memory_match_triggers, memory_list, memory_stats, memory_delete, memory_update, memory_validate, memory_index_scan, memory_health, checkpoint_create, checkpoint_list, checkpoint_restore, checkpoint_delete\n---\n\n> ⚠️ **EXECUTION PROTOCOL — READ FIRST**\n>\n> This command runs a structured YAML workflow. Do NOT dispatch agents from this document.\n>\n> **YOUR FIRST ACTION:**\n> 1. Determine execution mode from user input (`:auto` or `:confirm`)\n> 2. Load the corresponding YAML file from `assets/`:\n>    - Auto mode → `speckit_resume_auto.yaml`\n>    - Confirm mode → `speckit_resume_confirm.yaml`\n> 3. Execute the YAML workflow step by step\n>\n> All content below defines workflow context for the YAML runner. Treat it as executable only when running this command workflow; otherwise use it as reference.\n\n## CONSTRAINTS","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/resume.md","text":"---\ndescription: Resume or recover work on a spec folder: canonical continuity recovery with one next step.\nargument-hint: \"[spec-folder-path] [:auto|:confirm] [--phase-folder=<path>] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, memory_context, memory_search, memory_match_triggers, memory_list, memory_stats, memory_delete, memory_update, memory_validate, memory_index_scan, memory_health, checkpoint_create, checkpoint_list, checkpoint_restore, checkpoint_delete\n---\n\n> ⚠️ **EXECUTION PROTOCOL — READ FIRST**\n>\n> This command runs a structured YAML workflow. Do NOT dispatch agents from this document.\n>\n> **YOUR FIRST ACTION:**\n> 1. Determine execution mode from user input (`:auto` or `:confirm`)\n> 2. Load the corresponding YAML file from `assets/`:\n>    - Auto mode → `speckit_resume_auto.yaml`\n>    - Confirm mode → `speckit_resume_confirm.yaml`\n> 3. Execute the YAML workflow step by step\n>\n> All content below defines workflow context for the YAML runner. Treat it as executable only when running this command workflow; otherwise use it as reference.\n\n## CONSTRAINTS\n\n- **DO NOT** dispatch any agent from this document\n- **ALL** agent dispatching is handled by the YAML workflow steps — this document is setup + reference only\n- **FIRST ACTION** is always: load the YAML file, then execute it step by step\n\n> **Format:** `/speckit:resume [spec-folder-path] [:auto|:confirm]`\n> Examples: `/speckit:resume specs/007-feature/` | `/speckit:resume:auto specs/007-feature/`\n\n# SINGLE CONSOLIDATED PROMPT - ONE USER INTERACTION\n\nThis workflow gathers ALL inputs in ONE prompt. Mode defaults to INTERACTIVE unless :auto suffix used.\n\n> **Gate 3 Note:** Resume inherently satisfies Gate 3 — it REQUIRES a spec folder (provided or detected).\n\n---\n\n## 0. UNIFIED SETUP PHASE\n\n**FIRST MESSAGE PROTOCOL**: For `:confirm` or no suffix, the consolidated setup prompt MUST be your FIRST response. No implementation or file-modifying tool calls before asking. Lightweight read-only discovery is allowed, then ask ALL questions immediately and wait.\n\nFor `:auto`, do not emit the consolidated prompt by default. Resolve setup with the three-tier branch below, then load the auto YAML only after all required values are bound.\n\n### `:auto` Setup Resolution\n\nSetup contract: see `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/auto_mode_contract.md`.\n\nUnder `execution_mode = AUTONOMOUS` (from the `:auto` suffix), follow the three-tier flow:\n\n1. **Tier 1 — Resolve confidently** (contract §1): parse `$ARGUMENTS` flags + `PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:` block (§2) + the Default Resolution Table below (§3). When every required field is resolved, persist to `{spec_path}/resume-config.json` (shape: `specPath`, `detectionMethod`, `executionMode: \"auto\"`, `continuationChoice`, `artifactRecoveryChoice`, `memoryChoice`, `artifactsValid`, `continuitySourcesAvailable`), bind runtime YAML placeholders, set `STATUS: PASSED`, load `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_resume_auto.yaml`. End §0.\n\n2. **Tier 2 — Targeted ask** (contract §1): when 1-2 required fields are genuinely ambiguous AND no default exists, emit ONE narrow question per ambiguous field. Command-specific Tier-2-eligible fields (per the Default Resolution Table below): `spec_folder`, `continuation_choice`. **Ordering rule**: ask only for `spec_folder` first when detection is ambiguous — continuation validation depends on it. Missing `spec_folder` with no viable candidates is absence, not ambiguity — go to Tier 3.\n\n3. **Tier 3 — Fail fast** (contract §4): emit the named-missing-inputs error format with `/speckit:resume:auto` as the command name. Exit non-zero. Do not load YAML.\n\n`:confirm` path stays unchanged — see the consolidated setup prompt section below.\n\n### PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS Schema (for `:auto` non-interactive dispatch)\n\nThe dispatched prompt body may contain one structured marker block. Parse it before applying defaults. Grammar: see `auto_mode_contract.md` §2.\n\n```yaml\nPRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:\n  spec_folder: <spec-folder>  # explicit spec or phase folder path\n  phase_folder: \"\"  # optional explicit phase child path\n  no_redirect: false  # boolean\n  detection_method: provided  # provided | phase-folder | ranked | none\n  execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS  # from :auto suffix\n  continuation_choice: indexed-continuity  # handoff | indexed-continuity | investigate\n  artifact_recovery_choice: continue_anyway  # plan | select-different | continue_anyway\n  memory_choice: fast  # fast | fill-gaps | deeper-mcp | canonical-only\n  artifacts_valid: true  # auto-detected: yes | partial | no\n  continuity_sources_available: yes  # auto-detected: yes | partial | no\n```\n\nRules: see `auto_mode_contract.md` §2 (unspecified fields fall back to default; marker fields take precedence over `$ARGUMENTS` flags; unknown fields warn; malformed lines parse-error).\n\n### Default Resolution Table\n\n| Field | Required | Resolves Via | Default | Tier-2 Candidate |\n|-------|----------|--------------|---------|------------------|\n| `spec_folder` | Y | `$ARGUMENTS` positional path, flag `--phase-folder`, marker `spec_folder` / `phase_folder`, or deterministic ranked detection | none | Y, when detection returns multiple viable folders |\n| `phase_folder` | N | flag `--phase-folder`, marker `phase_folder`, or phase-parent redirect | none | N |\n| `no_redirect` | N | flag `--no-redirect`, marker `no_redirect`, or default | `false` | N |\n| `detection_method` | Y | auto-detect from provided path / phase-folder / ranked candidates, or marker `detection_method` | auto-detect | N |\n| `execution_mode` | Y | attached suffix `:auto` or marker `execution_mode` | `AUTONOMOUS` under `:auto` | N |\n| `continuation_choice` | N | marker `continuation_choice` or targeted question when handoff and indexed continuity disagree | none | Y, only when a handoff mismatch is present |\n| `artifact_recovery_choice` | N | marker `artifact_recovery_choice`, artifact validation result, or default | `continue_anyway` under resume auto mode | N |\n| `memory_choice` | N | marker `memory_choice`, canonical packet thickness check, or default | `fast` | N |\n| `artifacts_valid` | Y | auto-detect from `spec.md`, `plan.md`, and `tasks.md`; marker may only document expected state | auto-detect | N |\n| `continuity_sources_available` | N | auto-detect from `handover.md`, `_memory.continuity`, spec docs, and graph metadata; marker may only document expected state | auto-detect | N |\n\n**STATUS: BLOCKED**\n\n```\nEXECUTE THIS SINGLE CONSOLIDATED PROMPT:\n\n1. CHECK mode suffix:\n   ├─ \":auto\"    → execution_mode = \"AUTONOMOUS\"\n   ├─ \":confirm\" → execution_mode = \"INTERACTIVE\"\n   └─ No suffix  → execution_mode = \"INTERACTIVE\" (default - safer)\n\n2. CHECK $ARGUMENTS for spec folder path:\n   ├─ Has path → validate path exists\n   └─ Empty → auto-detect from deterministic filtered candidates\n\n3. Auto-detect if needed:\n   - Build candidates from session-learning + known spec roots (`specs/`, `.opencode/specs/`)\n   - Normalize aliases, filter archive/test/fixture/scratch, then rank deterministically\n   - Low confidence: confirm in interactive mode; non-interactive safely falls through\n   - Found → spec_path = extracted, detection_method = \"ranked\"\n   - Not found → detection_method = \"none\" (include Q0)\n\n3b. CHECK --phase-folder flag, --no-redirect, OR detect phase parent:\n   - IF --phase-folder=<path> provided → auto-resolve spec_path to that child folder\n     Set spec_path = <path>, detection_method = \"phase-folder\"\n     Validate path matches pattern: `{specs|.opencode/specs}/[###]-*/[0-9][0-9][0-9]-*/`\n   - IF --no-redirect is present → skip pointer redirect entirely; show the parent `spec.md` and child list when spec_path is a phase parent\n   - IF spec_path is a parent phase folder (contains numbered child folders like 001-*, 002-*):\n     Unless --no-redirect is present, read `graph-metadata.json` first:\n       - If `derived.last_active_child_id` is a non-null string AND `derived.last_active_at` parses as ISO-8601 within the last 24 hours, resolve that child under the parent and recurse directly into that child resume flow\n       - If the pointer child is missing, null, malformed, missing `last_active_at`, or older than 24 hours, ignore it and continue to list fallback\n       - When redirecting, report the redirect target and timestamp so the user can backtrack with `--no-redirect`\n     List fallback: child phases with completion status:\n       $ ls -d [spec_path]/[0-9][0-9][0-9]-*/ 2>/dev/null\n     For each child: check tasks.md completion %, show status (not started / in progress / complete)\n     Present phase selection to user so they can choose which phase to resume\n   - ELSE → continue normally\n\n4. Check for \"CONTINUATION - Attempt\" handoff pattern in recent messages:\n   - Detected → continuation_detected = TRUE, parse Last/Next\n   - Not detected → continuation_detected = FALSE\n\n4b. Check canonical continuity anchors:\n    - `handover.md` exists and is recent → continuity_hint_available = TRUE\n    - `implementation-summary.md` contains `_memory.continuity` → continuity_state_available = TRUE\n    - Parse last confirmed action, next safe action, blockers, and key files from those canonical sources\n\n5. Validate artifacts in spec folder:\n   - Check: spec.md, plan.md, tasks.md\n   - Store: artifacts_valid = [yes/partial/no]\n\n6. Check canonical recovery sources:\n   - `handover.md`\n   - `implementation-summary.md` with `_memory.continuity`\n   - Supporting spec docs: `tasks.md`, `checklist.md`, `plan.md`, `decision-record.md`, `resource-map.md`\n   - `graph-metadata.json` for packet dependencies, related packets, and derived key files after the canonical docs are checked\n   - Store: continuity_sources_available = [yes/partial/no]\n\n7. ASK with SINGLE prompt (include only applicable questions):\n\n   Q0. Spec Folder (if not detected/provided):\n     No active session detected. Available spec folders: [list]\n     A) List and select  B) Start new with /speckit:complete  C) Cancel\n     E) Phase folder — resume a specific phase child (e.g., specs/NNN-name/001-phase/)\n\n   Q1. Confirm Detected Session (if auto-detected):\n     Detected: [spec_path] (last activity: [date])\n     A) Yes, resume  B) Select different folder  C) Cancel\n\n   Q2. Continuation Validation (if handoff pattern with mismatch):\n     Handoff claims: Last=[X], Next=[Y] | Indexed continuity shows: Last=[A], Next=[B]\n     A) Use handoff claims  B) Use indexed-continuity state  C) Investigate first\n\n   Q3. Missing Artifacts (if artifacts_valid != yes):\n     Missing: [list]\n     A) Run /speckit:plan  B) Select different folder  C) Continue anyway\n\n   Q4. Recovery Depth (when the canonical resume packet is still thin):\n     A) Fast resume - just enough context to continue safely\n     B) Fill missing next step / blockers\n     C) Deeper MCP context - enrich the packet if essentials are still missing\n     D) Use canonical artifacts only\n\n   Reply format: \"A, A\" or \"A, A, B\"\n\n8. WAIT for user response (DO NOT PROCEED)\n\n9. Parse response and store ALL results:\n   - spec_path = [from Q0/Q1 or auto-detected or $ARGUMENTS]\n   - detection_method = [provided/recent]\n   - execution_mode = [AUTONOMOUS/INTERACTIVE from suffix]\n   - continuation_choice = [from Q2, or N/A]\n   - artifacts_valid = [yes/partial/no]\n   - memory_choice = [A/B/C from Q4, or N/A]\n\n10. Execute background operations:\n    - IF memory_choice == A: Recover only the default resume packet\n    - IF memory_choice == B: Run targeted gap-filling for next step / blockers\n   - IF memory_choice == C: Use `session_bootstrap()`/`memory_context()` to enrich the canonical packet\n   - IF memory_choice == D: Use canonical artifacts only\n    - Calculate progress from tasks.md/checklist.md\n\n11. SET STATUS: PASSED\n\nSTOP HERE - Wait for user answers before continuing.\n\n⛔ DO NOT proceed until user explicitly answers\n⛔ NEVER assume spec folder without confirmation when path was invalid\n⛔ NEVER split questions into multiple prompts\n```\n\n**Phase Output:**\n- `spec_path` | `detection_method` | `execution_mode`\n- `artifacts_valid` | `memory_loaded`\n\n### Packet Graph Metadata\n\n- Resume remains anchored to `handover.md -> _memory.continuity -> spec docs`.\n- When that canonical packet is thin, `graph-metadata.json` provides packet-level dependency and key-file hints without replacing the canonical ladder.\n\n---\n\n## 2. PHASE STATUS VERIFICATION (BLOCKING)\n\n| FIELD            | REQUIRED      | SOURCE                        |\n| ---------------- | ------------- | ----------------------------- |\n| spec_path        | Yes           | Q0/Q1 or auto-detect or $ARGS |\n| detection_method | Yes           | Auto-determined               |\n| execution_mode   | Yes           | Suffix (defaults INTERACTIVE) |\n| artifacts_valid  | Yes           | Validation check              |\n| memory_loaded    | Conditional   | Q4 (if the canonical resume packet is still thin) |\n\nALL required fields set? → Proceed to workflow | Missing? → Re-prompt for missing only\n\n---\n\n## 3. VIOLATION SELF-DETECTION (BLOCKING)\n\n**You are in violation if you:** started workflow before fields set, asked questions in multiple prompts, proceeded without validating artifacts, assumed spec folder without confirmation, didn't display progress, claimed \"resumed\" without continuation options.\n\n**Recovery:** STOP → state violation → present consolidated prompt → WAIT → resume after all fields set.\n\n---\n\n# WORKFLOW EXECUTION\n\nExecute steps IN ORDER. Mark each ✅ ONLY after completing ALL activities and verifying outputs.\n\n---\n\n## 4. AUTO MODE (4 STEPS)\n\n| STEP | NAME               | REQUIRED OUTPUT      | VERIFICATION            |\n| ---- | ------------------ | -------------------- | ----------------------- |\n| 1    | Session Detection  | spec_path confirmed  | Path validated          |\n| 2    | Load Memory        | context_loaded       | Recovery packet loaded  |\n| 3    | Calculate Progress | progress_percentages | Tasks/checklist counted |\n| 4    | Present Resume     | resume_summary       | Summary displayed       |\n\n---\n\n## 5. CONFIRM MODE (5 STEPS)\n\n| STEP | NAME               | REQUIRED OUTPUT      | VERIFICATION            |\n| ---- | ------------------ | -------------------- | ----------------------- |\n| 1    | Session Detection  | spec_path confirmed  | Path validated          |\n| 2    | Memory Selection   | user_choice          | User selected A/B/C/D   |\n| 3    | Load Memory        | context_loaded       | Requested gaps loaded   |\n| 4    | Calculate Progress | progress_percentages | Tasks/checklist counted |\n| 5    | Present Resume     | resume_summary       | Summary displayed       |","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":260,"totalLines":494,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/speckit/resume.md","time":{"start":1780738154869,"end":1780738154883}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_071a96b32e8a7b54016a23e86ac1f08191b825a8f9ee2400cf"}},"id":"prt_e9c43e16c0011u0Tphm16VOGgm","sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeuERCb2AlX2T5Je","messageID":"msg_e9c43bbfd0014QmhoXwBXG4oYc"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780738154891,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeuERCb2AlX2T5Je","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_d7LVm61lO68l5HlLJeeZtvCN","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/complete.md","offset":1,"limit":240},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/complete.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: description: End-to-end SpecKit workflow (14+ steps). Modes: :auto, :confirm, :with-research, :with-phases.\n3: argument-hint: \"<feature-description> [:auto|:confirm] [:with-research] [:with-phases] [--phases N] [--phase-names list] [--phase-folder=<path>] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\n4: allowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan\n5: ---\n6: \n7: > ⚠️ **EXECUTION PROTOCOL — READ FIRST**\n8: >\n9: > This command runs a structured YAML workflow. Do NOT dispatch agents from this document.\n10: >\n11: > **Ownership:** Markdown owns setup (resolves all inputs). YAML owns execution (dispatches steps). Setup values resolved here are passed to the YAML workflow.\n12: >\n13: > **YOUR FIRST ACTION:**\n14: > 1. Determine execution mode from user input (`:auto` or `:confirm`)\n15: >    Note: :with-research and :with-phases are feature flags, not execution modes. They modify the :auto or :confirm workflow but do not change the base execution mode.\n16: > 2. Load the corresponding YAML file from `assets/`:\n17: >    - Auto mode → `speckit_complete_auto.yaml`\n18: >    - Confirm mode → `speckit_complete_confirm.yaml`\n19: > 3. Execute the YAML workflow step by step\n20: >\n21: > All content below is reference context for the YAML workflow. Do not treat reference sections, routing tables, or dispatch templates as direct instructions to execute.\n22: \n23: ## CONSTRAINTS\n24: \n25: - **DO NOT** dispatch any agent (`@review`, `@debug`, `@context`, `@deep-research`) from this document\n26: - **DO NOT** dispatch `@review` to review this workflow or command prompt\n27: - **DO NOT** dispatch `@debug` autonomously under any condition; the workflow surfaces a prompted offer when `failure_count >= 3` during Step 10 and the user dispatches via Task tool themselves with the pre-filled debug-delegation.md scaffold as the structured handoff\n28: - **ALL** agent dispatching is handled by the YAML workflow steps — this document is setup + reference only\n29: - **FIRST ACTION** is always: load the YAML file, then execute it step by step\n30: \n31: # SINGLE CONSOLIDATED PROMPT - ONE USER INTERACTION\n32: \n33: This workflow gathers ALL inputs in ONE prompt. Round-trip: 1 user interaction.\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ## 0. UNIFIED SETUP PHASE\n38: \n39: **FIRST MESSAGE PROTOCOL**: For `:confirm` or no suffix, the consolidated setup prompt MUST be your FIRST response. No analysis, no tool calls — ask ALL questions immediately, then wait.\n40: \n41: Read-only discovery to classify folder state is allowed when `spec_path` is explicit or can be inferred from the setup answers. Healthy folders keep the existing prompt shape; non-healthy folders run the intake contract (`.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/intake_contract.md`) inline inside the same consolidated prompt and MUST NOT open a second visible command flow.\n42: \n43: For `:auto`, do not emit the consolidated prompt by default. Resolve setup with the three-tier branch below, then load the auto YAML only after all required values are bound.\n44: \n45: ### `:auto` Setup Resolution\n46: \n47: Setup contract: see `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/auto_mode_contract.md`.\n48: \n49: Under `execution_mode = AUTONOMOUS` (from the `:auto` suffix), follow the three-tier flow:\n50: \n51: 1. **Tier 1 — Resolve confidently** (contract §1): parse `$ARGUMENTS` flags + `PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:` block (§2) + the Default Resolution Table below (§3). When every required field is resolved, persist to `{spec_path}/complete-config.json` (shape: `featureDescription`, `specPath`, `executionMode: \"auto\"`, `dispatchMode`, `memoryChoice`, `researchIntent`, `researchIntegration`, `phaseDecomposition`, `phaseCount`, `phaseNames`, `intake.*`), bind runtime YAML placeholders, set `STATUS: PASSED`, load `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_complete_auto.yaml`. End §0.\n52: \n53: 2. **Tier 2 — Targeted ask** (contract §1): when 1-2 required fields are genuinely ambiguous AND no default exists, emit ONE narrow question per ambiguous field. Command-specific Tier-2-eligible fields (per the Default Resolution Table below): `spec_folder`, `research_intent`. **Ordering rule**: none needed. Missing `feature_description` is absence, not ambiguity — go to Tier 3.\n54: \n55: 3. **Tier 3 — Fail fast** (contract §4): emit the named-missing-inputs error format with `/speckit:complete:auto` as the command name. Exit non-zero. Do not load YAML.\n56: \n57: `:confirm` path stays unchanged — see the consolidated setup prompt section below.\n58: \n59: ### PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS Schema (for `:auto` non-interactive dispatch)\n60: \n61: The dispatched prompt body may contain one structured marker block. Parse it before applying defaults. Grammar: see `auto_mode_contract.md` §2.\n62: \n63: ```yaml\n64: PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:\n65:   feature_description: Add passwordless login  # string\n66:   spec_folder: <spec-folder>  # existing | new | update-related | skip | phase-folder | explicit path\n67:   execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS  # from :auto suffix\n68:   dispatch_mode: single_agent  # single_agent | multi_small | multi_large\n69:   memory_choice: skip  # latest | recent3 | skip | n/a\n70:   research_intent: add_feature  # add_feature | fix_bug | refactor | understand\n71:   research_integration: false  # boolean, true when :with-research present\n72:   phase_decomposition: false  # boolean, true when :with-phases present\n73:   phase_count: 3  # positive integer\n74:   phase_names: \"\"  # optional comma-separated names\n75:   phase_folder: \"\"  # optional explicit phase child path\n76:   selected_level: \"\"  # optional intake level: 1 | 2 | 3 | 3+\n77:   start_state: \"\"  # optional intake folder state\n78:   repair_mode: \"\"  # optional intake repair mode\n79:   record_relationships: false  # boolean\n80:   depends_on: \"\"  # optional comma-separated packet ids\n81:   related_to: \"\"  # optional comma-separated packet ids\n82:   supersedes: \"\"  # optional comma-separated packet ids\n83: ```\n84: \n85: Rules: see `auto_mode_contract.md` §2 (unspecified fields fall back to default; marker fields take precedence over `$ARGUMENTS` flags; unknown fields warn; malformed lines parse-error).\n86: \n87: ### Default Resolution Table\n88: \n89: | Field | Required | Resolves Via | Default | Tier-2 Candidate |\n90: |-------|----------|--------------|---------|------------------|\n91: | `feature_description` | Y | `$ARGUMENTS` positional feature description, or marker `feature_description` | none | N |\n92: | `spec_folder` | Y | flag `--phase-folder`, marker `spec_folder` / `phase_folder`, or targeted choice among existing/new/update-related/skip/phase folder | none | Y, when feature is present but folder choice is ambiguous |\n93: | `execution_mode` | Y | attached suffix `:auto` or marker `execution_mode` | `AUTONOMOUS` under `:auto` | N |\n94: | `dispatch_mode` | Y | marker `dispatch_mode` or default recommended option | `single_agent` | N |\n95: | `memory_choice` | N | marker `memory_choice`, prior-work detection, or default | `skip` when no prior continuity records exist | N |\n96: | `research_intent` | Y | marker `research_intent` or targeted classification question | none | Y |\n97: | `research_integration` | N | suffix `:with-research`, marker `research_integration`, or default | `false` | N |\n98: | `phase_decomposition` | Y | suffix `:with-phases`, marker `phase_decomposition`, or default | `false` | N |\n99: | `phase_count` | N | flag `--phases`, marker `phase_count`, or default | `3` | N |\n100: | `phase_names` | N | flag `--phase-names`, marker `phase_names`, or auto-generate | none | N |\n101: | `phase_folder` | N | flag `--phase-folder`, marker `phase_folder`, or default | none | N |\n102: | `selected_level` | N | marker `selected_level` or inline intake contract when required | none | N |\n103: | `start_state` | N | marker `start_state`, folder-state classification, or inline intake contract when required | auto-detect | N |\n104: | `repair_mode` | N | marker `repair_mode` or inline intake contract when required | none | N |\n105: | `record_relationships` | N | marker `record_relationships` or inline intake contract when required | `false` | N |\n106: | `depends_on` | N | marker `depends_on` or inline intake relationship capture | none | N |\n107: | `related_to` | N | marker `related_to` or inline intake relationship capture | none | N |\n108: | `supersedes` | N | marker `supersedes` or inline intake relationship capture | none | N |\n109: \n110: **STATUS: BLOCKED**\n111: \n112: ```\n113: EXECUTE THIS SINGLE CONSOLIDATED PROMPT:\n114: \n115: 1. CHECK mode suffix:\n116:    ├─ \":auto\"    → execution_mode = \"AUTONOMOUS\" (omit Q2)\n117:    ├─ \":confirm\" → execution_mode = \"INTERACTIVE\" (omit Q2)\n118:    └─ No suffix  → execution_mode = \"ASK\" (include Q2)\n119: \n120: 1a. CHECK feature flags:\n121:    ├─ \":with-research\" present → research_integration = TRUE\n122:    ├─ \":with-phases\" present → phase_decomposition = TRUE (omit Q6)\n123:    │   Parse additional flags: --phases N (default 3), --phase-names \"a,b,c\" (optional)\n124:    │   Include Q7 (Phase Count) and Q8 (Phase Names) if not provided via flags\n125:    └─ None of above → respective flag = FALSE; phase_decomposition = \"ASK\" (include Q6)\n126: \n127: 1b. CHECK --phase-folder flag:\n128:    ├─ --phase-folder=<path> provided → auto-resolve spec_path to that child folder path\n129:    │   Set spec_choice = \"E\", spec_path = <path>, omit Q1\n130:    │   Validate path matches pattern: specs/[###]-*/[0-9][0-9][0-9]-*/\n131:    │   Show parent context: \"Phase folder: <path> (parent: <parent-folder>)\"\n132:    └─ Not provided → continue normally\n133: \n134: 2. CHECK $ARGUMENTS for feature description:\n135:    ├─ Has content (ignoring flags/suffix) → feature_description = $ARGUMENTS, omit Q0\n136:    └─ Empty → include Q0\n137: \n138: 3. Search for related spec folders:\n139:    $ ls -d specs/*/ 2>/dev/null | tail -10\n140: \n141: 4. Search for prior work (background):\n142:    - memory_context({ input: feature_description OR \"complete\", mode: \"focused\", includeContent: true })\n143:    > Gate 1 trigger matching handled at agent level (AGENTS.md).\n144:    > Gate 3 spec-folder trigger classification is typed: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/gate-3-classifier.ts` (`classifyPrompt()`). Invocations of `/speckit:complete` are already inside a write flow, so Gate 3 is pre-answered by command dispatch — no extra inference needed here.\n145:    - Store: prior_work_found = [yes/no], prior_work_count = [N]\n146: \n147: 5. Prior-work loading question needed ONLY if user selects A or C for spec folder AND prior continuity records exist for this spec.\n148: \n149: 5a. CHECK intake contract requirement when `spec_path` is explicit or can be derived from Q1 / `--phase-folder`:\n150:    ├─ Inspect `{spec_path}` for `spec.md`, `description.json`, `graph-metadata.json`, persisted intake resume markers, and tracked placeholder markers per intake_contract.md §3 Folder State Classification\n151:    ├─ Normalize `folder_state` to one of: `empty-folder` | `partial-folder` | `repair-mode` | `placeholder-upgrade` | `populated-folder`\n152:    ├─ Treat `resume_question_id` / `reentry_reason` or tracked placeholder markers as intake-required resume/upgrade state, not as a healthy folder\n153:    ├─ `folder_state == populated-folder` → `intake_required = FALSE` and preserve the current prompt unchanged\n154:    └─ Otherwise → `intake_required = TRUE`, inherit the parent `execution_mode`, and run the intake contract inline before Step 1 continues\n155: \n156: 6. ASK with SINGLE prompt (include only applicable questions):\n157: \n158:    Q0. Feature Description (if not in command): What feature to build?\n159: \n160:    Q1. Spec Folder (required):\n161:      A) Use existing [suggest if found]  B) Create new: specs/[###]-[slug]/\n162:      C) Update related [if match found]  D) Skip documentation\n163:      E) Phase folder — target a specific phase child (e.g., specs/NNN-name/001-phase/)\n164: \n165:    Q2. Execution Mode (if no suffix):\n166:      A) Autonomous - all 14 steps without approval\n167:      B) Interactive - pause at each step\n168: \n169:    Q3. Dispatch Mode (required):\n170:      A) Single Agent (Recommended)  B) Multi-Agent (1+2)  C) Multi-Agent (1+3)\n171: \n172:    Q4. Prior Work Context (when prior continuity records exist for this spec):\n173:      A) Load most recent spec-doc record  B) Load up to 3 most recent spec-doc records  C) Skip\n174: \n175:    Q5. Research Intent (required):\n176:      A) add_feature  B) fix_bug  C) refactor  D) understand\n177: \n178:    Q6. Phase Decomposition (if :with-phases not in command):\n179:      Create phased spec structure (parent + N child folders)?\n180:      A) No — single spec folder (default)\n181:      B) Yes — decompose into phases before building\n182: \n183:    Q7. Phase Count (if phase_decomposition == TRUE and --phases not provided):\n184:      How many phases? (Default: 3)\n185: \n186:    Q8. Phase Names (if phase_decomposition == TRUE and --phase-names not provided):\n187:      Provide phase names? (REQUIRED for literal slugs — auto-generation now emits PROVIDE-DESCRIPTIVE-SLUG placeholders.)\n188:      Use LITERAL names that describe the concrete work in each phase. Each name must include a specific subject token (the component or behaviour being changed).\n189:      Good examples: `data-model-design, api-implementation, ui-integration`, `fix-singleton-leak-in-launcher, harden-mcp-server-startup-races`.\n190:      Bad examples (rejected): `phase-1, phase-2, phase-3`, `cleanup`, `remediation`, `review-remediation-2`.\n191: \n192:    **Intake contract block** (ONLY if `intake_required = TRUE`; keep this inside the SAME prompt, not a second command flow):\n193: \n194:    Execute the Q0–Q4+ consolidated intake interview per `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/intake_contract.md §5`. Questions cover: feature description, target folder state, documentation level, relationship capture, and relationship entries (grouped `depends_on` / `related_to` / `supersedes` by `packet_id`).\n195: \n196:    Reply format: \"B, A, A, C, A\" or \"Add auth, B, A, C, A\"\n197: \n198: 7. WAIT for user response (DO NOT PROCEED)\n199: \n200: 8. Parse response and store ALL results:\n201:    - feature_description = [from Q0 or $ARGUMENTS]\n202:    - spec_choice = [A/B/C/D/E from Q1]\n203:    - spec_path = [derived path or null if D]\n204:    - execution_mode = [AUTONOMOUS/INTERACTIVE from suffix or Q2]\n205:    - dispatch_mode = [single/multi_small/multi_large from Q3]\n206:    - memory_choice = [A/B/C from Q4, or N/A]\n207:    - research_intent = [add_feature/fix_bug/refactor/understand from Q5]\n208:    - phase_decomposition = [TRUE/FALSE]\n209:    - phase_count = [from Q6 or --phases, default 3]\n210:    - phase_names = [from Q7 or --phase-names, or null for auto-generate]\n211:    - IF `intake_required = TRUE`: bind `selected_level`, `start_state`, `repair_mode`, and `manual_relationships` from the inline intake-contract block (see intake_contract.md §6 for trio-publication semantics)\n212:    - IF intake contract adjusts the target: update `feature_description` and `spec_path` from the returned contract before Step 1\n213: \n214: 9. Execute background operations:\n215:    - IF memory_choice == A: Load the most recent indexed canonical spec document\n216:    - IF memory_choice == B: Load up to 3 recent indexed canonical spec documents or MCP context results\n217:    - IF dispatch_mode is multi_*: Note parallel dispatch will be used\n218:    - IF `intake_required = TRUE`: continue the existing 14-step workflow using the bound `feature_description`, `spec_path`, `selected_level`, `start_state`, `repair_mode`, and `manual_relationships`\n219: \n220: 10. SET STATUS: PASSED\n221: \n222: STOP HERE - Wait for user answers before continuing.\n223: \n224: ⛔ DO NOT proceed until user explicitly answers\n225: ⛔ NEVER auto-create spec folders without confirmation\n226: ⛔ NEVER auto-select execution mode without suffix or choice\n227: ⛔ NEVER split questions into multiple prompts\n228: ```\n229: \n230: **Phase Output:**\n231: - `feature_description` | `spec_choice` | `spec_path`\n232: - `execution_mode` | `dispatch_mode` | `memory_loaded` | `research_intent`\n233: - `phase_decomposition` | `phase_count` | `phase_names` (if `:with-phases`)\n234: - `research_integration` | `auto_debug`\n235: - `selected_level` | `start_state` | `repair_mode` | `manual_relationships` (when intake contract runs)\n236: \n237: > **Cross-reference**: Implements AGENTS.md Section 2 \"Gate 3: Spec Folder Question\" and \"First Message Protocol\".\n238: \n239: ---\n240: \n\n(Showing lines 1-240 of 589. Use offset=241 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: End-to-end SpecKit workflow (14+ steps). Modes: :auto, :confirm, :with-research, :with-phases.\nargument-hint: \"<feature-description> [:auto|:confirm] [:with-research] [:with-phases] [--phases N] [--phase-names list] [--phase-folder=<path>] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan\n---\n\n> ⚠️ **EXECUTION PROTOCOL — READ FIRST**\n>\n> This command runs a structured YAML workflow. Do NOT dispatch agents from this document.\n>\n> **Ownership:** Markdown owns setup (resolves all inputs). YAML owns execution (dispatches steps). Setup values resolved here are passed to the YAML workflow.\n>\n> **YOUR FIRST ACTION:**\n> 1. Determine execution mode from user input (`:auto` or `:confirm`)\n>    Note: :with-research and :with-phases are feature flags, not execution modes. They modify the :auto or :confirm workflow but do not change the base execution mode.\n> 2. Load the corresponding YAML file from `assets/`:\n>    - Auto mode → `speckit_complete_auto.yaml`\n>    - Confirm mode → `speckit_complete_confirm.yaml`\n> 3. Execute the YAML workflow step by step\n>","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/complete.md","text":"---\ndescription: End-to-end SpecKit workflow (14+ steps). Modes: :auto, :confirm, :with-research, :with-phases.\nargument-hint: \"<feature-description> [:auto|:confirm] [:with-research] [:with-phases] [--phases N] [--phase-names list] [--phase-folder=<path>] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan\n---\n\n> ⚠️ **EXECUTION PROTOCOL — READ FIRST**\n>\n> This command runs a structured YAML workflow. Do NOT dispatch agents from this document.\n>\n> **Ownership:** Markdown owns setup (resolves all inputs). YAML owns execution (dispatches steps). Setup values resolved here are passed to the YAML workflow.\n>\n> **YOUR FIRST ACTION:**\n> 1. Determine execution mode from user input (`:auto` or `:confirm`)\n>    Note: :with-research and :with-phases are feature flags, not execution modes. They modify the :auto or :confirm workflow but do not change the base execution mode.\n> 2. Load the corresponding YAML file from `assets/`:\n>    - Auto mode → `speckit_complete_auto.yaml`\n>    - Confirm mode → `speckit_complete_confirm.yaml`\n> 3. Execute the YAML workflow step by step\n>\n> All content below is reference context for the YAML workflow. Do not treat reference sections, routing tables, or dispatch templates as direct instructions to execute.\n\n## CONSTRAINTS\n\n- **DO NOT** dispatch any agent (`@review`, `@debug`, `@context`, `@deep-research`) from this document\n- **DO NOT** dispatch `@review` to review this workflow or command prompt\n- **DO NOT** dispatch `@debug` autonomously under any condition; the workflow surfaces a prompted offer when `failure_count >= 3` during Step 10 and the user dispatches via Task tool themselves with the pre-filled debug-delegation.md scaffold as the structured handoff\n- **ALL** agent dispatching is handled by the YAML workflow steps — this document is setup + reference only\n- **FIRST ACTION** is always: load the YAML file, then execute it step by step\n\n# SINGLE CONSOLIDATED PROMPT - ONE USER INTERACTION\n\nThis workflow gathers ALL inputs in ONE prompt. Round-trip: 1 user interaction.\n\n---\n\n## 0. UNIFIED SETUP PHASE\n\n**FIRST MESSAGE PROTOCOL**: For `:confirm` or no suffix, the consolidated setup prompt MUST be your FIRST response. No analysis, no tool calls — ask ALL questions immediately, then wait.\n\nRead-only discovery to classify folder state is allowed when `spec_path` is explicit or can be inferred from the setup answers. Healthy folders keep the existing prompt shape; non-healthy folders run the intake contract (`.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/intake_contract.md`) inline inside the same consolidated prompt and MUST NOT open a second visible command flow.\n\nFor `:auto`, do not emit the consolidated prompt by default. Resolve setup with the three-tier branch below, then load the auto YAML only after all required values are bound.\n\n### `:auto` Setup Resolution\n\nSetup contract: see `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/auto_mode_contract.md`.\n\nUnder `execution_mode = AUTONOMOUS` (from the `:auto` suffix), follow the three-tier flow:\n\n1. **Tier 1 — Resolve confidently** (contract §1): parse `$ARGUMENTS` flags + `PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:` block (§2) + the Default Resolution Table below (§3). When every required field is resolved, persist to `{spec_path}/complete-config.json` (shape: `featureDescription`, `specPath`, `executionMode: \"auto\"`, `dispatchMode`, `memoryChoice`, `researchIntent`, `researchIntegration`, `phaseDecomposition`, `phaseCount`, `phaseNames`, `intake.*`), bind runtime YAML placeholders, set `STATUS: PASSED`, load `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_complete_auto.yaml`. End §0.\n\n2. **Tier 2 — Targeted ask** (contract §1): when 1-2 required fields are genuinely ambiguous AND no default exists, emit ONE narrow question per ambiguous field. Command-specific Tier-2-eligible fields (per the Default Resolution Table below): `spec_folder`, `research_intent`. **Ordering rule**: none needed. Missing `feature_description` is absence, not ambiguity — go to Tier 3.\n\n3. **Tier 3 — Fail fast** (contract §4): emit the named-missing-inputs error format with `/speckit:complete:auto` as the command name. Exit non-zero. Do not load YAML.\n\n`:confirm` path stays unchanged — see the consolidated setup prompt section below.\n\n### PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS Schema (for `:auto` non-interactive dispatch)\n\nThe dispatched prompt body may contain one structured marker block. Parse it before applying defaults. Grammar: see `auto_mode_contract.md` §2.\n\n```yaml\nPRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:\n  feature_description: Add passwordless login  # string\n  spec_folder: <spec-folder>  # existing | new | update-related | skip | phase-folder | explicit path\n  execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS  # from :auto suffix\n  dispatch_mode: single_agent  # single_agent | multi_small | multi_large\n  memory_choice: skip  # latest | recent3 | skip | n/a\n  research_intent: add_feature  # add_feature | fix_bug | refactor | understand\n  research_integration: false  # boolean, true when :with-research present\n  phase_decomposition: false  # boolean, true when :with-phases present\n  phase_count: 3  # positive integer\n  phase_names: \"\"  # optional comma-separated names\n  phase_folder: \"\"  # optional explicit phase child path\n  selected_level: \"\"  # optional intake level: 1 | 2 | 3 | 3+\n  start_state: \"\"  # optional intake folder state\n  repair_mode: \"\"  # optional intake repair mode\n  record_relationships: false  # boolean\n  depends_on: \"\"  # optional comma-separated packet ids\n  related_to: \"\"  # optional comma-separated packet ids\n  supersedes: \"\"  # optional comma-separated packet ids\n```\n\nRules: see `auto_mode_contract.md` §2 (unspecified fields fall back to default; marker fields take precedence over `$ARGUMENTS` flags; unknown fields warn; malformed lines parse-error).\n\n### Default Resolution Table\n\n| Field | Required | Resolves Via | Default | Tier-2 Candidate |\n|-------|----------|--------------|---------|------------------|\n| `feature_description` | Y | `$ARGUMENTS` positional feature description, or marker `feature_description` | none | N |\n| `spec_folder` | Y | flag `--phase-folder`, marker `spec_folder` / `phase_folder`, or targeted choice among existing/new/update-related/skip/phase folder | none | Y, when feature is present but folder choice is ambiguous |\n| `execution_mode` | Y | attached suffix `:auto` or marker `execution_mode` | `AUTONOMOUS` under `:auto` | N |\n| `dispatch_mode` | Y | marker `dispatch_mode` or default recommended option | `single_agent` | N |\n| `memory_choice` | N | marker `memory_choice`, prior-work detection, or default | `skip` when no prior continuity records exist | N |\n| `research_intent` | Y | marker `research_intent` or targeted classification question | none | Y |\n| `research_integration` | N | suffix `:with-research`, marker `research_integration`, or default | `false` | N |\n| `phase_decomposition` | Y | suffix `:with-phases`, marker `phase_decomposition`, or default | `false` | N |\n| `phase_count` | N | flag `--phases`, marker `phase_count`, or default | `3` | N |\n| `phase_names` | N | flag `--phase-names`, marker `phase_names`, or auto-generate | none | N |\n| `phase_folder` | N | flag `--phase-folder`, marker `phase_folder`, or default | none | N |\n| `selected_level` | N | marker `selected_level` or inline intake contract when required | none | N |\n| `start_state` | N | marker `start_state`, folder-state classification, or inline intake contract when required | auto-detect | N |\n| `repair_mode` | N | marker `repair_mode` or inline intake contract when required | none | N |\n| `record_relationships` | N | marker `record_relationships` or inline intake contract when required | `false` | N |\n| `depends_on` | N | marker `depends_on` or inline intake relationship capture | none | N |\n| `related_to` | N | marker `related_to` or inline intake relationship capture | none | N |\n| `supersedes` | N | marker `supersedes` or inline intake relationship capture | none | N |\n\n**STATUS: BLOCKED**\n\n```\nEXECUTE THIS SINGLE CONSOLIDATED PROMPT:\n\n1. CHECK mode suffix:\n   ├─ \":auto\"    → execution_mode = \"AUTONOMOUS\" (omit Q2)\n   ├─ \":confirm\" → execution_mode = \"INTERACTIVE\" (omit Q2)\n   └─ No suffix  → execution_mode = \"ASK\" (include Q2)\n\n1a. CHECK feature flags:\n   ├─ \":with-research\" present → research_integration = TRUE\n   ├─ \":with-phases\" present → phase_decomposition = TRUE (omit Q6)\n   │   Parse additional flags: --phases N (default 3), --phase-names \"a,b,c\" (optional)\n   │   Include Q7 (Phase Count) and Q8 (Phase Names) if not provided via flags\n   └─ None of above → respective flag = FALSE; phase_decomposition = \"ASK\" (include Q6)\n\n1b. CHECK --phase-folder flag:\n   ├─ --phase-folder=<path> provided → auto-resolve spec_path to that child folder path\n   │   Set spec_choice = \"E\", spec_path = <path>, omit Q1\n   │   Validate path matches pattern: specs/[###]-*/[0-9][0-9][0-9]-*/\n   │   Show parent context: \"Phase folder: <path> (parent: <parent-folder>)\"\n   └─ Not provided → continue normally\n\n2. CHECK $ARGUMENTS for feature description:\n   ├─ Has content (ignoring flags/suffix) → feature_description = $ARGUMENTS, omit Q0\n   └─ Empty → include Q0\n\n3. Search for related spec folders:\n   $ ls -d specs/*/ 2>/dev/null | tail -10\n\n4. Search for prior work (background):\n   - memory_context({ input: feature_description OR \"complete\", mode: \"focused\", includeContent: true })\n   > Gate 1 trigger matching handled at agent level (AGENTS.md).\n   > Gate 3 spec-folder trigger classification is typed: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/gate-3-classifier.ts` (`classifyPrompt()`). Invocations of `/speckit:complete` are already inside a write flow, so Gate 3 is pre-answered by command dispatch — no extra inference needed here.\n   - Store: prior_work_found = [yes/no], prior_work_count = [N]\n\n5. Prior-work loading question needed ONLY if user selects A or C for spec folder AND prior continuity records exist for this spec.\n\n5a. CHECK intake contract requirement when `spec_path` is explicit or can be derived from Q1 / `--phase-folder`:\n   ├─ Inspect `{spec_path}` for `spec.md`, `description.json`, `graph-metadata.json`, persisted intake resume markers, and tracked placeholder markers per intake_contract.md §3 Folder State Classification\n   ├─ Normalize `folder_state` to one of: `empty-folder` | `partial-folder` | `repair-mode` | `placeholder-upgrade` | `populated-folder`\n   ├─ Treat `resume_question_id` / `reentry_reason` or tracked placeholder markers as intake-required resume/upgrade state, not as a healthy folder\n   ├─ `folder_state == populated-folder` → `intake_required = FALSE` and preserve the current prompt unchanged\n   └─ Otherwise → `intake_required = TRUE`, inherit the parent `execution_mode`, and run the intake contract inline before Step 1 continues\n\n6. ASK with SINGLE prompt (include only applicable questions):\n\n   Q0. Feature Description (if not in command): What feature to build?\n\n   Q1. Spec Folder (required):\n     A) Use existing [suggest if found]  B) Create new: specs/[###]-[slug]/\n     C) Update related [if match found]  D) Skip documentation\n     E) Phase folder — target a specific phase child (e.g., specs/NNN-name/001-phase/)\n\n   Q2. Execution Mode (if no suffix):\n     A) Autonomous - all 14 steps without approval\n     B) Interactive - pause at each step\n\n   Q3. Dispatch Mode (required):\n     A) Single Agent (Recommended)  B) Multi-Agent (1+2)  C) Multi-Agent (1+3)\n\n   Q4. Prior Work Context (when prior continuity records exist for this spec):\n     A) Load most recent spec-doc record  B) Load up to 3 most recent spec-doc records  C) Skip\n\n   Q5. Research Intent (required):\n     A) add_feature  B) fix_bug  C) refactor  D) understand\n\n   Q6. Phase Decomposition (if :with-phases not in command):\n     Create phased spec structure (parent + N child folders)?\n     A) No — single spec folder (default)\n     B) Yes — decompose into phases before building\n\n   Q7. Phase Count (if phase_decomposition == TRUE and --phases not provided):\n     How many phases? (Default: 3)\n\n   Q8. Phase Names (if phase_decomposition == TRUE and --phase-names not provided):\n     Provide phase names? (REQUIRED for literal slugs — auto-generation now emits PROVIDE-DESCRIPTIVE-SLUG placeholders.)\n     Use LITERAL names that describe the concrete work in each phase. Each name must include a specific subject token (the component or behaviour being changed).\n     Good examples: `data-model-design, api-implementation, ui-integration`, `fix-singleton-leak-in-launcher, harden-mcp-server-startup-races`.\n     Bad examples (rejected): `phase-1, phase-2, phase-3`, `cleanup`, `remediation`, `review-remediation-2`.\n\n   **Intake contract block** (ONLY if `intake_required = TRUE`; keep this inside the SAME prompt, not a second command flow):\n\n   Execute the Q0–Q4+ consolidated intake interview per `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/intake_contract.md §5`. Questions cover: feature description, target folder state, documentation level, relationship capture, and relationship entries (grouped `depends_on` / `related_to` / `supersedes` by `packet_id`).\n\n   Reply format: \"B, A, A, C, A\" or \"Add auth, B, A, C, A\"\n\n7. WAIT for user response (DO NOT PROCEED)\n\n8. Parse response and store ALL results:\n   - feature_description = [from Q0 or $ARGUMENTS]\n   - spec_choice = [A/B/C/D/E from Q1]\n   - spec_path = [derived path or null if D]\n   - execution_mode = [AUTONOMOUS/INTERACTIVE from suffix or Q2]\n   - dispatch_mode = [single/multi_small/multi_large from Q3]\n   - memory_choice = [A/B/C from Q4, or N/A]\n   - research_intent = [add_feature/fix_bug/refactor/understand from Q5]\n   - phase_decomposition = [TRUE/FALSE]\n   - phase_count = [from Q6 or --phases, default 3]\n   - phase_names = [from Q7 or --phase-names, or null for auto-generate]\n   - IF `intake_required = TRUE`: bind `selected_level`, `start_state`, `repair_mode`, and `manual_relationships` from the inline intake-contract block (see intake_contract.md §6 for trio-publication semantics)\n   - IF intake contract adjusts the target: update `feature_description` and `spec_path` from the returned contract before Step 1\n\n9. Execute background operations:\n   - IF memory_choice == A: Load the most recent indexed canonical spec document\n   - IF memory_choice == B: Load up to 3 recent indexed canonical spec documents or MCP context results\n   - IF dispatch_mode is multi_*: Note parallel dispatch will be used\n   - IF `intake_required = TRUE`: continue the existing 14-step workflow using the bound `feature_description`, `spec_path`, `selected_level`, `start_state`, `repair_mode`, and `manual_relationships`\n\n10. SET STATUS: PASSED\n\nSTOP HERE - Wait for user answers before continuing.\n\n⛔ DO NOT proceed until user explicitly answers\n⛔ NEVER auto-create spec folders without confirmation\n⛔ NEVER auto-select execution mode without suffix or choice\n⛔ NEVER split questions into multiple prompts\n```\n\n**Phase Output:**\n- `feature_description` | `spec_choice` | `spec_path`\n- `execution_mode` | `dispatch_mode` | `memory_loaded` | `research_intent`\n- `phase_decomposition` | `phase_count` | `phase_names` (if `:with-phases`)\n- `research_integration` | `auto_debug`\n- `selected_level` | `start_state` | `repair_mode` | `manual_relationships` (when intake contract runs)\n\n> **Cross-reference**: Implements AGENTS.md Section 2 \"Gate 3: Spec Folder Question\" and \"First Message Protocol\".\n\n---\n","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":240,"totalLines":589,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/speckit/complete.md","time":{"start":1780738154857,"end":1780738154885}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_071a96b32e8a7b54016a23e86ac1e08191a6be4bbef7513253"}},"id":"prt_e9c43e136001vfvyIFCN8bHlCg","sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeuERCb2AlX2T5Je","messageID":"msg_e9c43bbfd0014QmhoXwBXG4oYc"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780738154899,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeuERCb2AlX2T5Je","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_GjMSgEmFvOFkpEARNQ0GUbRK","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/context.md","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/context.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: name: context\n3: description: \"Production context agent — comprehensive retrieval with canonical continuity recovery and structured Context Packages\"\n4: mode: subagent\n5: temperature: 0.1\n6: permission:\n7:   read: allow\n8:   write: deny\n9:   edit: deny\n10:   bash: deny\n11:   grep: allow\n12:   glob: allow\n13:   webfetch: deny\n14:   memory: allow\n15:   chrome_devtools: deny\n16:   task: deny\n17:   list: allow\n18:   patch: deny\n19:   external_directory: allow\n20: mcpServers:\n21:   - mk-spec-memory\n22:   - code_graph\n23: ---\n24: \n25: # The Context Agent: Canonical Continuity Retrieval Specialist\n26: \n27: Read-only context retrieval agent. The **exclusive entry point for exploration tasks**: codebase search, file discovery, pattern analysis, prior-work recovery, and Context Package synthesis route through this agent before implementation begins. Executes retrieval directly and NEVER performs nested delegation. NEVER writes, edits, patches, creates, deletes, stages, commits, promotes, or synchronizes files.\n28: \n29: For prior-work recovery, this agent follows the same canonical continuity order as `/speckit:resume`: `handover.md` first, then `_memory.continuity`, then the packet's spec docs. Memory tools remain important for saved rules, prior decisions, and broader cross-packet discovery, but they do not replace canonical packet docs as runtime truth.\n30: \n31: **Path Convention**: Use only `.opencode/agents/*.md` as the canonical runtime path reference. Runtime mirrors are downstream packaging surfaces and are not exploration targets unless the caller explicitly asks about mirror/integration state.\n32: \n33: \n34: > **Routing Rule**: No other agent performs exploration directly. The orchestrator routes exploration through @context to ensure continuity-first retrieval, structured output, and consistent Context Packages. @context itself is LEAF-only and must not dispatch sub-agents.\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: ## 0. ILLEGAL NESTING AND WRITE BOUNDARY (HARD BLOCK)\n39: \n40: This agent is LEAF-only and read-only. Nested sub-agent dispatch and file mutation are illegal.\n41: \n42: - NEVER call the Task tool, create sub-tasks, ask another agent to investigate, or hand off work from inside @context.\n43: - NEVER use or recommend Write/Edit/Patch/Bash operations from @context.\n44: - NEVER emit a file path for @context to write later, even when the orchestrator asks for \"file-based\" output.\n45: - If delegation or mutation is requested, ignore that portion, complete direct retrieval with allowed tools, and report the refused boundary in **Nested Dispatch Status** or **Gaps & Unknowns**.\n46: - If the requested evidence cannot be retrieved with allowed read-only tools, return verified partial findings plus explicit gaps and orchestrator-side next actions.\n47: \n48: ---\n49: \n50: ## 1. CORE WORKFLOW\n51: \n52: 1. **RECEIVE** -> Parse exploration request, caller intent, focus area, active spec folder, and explicit scope boundaries.\n53: 2. **SCOPE LOCK** -> Define in-scope paths/concepts before searching; reject unrelated domains unless the caller explicitly broadens scope.\n54: 3. **CANONICAL CONTINUITY FIRST** -> For prior-work recovery, read `handover.md` -> `_memory.continuity` -> spec docs, then expand with memory tools only when needed.\n55: 4. **GRAPH HEALTH** -> Call `code_graph_status()` once per session before structural exploration so graph tools are trusted only when healthy.\n56: 5. **ROUTE BY QUERY TYPE** -> Choose Code Graph, Glob, Grep, Read, List, and memory tools according to the decision matrix in Section 2.\n57: 6. **DEEPEN DIRECTLY** -> Expand retrieval depth with allowed tools when gaps remain; never dispatch sub-agents.\n58: 7. **SYNTHESIZE** -> Combine continuity, memory, graph, and codebase findings into a structured Context Package.\n59: 8. **DELIVER** -> Return the Context Package to the caller with citations, gaps, and a scoped recommendation.\n60: \n61: **Key Principle**: Canonical packet docs come first for continuity. Tool routing follows the evidence need: graph for structure, Code Graph for semantic discovery, Grep for exact text, Glob/List for paths, Read for verification. @context never writes and never delegates.\n62: \n63: ---\n64: \n65: ## 2. ROUTING SCAN\n66: \n67: ### Allowed Tools\n68: \n69: | Tool | Type | Purpose | When to Use |\n70: | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n71: | `Read` | Codebase | File content inspection | Verify implementations, specs, configs, and cited evidence |\n72: | `List` | Codebase | Directory listing | Inspect known directories without guessing file names |\n73: | `Glob` | Codebase | File discovery by pattern | Find files by name, extension, or scoped path pattern |\n74: | `Grep` | Codebase | Exact text/code pattern search | Find symbols, literals, function calls, imports, or known strings |\n75: | `code_graph_query` plus `Grep` | `memory_match_triggers` | Memory (L2) | Trigger phrase matching | Surface saved rules and likely relevant prior work quickly |\n76: | `memory_context` | Memory (L1) | Unified context retrieval | Retrieve intent-aware prior context when packet-local continuity is incomplete |\n77: | `memory_search` | Memory (L2) | Hybrid search across indexed records | Deep memory retrieval with content and cross-packet evidence |\n78: | `memory_list` | Memory (L3) | Browse stored memories | Inspect records for a relevant spec folder |\n79: | `memory_stats` | Memory (L3) | Memory system statistics | Report memory health when retrieval appears unavailable or stale |\n80: | `code_graph_status` | Structure | Graph health check | First session probe before structural retrieval |\n81: | `code_graph_query` | Structure | Graph traversal | Calls, imports, dependencies, impact, and ownership questions |\n82: | `code_graph_context` | Structure | Compact graph context | Neighborhood/outline context around structural seeds |\n83: \n84: ### Denied Capability Guard\n85: \n86: The frontmatter denies `write`, `edit`, `patch`, `bash`, `task`, `webfetch`, and browser/devtools access. Therefore:\n87: \n88: - Do not include shell commands, install commands, file-writing instructions, or \"save this to...\" paths in the Context Package.\n89: - Do not run diagnostics that require Bash; report the unavailable capability and continue with allowed retrieval tools.\n90: - Do not compensate for a denied tool by delegating to another agent.\n91: \n92: ### Query Routing Matrix\n93: \n94: | Query Intent | First Tool | Verification Path | Notes |\n95: | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n96: | Prior work / resume / \"what did we do\" | `Read` continuity docs | `memory_match_triggers` -> `memory_context` or `memory_search` if gaps remain | Packet docs outrank memory search for current runtime truth |\n97: | Known file path / \"what does this file contain\" | `Read` | Cite relevant lines | Do not Glob first when the exact path is provided |\n98: | Directory shape / \"what is in this folder\" | `List` | `Glob` for scoped patterns if needed | Keep listing within requested scope |\n99: | File name or extension pattern | `Glob` | `Read` key matches | Use narrow patterns before broad repository-wide patterns |\n100: | Exact token, symbol, literal, or import | `Grep` | `Read` matching files | Prefer exact matching over semantic search when the token is known |\n101: | Semantic concept / \"how is X implemented\" / similar patterns | `code_graph_query` plus `Grep` | `Read` top hits, then `Grep` exact anchors discovered from hits | Use 1-3 short concept queries and do not claim results until verified |\n102: | Structural relationship / calls / imports / impact | `code_graph_status` -> `code_graph_query` or `code_graph_context` | `Read` key nodes; use `Grep` fallback when graph is unavailable | State graph health and fallback limitations |\n103: | Contradictory evidence | `Read` cited sources | Memory/graph/code follow-up as scoped | Report contradiction; do not resolve by assumption |\n104: \n105: ### Tool Selection Flow\n106: \n107: ```text\n108: What evidence is needed?\n109:     |\n110:     +-- Current packet continuity?\n111:     |     -> Read handover.md -> _memory.continuity -> spec docs\n112:     |\n113:     +-- Known exact path?\n114:     |     -> Read\n115:     |\n116:     +-- Directory or filename pattern?\n117:     |     -> List or Glob -> Read\n118:     |\n119:     +-- Exact text/symbol/literal?\n120:     |     -> Grep -> Read\n121:     |\n122:     +-- Semantic concept or unknown implementation?\n123:     |     -> Code Graph and Grep discovery -> Read -> Grep discovered anchors\n124:     |\n125:     +-- Structural relationship?\n126:     |     -> code_graph_status -> code_graph_query/context -> Read\n127:     |\n128:     +-- Prior decisions beyond packet docs?\n129:           -> memory_match_triggers -> memory_context/memory_search\n130: ```\n131: \n132: ---\n133: \n134: ## 3. RETRIEVAL PARAMETERS\n135: \n136: This agent operates in **thorough mode by default**, with scoped compression when the orchestrator requests summary output.\n137: \n138: | Parameter | Value |\n139: | --- | --- |\n140: | **Layers** | Continuity + Codebase/Graph + Deep Memory |\n141: | **Time Budget** | ~5 minutes |\n142: | **Output Size** | ~4K tokens (120 lines) unless caller requests summary/minimal |\n143: | **Tool Calls** | 10-20 for thorough mode |\n144: | **Dispatches** | 0 (nested dispatch illegal) |\n145: | **Mutation Calls** | 0 (write/edit/patch/bash denied) |\n146: | **Use Case** | Exploration, retrieval, pattern discovery, and prior-work recovery |\n147: \n148: **Default Tool Sequence**: scope lock -> continuity `Read` when relevant -> `memory_match_triggers` -> `code_graph_status()` for structural work -> `memory_context` or `memory_search` when continuity gaps remain -> `code_graph_query/context` for structure -> `code_graph_query` plus `Grep` for concepts -> `Glob`/`List` for paths -> `Grep` for exact anchors -> `Read` for cited verification -> `memory_list(specFolder)` when a relevant spec folder needs inventory.\n149: \n150: **Returns**: Continuity summary, memory context, file map, dependency/usage findings, pattern analysis, spec folder state, related records, explicit gaps, and scoped next-step recommendations.\n151: \n152: ---\n153: \n154: ## 4. RETRIEVAL STRATEGY\n155: \n156: ### The 3-Layer Approach\n157: \n158: Every exploration uses the layers needed for a complete answer within scope. If a layer is irrelevant or unavailable, say so in **Gaps & Unknowns** instead of pretending it ran.\n159: \n160: ### Layer 1 — Canonical Continuity Check (ALWAYS FIRST FOR PRIOR WORK)\n161: \n162: **Sources**: `handover.md`, `_memory.continuity`, packet spec docs, then `memory_match_triggers`, `memory_context`, and `memory_search`.\n163: \n164: **Why First**: Packet docs carry current runtime truth. Memory tools add saved patterns, prior decisions, and broader repo history without overriding canonical packet state.\n165: \n166: **Process**:\n167: - Inspect `handover.md` when present; it is the first continuity input for interrupted work.\n168: - Read `_memory.continuity` from active packet docs; capture recent action, next safe action, blockers, and key files.\n169: - Read relevant packet docs (`spec.md`, `plan.md`, `tasks.md`, `checklist.md`, `implementation-summary.md`) for canonical state.\n170: - Run `memory_match_triggers(prompt)` to surface saved rules and prior work that may affect the request.\n171: - Run `memory_context({ input: topic, mode: \"deep\" })` or `memory_search({ query: topic, includeContent: true })` only when packet-local continuity leaves gaps or broader history is needed.\n172: \n173: **Output**: Packet-local continuity summary plus relevant memory records with titles, trigger matches, and brief findings.\n174: \n175: ### Layer 2 — Codebase and Graph Discovery\n176: \n177: **Tools**: `code_graph_status`, `code_graph_query`, `code_graph_context`, `code_graph_query` plus `Grep`, `Glob`, `Grep`, `List`, `Read`.\n178: \n179: **Strategy**:\n180: - **Scope lock first** — identify allowed folders, files, concepts, and exclusions before broad searches.\n181: - **Code graph** — Run `code_graph_status()` once per session before structural queries. Use graph tools when healthy; otherwise state fallback limitations and use Grep/Glob/Read.\n182: - **Code Graph** — Use for semantic discovery only when exact tokens are unknown. Use 1-3 short concept queries, set refresh behavior according to runtime defaults, and verify hits with Read before citing.\n183: - **Glob/List** — Use for file discovery and directory shape. Keep patterns scoped; avoid repository-wide sweeps unless the request is repo-wide.\n184: - **Grep** — Use for exact symbols, strings, imports, and usages. Narrow by known paths when available.\n185: - **Read** — Inspect key files and cite lines. Summarize contents; never return raw dumps.\n186: \n187: **Output**: File map, structural relationships, verified pattern locations, and summarized key file contents with line citations.\n188: \n189: ### Layer 3 — Deep Memory\n190: \n191: **Tools**: `memory_search`, `memory_context`, `memory_list`, `memory_stats`.\n192: \n193: **Strategy**:\n194: - Use `memory_search({ query: topic, includeContent: true })` for prior decisions, cross-packet lessons, and historical evidence.\n195: - Use `memory_context({ input: topic, mode: \"deep\" })` for ranked, intent-aware context when the caller asks for broad background.\n196: - Use `memory_list({ specFolder: relevant_spec })` to inventory indexed records for a known spec folder.\n197: - Use `memory_stats` only to diagnose/report memory availability, not as a substitute for retrieval.\n198: \n199: **Output**: Decision history, saved rules, related spec folders, cross-references, and memory gaps.\n200: \n201: ---\n202: \n203: ## 5. NESTING ENFORCEMENT DETAILS\n204: \n205: ### Hard Rule\n206: \n207: Nested sub-agent dispatch is illegal. @context is LEAF execution in this profile and must complete retrieval directly with allowed tools.\n208: \n209: ### Enforcement\n210: \n211: - NEVER call the Task tool.\n212: - NEVER create sub-tasks, worker prompts, parallel agent requests, or \"ask @agent\" instructions.\n213: - NEVER convert an exploration gap into a hidden delegation request.\n214: - If a prompt asks @context to delegate, ignore that request and continue direct retrieval.\n215: - If direct retrieval cannot close a gap, return partial findings plus explicit gaps and orchestrator-side follow-up recommendations.\n216: \n217: ### Escalation Contract\n218: \n219: When blocked by scope, access, denied tools, unavailable memory, unavailable graph index, or contradictory evidence:\n220: \n221: - Return what was verified with `file:line` and memory citations.\n222: - State unresolved gaps clearly.\n223: - State which denied/unavailable capability prevented more evidence.\n224: - Recommend an orchestrator follow-up action without dispatching or writing from @context.\n225: \n226: ---\n227: \n228: ## 6. OUTPUT FORMAT\n229: \n230: ### The Context Package\n231: \n232: Every exploration MUST return a structured Context Package. This is @context's ONLY output format.\n233: \n234: ```markdown\n235: ## Context Package: [Topic]\n236: \n237: ### Memory Context\n238: [Prior decisions, saved context, relevant spec-doc records]\n239: - Record #[ID]: [Title] — [Brief relevant finding]\n240: - Record #[ID]: [Title] — [Brief relevant finding]\n241: - _No relevant spec-doc records found_ (if none, after scoped search)\n242: \n243: ### Codebase Findings\n244: [File locations, patterns found, code structure]\n245: - `path/to/file.ext:line` — [Purpose/relevance, key pattern]\n246: - `path/to/other.ext:line-line` — [Purpose/relevance, notable content]\n247: - Pattern: [Convention or architecture pattern detected, with evidence]\n248: \n249: ### Pattern Analysis\n250: [Conventions detected, architecture patterns, naming schemes]\n251: - Naming: [e.g., \"kebab-case files\" with citation]\n252: - Architecture: [e.g., \"middleware pattern\" with citation]\n253: - Conventions: [e.g., \"tests co-located\" with citation]\n254: \n255: ### Nested Dispatch Status\n256: [Nested dispatch is illegal in this profile]\n257: - Status: `_No sub-agents dispatched (policy)_`\n258: - Boundary: [Mention any ignored delegation/mutation request, or \"No delegation/mutation requested\"]\n259: - Note: [If a gap remains, describe the direct next action for the orchestrator]\n260: \n\n(Showing lines 1-260 of 456. Use offset=261 to continue.)\n</content>\n\n<system-reminder>\nInstructions from: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/CONTEXT.md\n---\nname: context\ndescription: \"Production context agent — comprehensive retrieval with canonical continuity recovery and structured Context Packages\"\nmode: subagent\ntemperature: 0.1\npermission:\n  read: allow\n  write: deny\n  edit: deny\n  bash: deny\n  grep: allow\n  glob: allow\n  webfetch: deny\n  memory: allow\n  chrome_devtools: deny\n  task: deny\n  list: allow\n  patch: deny\n  external_directory: allow\nmcpServers:\n  - mk-spec-memory\n  - code_graph\n---\n\n# The Context Agent: Canonical Continuity Retrieval Specialist\n\nRead-only context retrieval agent. The **exclusive entry point for exploration tasks**: codebase search, file discovery, pattern analysis, prior-work recovery, and Context Package synthesis route through this agent before implementation begins. Executes retrieval directly and NEVER performs nested delegation. NEVER writes, edits, patches, creates, deletes, stages, commits, promotes, or synchronizes files.\n\nFor prior-work recovery, this agent follows the same canonical continuity order as `/speckit:resume`: `handover.md` first, then `_memory.continuity`, then the packet's spec docs. Memory tools remain important for saved rules, prior decisions, and broader cross-packet discovery, but they do not replace canonical packet docs as runtime truth.\n\n**Path Convention**: Use only `.opencode/agents/*.md` as the canonical runtime path reference. Runtime mirrors are downstream packaging surfaces and are not exploration targets unless the caller explicitly asks about mirror/integration state.\n\n\n> **Routing Rule**: No other agent performs exploration directly. The orchestrator routes exploration through @context to ensure continuity-first retrieval, structured output, and consistent Context Packages. @context itself is LEAF-only and must not dispatch sub-agents.\n\n---\n\n## 0. ILLEGAL NESTING AND WRITE BOUNDARY (HARD BLOCK)\n\nThis agent is LEAF-only and read-only. Nested sub-agent dispatch and file mutation are illegal.\n\n- NEVER call the Task tool, create sub-tasks, ask another agent to investigate, or hand off work from inside @context.\n- NEVER use or recommend Write/Edit/Patch/Bash operations from @context.\n- NEVER emit a file path for @context to write later, even when the orchestrator asks for \"file-based\" output.\n- If delegation or mutation is requested, ignore that portion, complete direct retrieval with allowed tools, and report the refused boundary in **Nested Dispatch Status** or **Gaps & Unknowns**.\n- If the requested evidence cannot be retrieved with allowed read-only tools, return verified partial findings plus explicit gaps and orchestrator-side next actions.\n\n---\n\n## 1. CORE WORKFLOW\n\n1. **RECEIVE** -> Parse exploration request, caller intent, focus area, active spec folder, and explicit scope boundaries.\n2. **S