{"type":"text","timestamp":1780738166126,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeuERCb2AlX2T5Je","part":{"id":"prt_e9c43f7e20017pcQ2wm3aOWvhJ","messageID":"msg_e9c43e3d0001MHa6m2jR868xZ9","sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeuERCb2AlX2T5Je","type":"text","text":"The shared mutation hook already centralizes post-write invalidation for trigger, tool, constitutional, graph, co-activation, and entity-density caches; that is the natural invisible trigger point for provenance, audit, feedback-event, and idempotency side effects.","time":{"start":1780738160610,"end":1780738166123},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_07a2c7b19d1ada51016a23e8708fd881918790fac122ac2e10","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780738166330,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeuERCb2AlX2T5Je","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_v14hKpAM8BOtJNqEpxtLdvxc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"memory_save|memory_update|memory_search|memory_context|constitutional|continuity|source_kind|feedback|audit","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents","include":"*.md"},"output":"Found 73 matches\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/ai-council.md:\n  Line 75:    2. Else, check the active continuity ladder (`handover.md` -> `_memory.continuity` -> `spec.md` frontmatter `packet_pointer`) for an active packet.\n\n  Line 82: 2. **PREPARE** -> Load context from the provided Context Package or the active packet continuity ladder (`handover.md` -> `_memory.continuity` -> spec docs), then gather required file context. Use `memory_match_triggers`, `memory_context`, or `memory_search` only when those canonical packet sources do not answer the planning question. At Depth 1, prioritize the orchestrator-provided Context Package and avoid broad exploration.\n\n  Line 126: | `memory_match_triggers` | Memory triggers | Supplemental context surfacing after packet continuity is checked |\n\n  Line 127: | `memory_context` | Unified memory retrieval | Deep historical context when `handover.md`, `_memory.continuity`, and spec docs are insufficient |\n\n  Line 128: | `memory_search` | Hybrid memory search | Finding older decisions and patterns after canonical packet sources are exhausted |\n\n  Line 710: Sophisticated convergence math is non-goal N1. Keep v1 simple and auditable.\n\n  Line 755: 4. Leave the rollback and supersede events in state history. v1 readers ignore unknown events; v1.2 readers use them for audit and completeness summaries.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/deep-review.md:\n  Line 70: The refusal MUST appear verbatim (grep-checkable) for stress tests and operator audit. Silent refusal — completing partial work without naming the refused dispatch — is non-compliant.\n\n  Line 103: Immediately after validating dispatch inputs, BEFORE any state read or workflow step, this agent MUST emit one canonical BINDING line per resolved setup value to stdout. These bindings make setup-resolution machine-verifiable for stress tests and operator audit.\n\n  Line 250: - `memory_search` / `memory_context`: broader history only after packet continuity is insufficient.\n\n  Line 356: - This leaf agent may read registry for continuity and deduplication.\n\n  Line 528: | Hold findings in memory | Loses continuity | Write everything to iteration-NNN.md |\n\n  Line 533: | Anonymous integration claim | Cannot be audited by reducer, caller, or operator | Name the exact command, workflow, skill, MCP/code tool, caller agent, or mirror |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/orchestrate.md:\n  Line 378: **Action:** The main agent writes spec-folder docs directly using `Level template contract`, runs `validate.sh --strict` after each doc write, and routes continuity via `/memory:save`.\n\n  Line 384: - `_memory.continuity` YAML block inside `implementation-summary.md` → may be edited directly by any implementing agent for lightweight session continuity updates\n\n  Line 387: **Logic:** Distributed governance keeps spec-doc quality anchored to template usage, strict validation, and `/memory:save` continuity routing without relying on a deprecated dedicated spec agent.\n\n  Line 470: | **Quality Score < 70**   | Scoring dimensions fail threshold     | Auto-retry with feedback         |\n\n  Line 477: STOP (do not synthesize rejected output) → provide specific feedback stating exactly what failed → retry with explicit requirements, expected format, and additional context → escalate to user after 2 rejections.\n\n  Line 496: **Auto-Retry:** Score < 70 → execute verification actions above → provide specific feedback → retry with revision guidance. If still < 70 after 2 retries → escalate to user.\n\n  Line 550: - Run `/memory:save` to refresh canonical continuity before ending the session\n\n  Line 618: | Session ending or user says \"stopping\" | `/memory:save`       | Preserve canonical continuity          |\n\n  Line 622: | Resuming prior work (known spec)       | `/speckit:resume`   | Recover via `handover.md` -> `_memory.continuity` -> spec docs |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/debug.md:\n  Line 136: **If dispatched with a Context Package** (from @context or orchestrator): Skip Layer 1 memory checks (memory_match_triggers, memory_context, memory_search). Use provided context instead.\n\n  Line 138: **If no Context Package or structured handoff is provided**: Rebuild the active packet context from `handover.md`, then `_memory.continuity`, then the relevant spec docs before widening to memory tools. Treat `/speckit:resume` as the operator-facing recovery surface; use broader memory retrieval only when the canonical packet sources are missing or insufficient.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/deep-research.md:\n  Line 83: 5. EXECUTE RESEARCH ─> 3-5 research actions (WebFetch, Grep, Read, memory_search)\n\n  Line 172: | memory_search | Prior research findings | Find related spec work |\n\n  Line 326: | `memory_search` | Find prior research in memory system |\n\n  Line 327: | `memory_context` | Load context for the research topic |\n\n  Line 341: | Structured RQ format | Numeric-audit research questions MUST be structured as counted tables, not prose. Use rows of the form \"Produce a table where each row has the cited `path:line`\" to force enumeration. Prose RQ formats produce fabricated or partial counts under SWE-1.6. |\n\n  Line 548: | Hold findings in memory | Lost when context ends, no continuity | Write everything to iteration-NNN.md |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/context.md:\n  Line 3: description: \"Production context agent — comprehensive retrieval with canonical continuity recovery and structured Context Packages\"\n\n  Line 29: For prior-work recovery, this agent follows the same canonical continuity order as `/speckit:resume`: `handover.md` first, then `_memory.continuity`, then the packet's spec docs. Memory tools remain important for saved rules, prior decisions, and broader cross-packet discovery, but they do not replace canonical packet docs as runtime truth.\n\n  Line 34: > **Routing Rule**: No other agent performs exploration directly. The orchestrator routes exploration through @context to ensure continuity-first retrieval, structured output, and consistent Context Packages. @context itself is LEAF-only and must not dispatch sub-agents.\n\n  Line 54: 3. **CANONICAL CONTINUITY FIRST** -> For prior-work recovery, read `handover.md` -> `_memory.continuity` -> spec docs, then expand with memory tools only when needed.\n\n  Line 58: 7. **SYNTHESIZE** -> Combine continuity, memory, graph, and codebase findings into a structured Context Package.\n\n  Line 61: **Key Principle**: Canonical packet docs come first for continuity. Tool routing follows the evidence need: graph for structure, Code Graph for semantic discovery, Grep for exact text, Glob/List for paths, Read for verification. @context never writes and never delegates.\n\n  Line 76: | `memory_context` | Memory (L1) | Unified context retrieval | Retrieve intent-aware prior context when packet-local continuity is incomplete |\n\n  Line 77: | `memory_search` | Memory (L2) | Hybrid search across indexed records | Deep memory retrieval with content and cross-packet evidence |\n\n  Line 96: | Prior work / resume / \"what did we do\" | `Read` continuity docs | `memory_match_triggers` -> `memory_context` or `memory_search` if gaps remain | Packet docs outrank memory search for current runtime truth |\n\n  Line 110:     +-- Current packet continuity?\n\n  Line 111:     |     -> Read handover.md -> _memory.continuity -> spec docs\n\n  Line 129:           -> memory_match_triggers -> memory_context/memory_search\n\n  Line 148: **Default Tool Sequence**: scope lock -> continuity `Read` when relevant -> `memory_match_triggers` -> `code_graph_status()` for structural work -> `memory_context` or `memory_search` when continuity gaps remain -> `code_graph_query/context` for structure -> `code_graph_query` plus `Grep` for concepts -> `Glob`/`List` for paths -> `Grep` for exact anchors -> `Read` for cited verification -> `memory_list(specFolder)` when a relevant spec folder needs inventory.\n\n  Line 162: **Sources**: `handover.md`, `_memory.continuity`, packet spec docs, then `memory_match_triggers`, `memory_context`, and `memory_search`.\n\n  Line 167: - Inspect `handover.md` when present; it is the first continuity input for interrupted work.\n\n  Line 168: - Read `_memory.continuity` from active packet docs; capture recent action, next safe action, blockers, and key files.\n\n  Line 171: - Run `memory_context({ input: topic, mode: \"deep\" })` or `memory_search({ query: topic, includeContent: true })` only when packet-local continuity leaves gaps or broader history is needed.\n\n  Line 173: **Output**: Packet-local continuity summary plus relevant memory records with titles, trigger matches, and brief findings.\n\n  Line 191: **Tools**: `memory_search`, `memory_context`, `memory_list`, `memory_stats`.\n\n  Line 194: - Use `memory_search({ query: topic, includeContent: true })` for prior decisions, cross-packet lessons, and historical evidence.\n\n  Line 195: - Use `memory_context({ input: topic, mode: \"deep\" })` for ranked, intent-aware context when the caller asks for broad background.\n\n  Line 306: | Resume/Recovery | Prior work or continuity uncertainty | Reconstruct current state from canonical continuity |\n\n  Line 362: - Use canonical continuity first for prior-work recovery.\n\n  Line 378: - Skip canonical continuity for prior-work recovery.\n\n  Line 434: │  ├─► Canonical continuity recovery before implementation                │\n\n  Line 440: │  ├─► Layer 1: handover.md, _memory.continuity, spec docs, memory tools  │\n\n  Line 446: │  ├─► 2. Recover canonical continuity when relevant                      │\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/markdown.md:\n  Line 84: The refusal MUST appear verbatim for stress tests and operator audit. Silent refusal is non-compliant.\n\n  Line 111: Immediately after validating dispatch inputs, BEFORE any state read or workflow step, this agent MUST emit one canonical BINDING line per resolved setup value to stdout. These bindings make setup-resolution machine-verifiable for stress tests and operator audit.\n\n  Line 150: | `system-spec-kit` | Spec folder discipline             | When command setup names a spec folder or memory save is applicable | Packet scope, validation, optional continuity save routing                                                      |\n\n  Line 160: | `grep`   | Confirm exact markers, frontmatter keys, command variables, and template sections  | Setup, validation, and audit                                             |\n\n  Line 163: | `memory` | Optional continuity save when command setup explicitly calls for it                | Only for command-authorized spec context; otherwise report applicability |\n\n  Line 177: | **Mutation Calls** | Scoped to command-resolved outputs and explicit spec continuity files                          |\n\n  Line 260: 1. If hook context names an active spec folder, verify it against command setup before writing or claiming continuity.\n\n  Line 273: | **Illegal Nesting**             | Violates LEAF boundary and loses auditability | Perform direct work or emit the nested-dispatch REFUSE line  |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkm