{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780738196917,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeuERCb2AlX2T5Je","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_vlFvHrtB02Dcti994ilhrMuP","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/hooks/skill_advisor_hook.md","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/hooks/skill_advisor_hook.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Skill Advisor Hook Reference\n3: description: Operator contract for the native-first Skill Advisor hooks across Claude Code, Copilot CLI, Gemini CLI, Codex CLI, and the OpenCode plugin bridge.\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # Skill Advisor Hook Reference\n7: \n8: This reference describes the current prompt-time Skill Advisor integrations. The primary routing implementation is the native TypeScript package at `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/`; Python remains as a compatibility fallback through `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py`.\n9: \n10: ---\n11: \n12: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n13: \n14: ### Purpose\n15: \n16: Define the prompt-time Skill Advisor hook contract across Claude Code, Copilot CLI, Gemini CLI, Codex CLI, and the OpenCode plugin bridge.\n17: \n18: ### When to Use\n19: \n20: Load this reference when wiring runtime hooks, smoke-testing advisor brief output, checking threshold behavior, or diagnosing freshness and fail-open states.\n21: \n22: ### Core Principle\n23: \n24: Hooks only surface prompt-safe routing context. They do not replace explicit skill loading, persist raw prompt text, or block the user prompt on advisor failures.\n25: \n26: ### Default Flow\n27: \n28: The hook layer injects a compact advisor brief before the model responds. It does not replace skill loading; it only surfaces the likely skill route and the freshness state.\n29: \n30: Default flow:\n31: \n32: 1. Runtime receives a prompt.\n33: 2. Hook adapter parses the prompt payload.\n34: 3. Adapter calls `buildSkillAdvisorBrief(prompt, { runtime, workspaceRoot })`.\n35: 4. Native advisor is used when live or stale.\n36: 5. Compatibility fallback is used when native routing is unavailable.\n37: 6. Renderer returns a short `Advisor: ...` brief or an empty fail-open result.\n38: 7. Diagnostics are written without raw prompt text.\n39: \n40: When the prompt resumes a phase-parent target and `graph-metadata.json` has a fresh `derived.last_active_child_id` pointer (non-null and `derived.last_active_at` within 24 hours), the brief surfaces that active child as the next-action target instead of the parent's child listing. Missing, null, stale, or invalid pointers fall back to the parent control file/listing behavior.\n41: \n42: Native tool baseline:\n43: \n44: | Tool | Purpose |\n45: | --- | --- |\n46: | `advisor_recommend` | Prompt-safe skill recommendations with explicit `workspaceRoot`, lane attribution, lifecycle metadata, and effective thresholds. |\n47: | `advisor_status` | Diagnostic-only freshness, generation, trust state, `skillCount`, `lastScanAt`, and lane weights. It does not rebuild. |\n48: | `advisor_rebuild` | Explicit repair command for stale, absent, or unavailable advisor state; pass `force:true` to rebuild even when status is live. |\n49: | `advisor_validate` | Corpus, holdout, parity, safety, latency, threshold semantics, and prompt-safe telemetry rollups. |\n50: \n51: ---\n52: \n53: ## 2. RUNTIME MATRIX\n54: \n55: | Runtime | Source Hook | Output Shape | Notes |\n56: | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n57: | Claude Code | `mcp_server/hooks/claude/user-prompt-submit.ts` | `hookSpecificOutput.additionalContext` | Reads `prompt` and `cwd`. |\n58: | Gemini CLI | `mcp_server/hooks/gemini/user-prompt-submit.ts` | `hookSpecificOutput.additionalContext` | Reads `prompt`, `userPrompt`, or `request.prompt`. |\n59: | Codex CLI | `mcp_server/hooks/codex/user-prompt-submit.ts` | `hookSpecificOutput.additionalContext` | Stdin JSON is canonical and wins over argv JSON. |\n60: | Codex fallback | `mcp_server/hooks/codex/prompt-wrapper.ts` | `promptWrapper` and `wrappedPrompt` | Runs only when Codex hook policy reports hooks unavailable. |\n61: | OpenCode | `.opencode/plugins/mk-skill-advisor.js` + `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/plugin_bridges/mk-skill-advisor-bridge.mjs` | `experimental.chat.system.transform` mutates `output.system` | Bridge imports native `compat/index.js`, applies the same effective threshold on native and fallback paths, then falls back to the Python-backed brief path only when native is unavailable. |\n62: \n63: Build all runtime adapters (both steps required):\n64: \n65: ```bash\n66: # 1. Builds the system-spec-kit hook shims.\n67: npm --prefix .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server run build\n68: # 2. Builds the real adapter targets that those shims spawn.\n69: npm --prefix .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server run build\n70: ```\n71: \n72: ---\n73: \n74: ## 3. SHARED BEHAVIOR\n75: \n76: All hook adapters:\n77: \n78: - fail open with `{}` or no context when parsing, native status, scoring, or rendering fails\n79: - honor `SPECKIT_SKILL_ADVISOR_HOOK_DISABLED=1`\n80: - avoid persisting raw prompts in diagnostics, cache metadata, status, or attribution\n81: - use the same freshness vocabulary: `live`, `stale`, `absent`, `unavailable`\n82: - use the same status vocabulary: `ok`, `skipped`, `degraded`, `fail_open`\n83: - render a compact `Advisor: ...` brief only when a route passes threshold\n84: - use `0.8 / 0.35` as the default prompt-time confidence/uncertainty routing thresholds unless a caller explicitly overrides the confidence threshold\n85: - persist prompt-safe hook diagnostics across hook processes and exclude raw prompt text from the durable sink\n86: \n87: Native `advisor_recommend` returns prompt-safe lane contribution metadata when `includeAttribution` is true. It does not return prompt-derived evidence snippets.\n88: \n89: ---\n90: \n91: ## 4. SETUP AND SMOKE TESTS\n92: \n93: ### Claude Code\n94: \n95: ```bash\n96: printf '%s' '{\"prompt\":\"help me commit my changes\",\"cwd\":\"'\"$PWD\"'\",\"hook_event_name\":\"UserPromptSubmit\"}' | \\\n97:   node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/dist/hooks/claude/user-prompt-submit.js\n98: ```\n99: \n100: Expected: `{}` or `hookSpecificOutput.additionalContext` beginning with `Advisor:`.\n101: \n102: ### Gemini CLI\n103: \n104: ```bash\n105: printf '%s' '{\"request\":{\"prompt\":\"create a flowchart for the auth process\",\"cwd\":\"'\"$PWD\"'\"}}' | \\\n106:   node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/dist/hooks/gemini/user-prompt-submit.js\n107: ```\n108: \n109: Expected: `{}` or `hookSpecificOutput.additionalContext`.\n110: \n111: ### Codex CLI\n112: \n113: ```bash\n114: printf '%s' '{\"prompt\":\"update documentation with DQI checks\",\"cwd\":\"'\"$PWD\"'\"}' | \\\n115:   node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/dist/hooks/codex/user-prompt-submit.js\n116: ```\n117: \n118: Prompt wrapper fallback:\n119: \n120: ```bash\n121: printf '%s' '{\"prompt\":\"update documentation with DQI checks\",\"cwd\":\"'\"$PWD\"'\"}' | \\\n122:   node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/dist/hooks/codex/prompt-wrapper.js\n123: ```\n124: \n125: ### OpenCode Plugin Bridge\n126: \n127: ```bash\n128: printf '%s' '{\"prompt\":\"save this conversation context to memory\",\"workspaceRoot\":\"'\"$PWD\"'\",\"runtime\":\"opencode\",\"maxTokens\":80,\"thresholdConfidence\":0.8}' | \\\n129:   node .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/plugin_bridges/mk-skill-advisor-bridge.mjs\n130: ```\n131: \n132: Expected: `status: \"ok\"` with `metadata.route: \"native\"` when native is available, `metadata.workspaceRoot` matching the supplied repo root, and `metadata.effectiveThresholds` showing the active confidence/uncertainty pair.\n133: \n134: ---\n135: \n136: ## 5. CONTROL FLAGS\n137: \n138: | Control | Applies To | Behavior |\n139: | --- | --- | --- |\n140: | `SPECKIT_SKILL_ADVISOR_HOOK_DISABLED=1` | native MCP recommendation path, runtime hooks, plugin bridge, Python shim | Disables prompt-time advisor work and returns empty/skipped prompt-safe output. |\n141: | `SPECKIT_COPILOT_INSTRUCTIONS_PATH` | Copilot CLI | Overrides the local custom-instructions target path; useful for tests and sandboxes. |\n142: | `SPECKIT_COPILOT_INSTRUCTIONS_DISABLED=1` | Copilot CLI | Skips writing the Spec Kit managed custom-instructions block while leaving the hook fail-open. |\n143: | `SPECKIT_SKILL_ADVISOR_FORCE_LOCAL=1` | Python shim and OpenCode bridge diagnostics | Forces local Python fallback where supported. |\n144: | `--force-native` | Python shim | Requires native `advisor_recommend`; exits nonzero if unavailable. |\n145: | `--force-local` | Python shim | Bypasses native routing and uses local Python scoring. |\n146: | `--threshold` | Python shim | Sets confidence threshold; default is `0.8`. |\n147: | `--stdin` | Python shim | Reads one prompt from stdin. |\n148: \n149: Examples:\n150: \n151: ```bash\n152: python3 .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py --force-native \"save this context\"\n153: python3 .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py --force-local \"save this context\"\n154: printf '%s' \"save this context\" | python3 .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py --stdin\n155: ```\n156: \n157: ---\n158: \n159: ## 6. OPERATOR STATES\n160: \n161: Use `advisor_status` for prompt-safe state:\n162: \n163: ```text\n164: advisor_status({\"workspaceRoot\":\"/absolute/path/to/repo\"})\n165: ```\n166: \n167: Freshness states (the canonical caller-trust axis returned by `advisor_status`):\n168: \n169: | State | Meaning | Operator Action |\n170: | --- | --- | --- |\n171: | `live` | Current graph generation is trusted. | No action. |\n172: | `stale` | Sources are newer than graph state. | Run `advisor_rebuild({})`, then recheck with `advisor_status`. |\n173: | `absent` | Required graph state is missing. | Run `advisor_rebuild({})`. `advisor_recommend` should fail open with empty recommendations until repaired. |\n174: | `unavailable` | Status cannot be read. | Inspect daemon logs and SQLite state, then run `advisor_rebuild({\"force\":true})` when source metadata is intact. |\n175: \n176: Hook statuses (the diagnostic axis on the rendered brief, distinct from freshness):\n177: \n178: | Status | Meaning | Operator Action |\n179: | --- | --- | --- |\n180: | `ok` | Brief produced or native call succeeded. | No action. |\n181: | `skipped` | Prompt policy, disable flag, or no matching route skipped advisor output. | No action. |\n182: | `degraded` | Hook or daemon can only provide limited trust. | Follow OP-001 in the playbook. |\n183: | `fail_open` | Error path returned safe empty output and let the prompt continue. | Inspect diagnostics if recurring. |\n184: \n185: H5 operator scenarios:\n186: \n187: - OP-001 degraded daemon detection, log inspection, remediation\n188: - OP-002 quarantined daemon malformed SKILL.md identify, fix, revert\n189: - OP-003 unavailable daemon corrupted SQLite rebuild-from-source trigger\n190: \n191: See `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md`.\n192: \n193: ---\n194: \n195: ## 7. PRIVACY AND DIAGNOSTICS\n196: \n197: Prompt-safety rules:\n198: \n199: - Raw prompt text is never persisted in status output.\n200: - Prompt cache keys are HMAC/hash based.\n201: - Diagnostics use runtime, status, freshness, duration, cache, skill label, generation, and normalized error codes.\n202: - `sanitizeSkillLabel` guards labels and lifecycle redirect fields before public output.\n203: - `includeAttribution` returns numeric lane contribution metadata only.\n204: \n205: Diagnostic status values:\n206: \n207: | Status | Meaning |\n208: | --- | --- |\n209: | `ok` | Brief produced or native call succeeded. |\n210: | `skipped` | Prompt policy, disable flag, or no matching route skipped advisor output. |\n211: | `degraded` | Native or fallback path could not provide full trust. |\n212: | `fail_open` | Error path returned safe empty output and let the prompt continue. |\n213: \n214: ---\n215: \n216: ## 8. VALIDATION\n217: \n218: Native validation:\n219: \n220: ```text\n221: advisor_validate({\"confirmHeavyRun\":true,\"workspaceRoot\":\"/absolute/path/to/repo\",\"skillSlug\":null})\n222: ```\n223: \n224: Package checks:\n225: \n226: ```bash\n227: npm --prefix .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server run typecheck\n228: npm --prefix .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server test -- --reporter=default\n229: ```\n230: \n231: Python compatibility:\n232: \n233: ```bash\n234: python3 .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor_regression.py \\\n235:   --dataset .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/fixtures/skill_advisor_regression_cases.jsonl\n236: ```\n237: \n238: Current baseline:\n239: \n240: - 80.5% full corpus.\n241: - 77.5% holdout.\n242: - UNKNOWN <= 10.\n243: - 0 regressions on Python-correct prompts.\n244: - 52/52 Python regression suite passed.\n245: \n246: Manual scenarios live in the Skill Advisor playbook:\n247: \n248: ```text\n249: .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md\n250: ```\n251: \n252: ---\n\n(End of file - total 252 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Skill Advisor Hook Reference\ndescription: Operator contract for the native-first Skill Advisor hooks across Claude Code, Copilot CLI, Gemini CLI, Codex CLI, and the OpenCode plugin bridge.\n---\n\n# Skill Advisor Hook Reference\n\nThis reference describes the current prompt-time Skill Advisor integrations. The primary routing implementation is the native TypeScript package at `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/`; Python remains as a compatibility fallback through `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py`.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nDefine the prompt-time Skill Advisor hook contract across Claude Code, Copilot CLI, Gemini CLI, Codex CLI, and the OpenCode plugin bridge.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this reference when wiring runtime hooks, smoke-testing advisor brief output, checking threshold behavior, or diagnosing freshness and fail-open states.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/hooks/skill_advisor_hook.md","text":"---\ntitle: Skill Advisor Hook Reference\ndescription: Operator contract for the native-first Skill Advisor hooks across Claude Code, Copilot CLI, Gemini CLI, Codex CLI, and the OpenCode plugin bridge.\n---\n\n# Skill Advisor Hook Reference\n\nThis reference describes the current prompt-time Skill Advisor integrations. The primary routing implementation is the native TypeScript package at `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/`; Python remains as a compatibility fallback through `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py`.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nDefine the prompt-time Skill Advisor hook contract across Claude Code, Copilot CLI, Gemini CLI, Codex CLI, and the OpenCode plugin bridge.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this reference when wiring runtime hooks, smoke-testing advisor brief output, checking threshold behavior, or diagnosing freshness and fail-open states.\n\n### Core Principle\n\nHooks only surface prompt-safe routing context. They do not replace explicit skill loading, persist raw prompt text, or block the user prompt on advisor failures.\n\n### Default Flow\n\nThe hook layer injects a compact advisor brief before the model responds. It does not replace skill loading; it only surfaces the likely skill route and the freshness state.\n\nDefault flow:\n\n1. Runtime receives a prompt.\n2. Hook adapter parses the prompt payload.\n3. Adapter calls `buildSkillAdvisorBrief(prompt, { runtime, workspaceRoot })`.\n4. Native advisor is used when live or stale.\n5. Compatibility fallback is used when native routing is unavailable.\n6. Renderer returns a short `Advisor: ...` brief or an empty fail-open result.\n7. Diagnostics are written without raw prompt text.\n\nWhen the prompt resumes a phase-parent target and `graph-metadata.json` has a fresh `derived.last_active_child_id` pointer (non-null and `derived.last_active_at` within 24 hours), the brief surfaces that active child as the next-action target instead of the parent's child listing. Missing, null, stale, or invalid pointers fall back to the parent control file/listing behavior.\n\nNative tool baseline:\n\n| Tool | Purpose |\n| --- | --- |\n| `advisor_recommend` | Prompt-safe skill recommendations with explicit `workspaceRoot`, lane attribution, lifecycle metadata, and effective thresholds. |\n| `advisor_status` | Diagnostic-only freshness, generation, trust state, `skillCount`, `lastScanAt`, and lane weights. It does not rebuild. |\n| `advisor_rebuild` | Explicit repair command for stale, absent, or unavailable advisor state; pass `force:true` to rebuild even when status is live. |\n| `advisor_validate` | Corpus, holdout, parity, safety, latency, threshold semantics, and prompt-safe telemetry rollups. |\n\n---\n\n## 2. RUNTIME MATRIX\n\n| Runtime | Source Hook | Output Shape | Notes |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Claude Code | `mcp_server/hooks/claude/user-prompt-submit.ts` | `hookSpecificOutput.additionalContext` | Reads `prompt` and `cwd`. |\n| Gemini CLI | `mcp_server/hooks/gemini/user-prompt-submit.ts` | `hookSpecificOutput.additionalContext` | Reads `prompt`, `userPrompt`, or `request.prompt`. |\n| Codex CLI | `mcp_server/hooks/codex/user-prompt-submit.ts` | `hookSpecificOutput.additionalContext` | Stdin JSON is canonical and wins over argv JSON. |\n| Codex fallback | `mcp_server/hooks/codex/prompt-wrapper.ts` | `promptWrapper` and `wrappedPrompt` | Runs only when Codex hook policy reports hooks unavailable. |\n| OpenCode | `.opencode/plugins/mk-skill-advisor.js` + `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/plugin_bridges/mk-skill-advisor-bridge.mjs` | `experimental.chat.system.transform` mutates `output.system` | Bridge imports native `compat/index.js`, applies the same effective threshold on native and fallback paths, then falls back to the Python-backed brief path only when native is unavailable. |\n\nBuild all runtime adapters (both steps required):\n\n```bash\n# 1. Builds the system-spec-kit hook shims.\nnpm --prefix .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server run build\n# 2. Builds the real adapter targets that those shims spawn.\nnpm --prefix .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server run build\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. SHARED BEHAVIOR\n\nAll hook adapters:\n\n- fail open with `{}` or no context when parsing, native status, scoring, or rendering fails\n- honor `SPECKIT_SKILL_ADVISOR_HOOK_DISABLED=1`\n- avoid persisting raw prompts in diagnostics, cache metadata, status, or attribution\n- use the same freshness vocabulary: `live`, `stale`, `absent`, `unavailable`\n- use the same status vocabulary: `ok`, `skipped`, `degraded`, `fail_open`\n- render a compact `Advisor: ...` brief only when a route passes threshold\n- use `0.8 / 0.35` as the default prompt-time confidence/uncertainty routing thresholds unless a caller explicitly overrides the confidence threshold\n- persist prompt-safe hook diagnostics across hook processes and exclude raw prompt text from the durable sink\n\nNative `advisor_recommend` returns prompt-safe lane contribution metadata when `includeAttribution` is true. It does not return prompt-derived evidence snippets.\n\n---\n\n## 4. SETUP AND SMOKE TESTS\n\n### Claude Code\n\n```bash\nprintf '%s' '{\"prompt\":\"help me commit my changes\",\"cwd\":\"'\"$PWD\"'\",\"hook_event_name\":\"UserPromptSubmit\"}' | \\\n  node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/dist/hooks/claude/user-prompt-submit.js\n```\n\nExpected: `{}` or `hookSpecificOutput.additionalContext` beginning with `Advisor:`.\n\n### Gemini CLI\n\n```bash\nprintf '%s' '{\"request\":{\"prompt\":\"create a flowchart for the auth process\",\"cwd\":\"'\"$PWD\"'\"}}' | \\\n  node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/dist/hooks/gemini/user-prompt-submit.js\n```\n\nExpected: `{}` or `hookSpecificOutput.additionalContext`.\n\n### Codex CLI\n\n```bash\nprintf '%s' '{\"prompt\":\"update documentation with DQI checks\",\"cwd\":\"'\"$PWD\"'\"}' | \\\n  node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/dist/hooks/codex/user-prompt-submit.js\n```\n\nPrompt wrapper fallback:\n\n```bash\nprintf '%s' '{\"prompt\":\"update documentation with DQI checks\",\"cwd\":\"'\"$PWD\"'\"}' | \\\n  node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/dist/hooks/codex/prompt-wrapper.js\n```\n\n### OpenCode Plugin Bridge\n\n```bash\nprintf '%s' '{\"prompt\":\"save this conversation context to memory\",\"workspaceRoot\":\"'\"$PWD\"'\",\"runtime\":\"opencode\",\"maxTokens\":80,\"thresholdConfidence\":0.8}' | \\\n  node .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/plugin_bridges/mk-skill-advisor-bridge.mjs\n```\n\nExpected: `status: \"ok\"` with `metadata.route: \"native\"` when native is available, `metadata.workspaceRoot` matching the supplied repo root, and `metadata.effectiveThresholds` showing the active confidence/uncertainty pair.\n\n---\n\n## 5. CONTROL FLAGS\n\n| Control | Applies To | Behavior |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| `SPECKIT_SKILL_ADVISOR_HOOK_DISABLED=1` | native MCP recommendation path, runtime hooks, plugin bridge, Python shim | Disables prompt-time advisor work and returns empty/skipped prompt-safe output. |\n| `SPECKIT_COPILOT_INSTRUCTIONS_PATH` | Copilot CLI | Overrides the local custom-instructions target path; useful for tests and sandboxes. |\n| `SPECKIT_COPILOT_INSTRUCTIONS_DISABLED=1` | Copilot CLI | Skips writing the Spec Kit managed custom-instructions block while leaving the hook fail-open. |\n| `SPECKIT_SKILL_ADVISOR_FORCE_LOCAL=1` | Python shim and OpenCode bridge diagnostics | Forces local Python fallback where supported. |\n| `--force-native` | Python shim | Requires native `advisor_recommend`; exits nonzero if unavailable. |\n| `--force-local` | Python shim | Bypasses native routing and uses local Python scoring. |\n| `--threshold` | Python shim | Sets confidence threshold; default is `0.8`. |\n| `--stdin` | Python shim | Reads one prompt from stdin. |\n\nExamples:\n\n```bash\npython3 .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py --force-native \"save this context\"\npython3 .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py --force-local \"save this context\"\nprintf '%s' \"save this context\" | python3 .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py --stdin\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. OPERATOR STATES\n\nUse `advisor_status` for prompt-safe state:\n\n```text\nadvisor_status({\"workspaceRoot\":\"/absolute/path/to/repo\"})\n```\n\nFreshness states (the canonical caller-trust axis returned by `advisor_status`):\n\n| State | Meaning | Operator Action |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| `live` | Current graph generation is trusted. | No action. |\n| `stale` | Sources are newer than graph state. | Run `advisor_rebuild({})`, then recheck with `advisor_status`. |\n| `absent` | Required graph state is missing. | Run `advisor_rebuild({})`. `advisor_recommend` should fail open with empty recommendations until repaired. |\n| `unavailable` | Status cannot be read. | Inspect daemon logs and SQLite state, then run `advisor_rebuild({\"force\":true})` when source metadata is intact. |\n\nHook statuses (the diagnostic axis on the rendered brief, distinct from freshness):\n\n| Status | Meaning | Operator Action |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| `ok` | Brief produced or native call succeeded. | No action. |\n| `skipped` | Prompt policy, disable flag, or no matching route skipped advisor output. | No action. |\n| `degraded` | Hook or daemon can only provide limited trust. | Follow OP-001 in the playbook. |\n| `fail_open` | Error path returned safe empty output and let the prompt continue. | Inspect diagnostics if recurring. |\n\nH5 operator scenarios:\n\n- OP-001 degraded daemon detection, log inspection, remediation\n- OP-002 quarantined daemon malformed SKILL.md identify, fix, revert\n- OP-003 unavailable daemon corrupted SQLite rebuild-from-source trigger\n\nSee `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 7. PRIVACY AND DIAGNOSTICS\n\nPrompt-safety rules:\n\n- Raw prompt text is never persisted in status output.\n- Prompt cache keys are HMAC/hash based.\n- Diagnostics use runtime, status, freshness, duration, cache, skill label, generation, and normalized error codes.\n- `sanitizeSkillLabel` guards labels and lifecycle redirect fields before public output.\n- `includeAttribution` returns numeric lane contribution metadata only.\n\nDiagnostic status values:\n\n| Status | Meaning |\n| --- | --- |\n| `ok` | Brief produced or native call succeeded. |\n| `skipped` | Prompt policy, disable flag, or no matching route skipped advisor output. |\n| `degraded` | Native or fallback path could not provide full trust. |\n| `fail_open` | Error path returned safe empty output and let the prompt continue. |\n\n---\n\n## 8. VALIDATION\n\nNative validation:\n\n```text\nadvisor_validate({\"confirmHeavyRun\":true,\"workspaceRoot\":\"/absolute/path/to/repo\",\"skillSlug\":null})\n```\n\nPackage checks:\n\n```bash\nnpm --prefix .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server run typecheck\nnpm --prefix .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server test -- --reporter=default\n```\n\nPython compatibility:\n\n```bash\npython3 .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor_regression.py \\\n  --dataset .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/fixtures/skill_advisor_regression_cases.jsonl\n```\n\nCurrent baseline:\n\n- 80.5% full corpus.\n- 77.5% holdout.\n- UNKNOWN <= 10.\n- 0 regressions on Python-correct prompts.\n- 52/52 Python regression suite passed.\n\nManual scenarios live in the Skill Advisor playbook:\n\n```text\n.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md\n```\n\n---","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":252,"totalLines":252,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/hooks/skill_advisor_hook.md","time":{"start":1780738196911,"end":1780738196916}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0850f20a74e32d69016a23e894d9308191970e5eee5365e376"}},"id":"prt_e9c4485a7001EJQPYkqRMP0RLw","sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeuERCb2AlX2T5Je","messageID":"msg_e9c4461320011YuE7wXipq34LO"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780738196970,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeuERCb2AlX2T5Je","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_yLSPqXQDA2fLcrK7fWTNFfw7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/hooks/memory-surface.ts","offset":1,"limit":300},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/hooks/memory-surface.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n2: // MODULE: Memory Surface\n3: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n4: // Lib modules\n5: import * as vectorIndex from '../lib/search/vector-index.js';\n6: import * as triggerMatcher from '../lib/parsing/trigger-matcher.js';\n7: import { enrichWithRetrievalDirectives } from '../lib/search/retrieval-directives.js';\n8: import { estimateTokenCount } from '@spec-kit/shared/utils/token-estimate';\n9: import { recordBootstrapEvent } from '../lib/session/context-metrics.js';\n10: import * as workingMemory from '../lib/cognitive/working-memory.js';\n11: import { buildStructuralBootstrapContract } from '../lib/session/session-snapshot.js';\n12: import { getCodeGraphStatusSnapshotFromMarker } from '../lib/code-graph-boundary.js';\n13: \n14: import type { Database } from '@spec-kit/shared/types';\n15: // Import the type from the neutral seam module instead of from\n16: // session-snapshot (which itself transitively imports this file's value-level\n17: // helpers `isSessionPrimed` and `getLastActiveSessionId`). The type-only\n18: // import via the seam breaks the value-level cycle.\n19: import type { StructuralBootstrapContract } from '../lib/session/structural-bootstrap-contract.js';\n20: \n21: /* ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n22:    1. TYPES\n23: ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n24: \n25: interface ConstitutionalMemory {\n26:   id: number;\n27:   specFolder: string;\n28:   filePath: string;\n29:   title: string;\n30:   importanceTier: string;\n31:   /** PI-A4: LLM-consumable retrieval directive, e.g. \"Always surface when: …\" */\n32:   retrieval_directive?: string;\n33: }\n34: \n35: interface AutoSurfaceResult {\n36:   constitutional: ConstitutionalMemory[];\n37:   triggered: {\n38:     memory_id: number;\n39:     spec_folder: string;\n40:     title: string;\n41:     matched_phrases: string[];\n42:   }[];\n43:   codeGraphStatus?: {\n44:     status: 'ok' | 'error';\n45:     data?: {\n46:       totalFiles: number;\n47:       totalNodes: number;\n48:       totalEdges: number;\n49:       staleFiles: number;\n50:       lastScanAt: string | null;\n51:       dbFileSize: number | null;\n52:       schemaVersion: number;\n53:       nodesByKind: Record<string, number>;\n54:       edgesByType: Record<string, number>;\n55:       parseHealth: Record<string, number>;\n56:     };\n57:     error?: string;\n58:   };\n59:   sessionPrimed?: boolean;\n60:   primedTool?: string;\n61:   /** Structured Prime Package returned on first tool call */\n62:   primePackage?: PrimePackage;\n63:   surfaced_at: string;\n64:   latencyMs: number;\n65: }\n66: \n67: /** Structured session prime payload for non-hook CLI auto-priming */\n68: interface PrimePackage {\n69:   specFolder: string | null;\n70:   currentTask: string | null;\n71:   codeGraphStatus: 'fresh' | 'stale' | 'empty';\n72:   recommendedCalls: string[];\n73:   /** Structural bootstrap contract for non-hook runtimes */\n74:   structuralContext?: StructuralBootstrapContract;\n75:   /** Graph retrieval routing rules for AI session priming */\n76:   routingRules?: {\n77:     graphRetrieval: string;\n78:     communitySearch: string;\n79:     toolRouting: string;\n80:   };\n81: }\n82: \n83: /* ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n84:    2. MEMORY SURFACE HOOK CONFIGURATION\n85: ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n86: \n87: const MEMORY_AWARE_TOOLS: Set<string> = new Set([\n88:   'memory_context',\n89:   'memory_search',\n90:   'memory_quick_search',\n91:   'memory_match_triggers',\n92:   'memory_list',\n93:   'memory_save',\n94:   'memory_index_scan'\n95: ]);\n96: \n97: // Token budgets for dual-scope lifecycle hooks\n98: const TOOL_DISPATCH_TOKEN_BUDGET = 4000;\n99: const COMPACTION_TOKEN_BUDGET = 4000;\n100: \n101: // Constitutional memory cache\n102: // Module-level mutable state: safe in a single-process MCP server.\n103: // If the server ever runs multi-process, replace with a shared store.\n104: let constitutionalCache: ConstitutionalMemory[] | null = null;\n105: let constitutionalCacheTime = 0;\n106: const CONSTITUTIONAL_CACHE_TTL = 60000; // 1 minute\n107: // Per-session priming tracker: a Set of session IDs that have been primed.\n108: // Replaces the previous process-global boolean to avoid skipping priming\n109: // for new sessions on long-lived MCP servers.\n110: const primedSessionIds: Set<string> = new Set();\n111: \n112: // Session-level tracking for prime package and session_health\n113: const serverStartedAt = Date.now();\n114: let lastToolCallAt = Date.now();\n115: let lastActiveSessionId: string | null = null;\n116: \n117: /** Update last tool call timestamp (called from context-server dispatch). */\n118: function recordToolCall(sessionId?: string): void {\n119:   lastToolCallAt = Date.now();\n120:   if (typeof sessionId === 'string' && sessionId.trim().length > 0) {\n121:     lastActiveSessionId = sessionId.trim();\n122:   }\n123: }\n124: \n125: /** Get session tracking timestamps */\n126: function getSessionTimestamps(): { serverStartedAt: number; lastToolCallAt: number } {\n127:   return { serverStartedAt, lastToolCallAt };\n128: }\n129: \n130: /**\n131:  * Check if a specific session has been primed.\n132:  * Session identity is required to avoid cross-session bleed-through.\n133:  */\n134: function isSessionPrimed(sessionId: string): boolean {\n135:   return primedSessionIds.has(sessionId);\n136: }\n137: \n138: /** Mark a specific session as primed */\n139: function markSessionPrimed(sessionId: string): void {\n140:   primedSessionIds.add(sessionId);\n141:   lastActiveSessionId = sessionId;\n142: }\n143: \n144: function getLastActiveSessionId(): string | null {\n145:   return lastActiveSessionId;\n146: }\n147: \n148: /* ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n149:    3. CONTEXT EXTRACTION\n150: ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n151: \n152: function extractContextHint(args: Record<string, unknown> | null | undefined): string | null {\n153:   if (!args || typeof args !== 'object') return null;\n154: \n155:   const contextFields = ['input', 'query', 'prompt', 'specFolder', 'filePath'];\n156:   for (const field of contextFields) {\n157:     if (args[field] && typeof args[field] === 'string' && (args[field] as string).length >= 3) {\n158:       return args[field] as string;\n159:     }\n160:   }\n161: \n162:   // Join concepts array if present\n163:   if (args.concepts && Array.isArray(args.concepts) && args.concepts.length > 0) {\n164:     const strings = args.concepts.filter((c): c is string => typeof c === 'string');\n165:     if (strings.length > 0) return strings.join(' ');\n166:   }\n167: \n168:   return null;\n169: }\n170: \n171: /* ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n172:    4. CONSTITUTIONAL MEMORIES\n173: ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n174: \n175: async function getConstitutionalMemories(): Promise<ConstitutionalMemory[]> {\n176:   const now = Date.now();\n177: \n178:   if (constitutionalCache && (now - constitutionalCacheTime) < CONSTITUTIONAL_CACHE_TTL) {\n179:     return constitutionalCache;\n180:   }\n181: \n182:   try {\n183:     const db: Database | null = vectorIndex.tryGetDb();\n184:     if (!db) return [];\n185: \n186:     const rows = db.prepare(`\n187:       SELECT id, spec_folder, file_path, title, trigger_phrases, importance_tier\n188:       FROM memory_index\n189:       WHERE importance_tier = 'constitutional'\n190:       AND embedding_status IN ('success', 'pending', 'partial')\n191:       ORDER BY created_at DESC\n192:       LIMIT 10\n193:     `).all();\n194: \n195:     constitutionalCache = (rows as Record<string, unknown>[]).map((r) => ({\n196:       id: r.id as number,\n197:       specFolder: r.spec_folder as string,\n198:       filePath: r.file_path as string,\n199:       title: r.title as string,\n200:       importanceTier: r.importance_tier as string\n201:     }));\n202:     constitutionalCacheTime = now;\n203: \n204:     return constitutionalCache;\n205:   } catch (err: unknown) {\n206:     const message = err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err);\n207:     console.warn('[SK-004] Failed to fetch constitutional memories:', message);\n208:     return [];\n209:   }\n210: }\n211: \n212: function clearConstitutionalCache(): void {\n213:   constitutionalCache = null;\n214:   constitutionalCacheTime = 0;\n215: }\n216: \n217: function getCodeGraphStatusSnapshot(): NonNullable<AutoSurfaceResult['codeGraphStatus']> {\n218:   return getCodeGraphStatusSnapshotFromMarker();\n219: }\n220: \n221: /* ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n222:    5. AUTO-SURFACE MEMORIES\n223: ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n224: \n225: function enforceAutoSurfaceTokenBudget(\n226:   result: AutoSurfaceResult | null,\n227:   tokenBudget: number,\n228:   hookName: 'tool-dispatch' | 'compaction' | 'memory-aware'\n229: ): AutoSurfaceResult | null {\n230:   if (!result) {\n231:     return null;\n232:   }\n233: \n234:   const measureTokens = (candidate: AutoSurfaceResult): number =>\n235:     estimateTokenCount(JSON.stringify(candidate));\n236: \n237:   const budgetLimit = Number.isFinite(tokenBudget) && tokenBudget > 0\n238:     ? tokenBudget\n239:     : TOOL_DISPATCH_TOKEN_BUDGET;\n240: \n241:   let boundedResult: AutoSurfaceResult = result;\n242:   let tokenCount = measureTokens(boundedResult);\n243: \n244:   if (tokenCount <= budgetLimit) {\n245:     return boundedResult;\n246:   }\n247: \n248:   const triggered = [...boundedResult.triggered];\n249:   while (triggered.length > 0 && tokenCount > budgetLimit) {\n250:     triggered.pop();\n251:     boundedResult = { ...boundedResult, triggered };\n252:     tokenCount = measureTokens(boundedResult);\n253:   }\n254: \n255:   const constitutional = [...boundedResult.constitutional];\n256:   while (constitutional.length > 0 && tokenCount > budgetLimit) {\n257:     constitutional.pop();\n258:     boundedResult = { ...boundedResult, constitutional };\n259:     tokenCount = measureTokens(boundedResult);\n260:   }\n261: \n262:   if (tokenCount > budgetLimit) {\n263:     console.warn(\n264:       `[SK-004] Auto-surface output exceeded ${hookName} token budget ` +\n265:       `(${tokenCount} > ${budgetLimit}); dropping payload`\n266:     );\n267:     return null;\n268:   }\n269: \n270:   console.warn(\n271:     `[SK-004] Auto-surface output truncated to fit ${hookName} token budget ` +\n272:     `(${tokenCount}/${budgetLimit})`\n273:   );\n274:   return boundedResult;\n275: }\n276: \n277: /**\n278:  * Phase C: Get top-N attention-weighted memory IDs from working memory.\n279:  * Used to boost trigger-matched results that also appear in the active\n280:  * working set, improving surface relevance.\n281:  *\n282:  * @param limit - Maximum number of memory IDs to return\n283:  * @returns Set of memory IDs with high attention in working memory\n284:  */\n285: function getAttentionWeightedMemoryIds(limit: number = 5): Set<number> {\n286:   try {\n287:     const db: Database | null = vectorIndex.tryGetDb();\n288:     if (!db) return new Set();\n289: \n290:     // Query top attention-weighted memories, scoped to the current session\n291:     // by filtering to entries focused within the last hour. This prevents\n292:     // stale cross-session entries from influencing auto-surface ordering.\n293:     const oneHourAgo = new Date(Date.now() - 60 * 60 * 1000).toISOString();\n294:     const rows = db.prepare(`\n295:       SELECT DISTINCT wm.memory_id\n296:       FROM working_memory wm\n297:       WHERE wm.memory_id IS NOT NULL\n298:         AND wm.attention_score > ?\n299:         AND wm.last_focused >= ?\n300:       ORDER BY wm.attention_score DESC, wm.last_focused DESC\n\n(Showing lines 1-300 of 659. Use offset=301 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// MODULE: Memory Surface\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// Lib modules\nimport * as vectorIndex from '../lib/search/vector-index.js';\nimport * as triggerMatcher from '../lib/parsing/trigger-matcher.js';\nimport { enrichWithRetrievalDirectives } from '../lib/search/retrieval-directives.js';\nimport { estimateTokenCount } from '@spec-kit/shared/utils/token-estimate';\nimport { recordBootstrapEvent } from '../lib/session/context-metrics.js';\nimport * as workingMemory from '../lib/cognitive/working-memory.js';\nimport { buildStructuralBootstrapContract } from '../lib/session/session-snapshot.js';\nimport { getCodeGraphStatusSnapshotFromMarker } from '../lib/code-graph-boundary.js';\n\nimport type { Database } from '@spec-kit/shared/types';\n// Import the type from the neutral seam module instead of from\n// session-snapshot (which itself transitively imports this file's value-level\n// helpers `isSessionPrimed` and `getLastActiveSessionId`). The type-only\n// import via the seam breaks the value-level cycle.\nimport type { StructuralBootstrapContract } from '../lib/session/structural-bootstrap-contract.js';\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/hooks/memory-surface.ts","text":"// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// MODULE: Memory Surface\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// Lib modules\nimport * as vectorIndex from '../lib/search/vector-index.js';\nimport * as triggerMatcher from '../lib/parsing/trigger-matcher.js';\nimport { enrichWithRetrievalDirectives } from '../lib/search/retrieval-directives.js';\nimport { estimateTokenCount } from '@spec-kit/shared/utils/token-estimate';\nimport { recordBootstrapEvent } from '../lib/session/context-metrics.js';\nimport * as workingMemory from '../lib/cognitive/working-memory.js';\nimport { buildStructuralBootstrapContract } from '../lib/session/session-snapshot.js';\nimport { getCodeGraphStatusSnapshotFromMarker } from '../lib/code-graph-boundary.js';\n\nimport type { Database } from '@spec-kit/shared/types';\n// Import the type from the neutral seam module instead of from\n// session-snapshot (which itself transitively imports this file's value-level\n// helpers `isSessionPrimed` and `getLastActiveSessionId`). The type-only\n// import via the seam breaks the value-level cycle.\nimport type { StructuralBootstrapContract } from '../lib/session/structural-bootstrap-contract.js';\n\n/* ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n   1. TYPES\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n\ninterface ConstitutionalMemory {\n  id: number;\n  specFolder: string;\n  filePath: string;\n  title: string;\n  importanceTier: string;\n  /** PI-A4: LLM-consumable retrieval directive, e.g. \"Always surface when: …\" */\n  retrieval_directive?: string;\n}\n\ninterface AutoSurfaceResult {\n  constitutional: ConstitutionalMemory[];\n  triggered: {\n    memory_id: number;\n    spec_folder: string;\n    title: string;\n    matched_phrases: string[];\n  }[];\n  codeGraphStatus?: {\n    status: 'ok' | 'error';\n    data?: {\n      totalFiles: number;\n      totalNodes: number;\n      totalEdges: number;\n      staleFiles: number;\n      lastScanAt: string | null;\n      dbFileSize: number | null;\n      schemaVersion: number;\n      nodesByKind: Record<string, number>;\n      edgesByType: Record<string, number>;\n      parseHealth: Record<string, number>;\n    };\n    error?: string;\n  };\n  sessionPrimed?: boolean;\n  primedTool?: string;\n  /** Structured Prime Package returned on first tool call */\n  primePackage?: PrimePackage;\n  surfaced_at: string;\n  latencyMs: number;\n}\n\n/** Structured session prime payload for non-hook CLI auto-priming */\ninterface PrimePackage {\n  specFolder: string | null;\n  currentTask: string | null;\n  codeGraphStatus: 'fresh' | 'stale' | 'empty';\n  recommendedCalls: string[];\n  /** Structural bootstrap contract for non-hook runtimes */\n  structuralContext?: StructuralBootstrapContract;\n  /** Graph retrieval routing rules for AI session priming */\n  routingRules?: {\n    graphRetrieval: string;\n    communitySearch: string;\n    toolRouting: string;\n  };\n}\n\n/* ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n   2. MEMORY SURFACE HOOK CONFIGURATION\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n\nconst MEMORY_AWARE_TOOLS: Set<string> = new Set([\n  'memory_context',\n  'memory_search',\n  'memory_quick_search',\n  'memory_match_triggers',\n  'memory_list',\n  'memory_save',\n  'memory_index_scan'\n]);\n\n// Token budgets for dual-scope lifecycle hooks\nconst TOOL_DISPATCH_TOKEN_BUDGET = 4000;\nconst COMPACTION_TOKEN_BUDGET = 4000;\n\n// Constitutional memory cache\n// Module-level mutable state: safe in a single-process MCP server.\n// If the server ever runs multi-process, replace with a shared store.\nlet constitutionalCache: ConstitutionalMemory[] | null = null;\nlet constitutionalCacheTime = 0;\nconst CONSTITUTIONAL_CACHE_TTL = 60000; // 1 minute\n// Per-session priming tracker: a Set of session IDs that have been primed.\n// Replaces the previous process-global boolean to avoid skipping priming\n// for new sessions on long-lived MCP servers.\nconst primedSessionIds: Set<string> = new Set();\n\n// Session-level tracking for prime package and session_health\nconst serverStartedAt = Date.now();\nlet lastToolCallAt = Date.now();\nlet lastActiveSessionId: string | null = null;\n\n/** Update last tool call timestamp (called from context-server dispatch). */\nfunction recordToolCall(sessionId?: string): void {\n  lastToolCallAt = Date.now();\n  if (typeof sessionId === 'string' && sessionId.trim().length > 0) {\n    lastActiveSessionId = sessionId.trim();\n  }\n}\n\n/** Get session tracking timestamps */\nfunction getSessionTimestamps(): { serverStartedAt: number; lastToolCallAt: number } {\n  return { serverStartedAt, lastToolCallAt };\n}\n\n/**\n * Check if a specific session has been primed.\n * Session identity is required to avoid cross-session bleed-through.\n */\nfunction isSessionPrimed(sessionId: string): boolean {\n  return primedSessionIds.has(sessionId);\n}\n\n/** Mark a specific session as primed */\nfunction markSessionPrimed(sessionId: string): void {\n  primedSessionIds.add(sessionId);\n  lastActiveSessionId = sessionId;\n}\n\nfunction getLastActiveSessionId(): string | null {\n  return lastActiveSessionId;\n}\n\n/* ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n   3. CONTEXT EXTRACTION\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n\nfunction extractContextHint(args: Record<string, unknown> | null | undefined): string | null {\n  if (!args || typeof args !== 'object') return null;\n\n  const contextFields = ['input', 'query', 'prompt', 'specFolder', 'filePath'];\n  for (const field of contextFields) {\n    if (args[field] && typeof args[field] === 'string' && (args[field] as string).length >= 3) {\n      return args[field] as string;\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Join concepts array if present\n  if (args.concepts && Array.isArray(args.concepts) && args.concepts.length > 0) {\n    const strings = args.concepts.filter((c): c is string => typeof c === 'string');\n    if (strings.length > 0) return strings.join(' ');\n  }\n\n  return null;\n}\n\n/* ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n   4. CONSTITUTIONAL MEMORIES\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n\nasync function getConstitutionalMemories(): Promise<ConstitutionalMemory[]> {\n  const now = Date.now();\n\n  if (constitutionalCache && (now - constitutionalCacheTime) < CONSTITUTIONAL_CACHE_TTL) {\n    return constitutionalCache;\n  }\n\n  try {\n    const db: Database | null = vectorIndex.tryGetDb();\n    if (!db) return [];\n\n    const rows = db.prepare(`\n      SELECT id, spec_folder, file_path, title, trigger_phrases, importance_tier\n      FROM memory_index\n      WHERE importance_tier = 'constitutional'\n      AND embedding_status IN ('success', 'pending', 'partial')\n      ORDER BY created_at DESC\n      LIMIT 10\n    `).all();\n\n    constitutionalCache = (rows as Record<string, unknown>[]).map((r) => ({\n      id: r.id as number,\n      specFolder: r.spec_folder as string,\n      filePath: r.file_path as string,\n      title: r.title as string,\n      importanceTier: r.importance_tier as string\n    }));\n    constitutionalCacheTime = now;\n\n    return constitutionalCache;\n  } catch (err: unknown) {\n    const message = err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err);\n    console.warn('[SK-004] Failed to fetch constitutional memories:', message);\n    return [];\n  }\n}\n\nfunction clearConstitutionalCache(): void {\n  constitutionalCache = null;\n  constitutionalCacheTime = 0;\n}\n\nfunction getCodeGraphStatusSnapshot(): NonNullable<AutoSurfaceResult['codeGraphStatus']> {\n  return getCodeGraphStatusSnapshotFromMarker();\n}\n\n/* ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n   5. AUTO-SURFACE MEMORIES\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n\nfunction enforceAutoSurfaceTokenBudget(\n  result: AutoSurfaceResult | null,\n  tokenBudget: number,\n  hookName: 'tool-dispatch' | 'compaction' | 'memory-aware'\n): AutoSurfaceResult | null {\n  if (!result) {\n    return null;\n  }\n\n  const measureTokens = (candidate: AutoSurfaceResult): number =>\n    estimateTokenCount(JSON.stringify(candidate));\n\n  const budgetLimit = Number.isFinite(tokenBudget) && tokenBudget > 0\n    ? tokenBudget\n    : TOOL_DISPATCH_TOKEN_BUDGET;\n\n  let boundedResult: AutoSurfaceResult = result;\n  let tokenCount = measureTokens(boundedResult);\n\n  if (tokenCount <= budgetLimit) {\n    return boundedResult;\n  }\n\n  const triggered = [...boundedResult.triggered];\n  while (triggered.length > 0 && tokenCount > budgetLimit) {\n    triggered.pop();\n    boundedResult = { ...boundedResult, triggered };\n    tokenCount = measureTokens(boundedResult);\n  }\n\n  const constitutional = [...boundedResult.constitutional];\n  while (constitutional.length > 0 && tokenCount > budgetLimit) {\n    constitutional.pop();\n    boundedResult = { ...boundedResult, constitutional };\n    tokenCount = measureTokens(boundedResult);\n  }\n\n  if (tokenCount > budgetLimit) {\n    console.warn(\n      `[SK-004] Auto-surface output exceeded ${hookName} token budget ` +\n      `(${tokenCount} > ${budgetLimit}); dropping payload`\n    );\n    return null;\n  }\n\n  console.warn(\n    `[SK-004] Auto-surface output truncated to fit ${hookName} token budget ` +\n    `(${tokenCount}/${budgetLimit})`\n  );\n  return boundedResult;\n}\n\n/**\n * Phase C: Get top-N attention-weighted memory IDs from working memory.\n * Used to boost trigger-matched results that also appear in the active\n * working set, improving surface relevance.\n *\n * @param limit - Maximum number of memory IDs to return\n * @returns Set of memory IDs with high attention in working memory\n */\nfunction getAttentionWeightedMemoryIds(limit: number = 5): Set<number> {\n  try {\n    const db: Database | null = vectorIndex.tryGetDb();\n    if (!db) return new Set();\n\n    // Query top attention-weighted memories, scoped to the current session\n    // by filtering to entries focused within the last hour. This prevents\n    // stale cross-session entries from influencing auto-surface ordering.\n    const oneHourAgo = new Date(Date.now() - 60 * 60 * 1000).toISOString();\n    const rows = db.prepare(`\n      SELECT DISTINCT wm.memory_id\n      FROM working_memory wm\n      WHERE wm.memory_id IS NOT NULL\n        AND wm.attention_score > ?\n        AND wm.last_focused >= ?\n      ORDER BY wm.attention_score DESC, wm.last_focused DESC","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":300,"totalLines":659,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/hooks/memory-surface.ts","time":{"start":1780738196951,"end":1780738196966}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0850f20a74e32d69016a23e894d9548191a4f195265a1ac1ba"}},"id":"prt_e9c4485cd0016hsrPz3OhsN0U5","sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeuERCb2AlX2T5Je","messageID":"msg_e9c4461320011YuE7wXipq34LO"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780738196970,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeuERCb2AlX2T5Je","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_mG1JL0n02eUorShcQKFXONax","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/hooks/claude/session-prime.ts","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/hooks/claude/session-prime.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: #!/usr/bin/env node\n2: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n3: // MODULE: SessionStart Hook — Session Prime\n4: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n5: // Runs on Claude Code SessionStart event. Injects context via stdout\n6: // based on the session source (compact, startup, resume, clear).\n7: \n8: import { resolve } from 'node:path';\n9: import { fileURLToPath } from 'node:url';\n10: import {\n11:   parseHookStdin, hookLog, formatHookOutput, truncateToTokenBudget,\n12:   withTimeout, HOOK_TIMEOUT_MS, COMPACTION_TOKEN_BUDGET, SESSION_PRIME_TOKEN_BUDGET,\n13:   calculatePressureAdjustedBudget, sanitizeRecoveredPayload, wrapRecoveredCompactPayload,\n14:   getRequiredSessionId,\n15:   type HookInput,\n16:   type OutputSection,\n17: } from './shared.js';\n18: import {\n19:   ensureStateDir,\n20:   loadState,\n21:   readCompactPrime,\n22:   clearCompactPrime,\n23:   validatePendingCompactPrimeSemantics,\n24: } from './hook-state.js';\n25: import { getCachedSessionSummaryDecision, logCachedSummaryDecision } from '../../handlers/session-resume.js';\n26: import { getStartupBriefFromMarker } from '../../lib/code-graph-boundary.js';\n27: \n28: const CACHE_TTL_MS = 30 * 60 * 1000;\n29: const IS_CLI_ENTRY = process.argv[1]\n30:   ? resolve(process.argv[1]) === fileURLToPath(import.meta.url)\n31:   : false;\n32: type StartupBrief = {\n33:   graphOutline: string | null;\n34:   sessionContinuity: string | null;\n35:   graphSummary: { files: number; nodes: number; edges: number; lastScan: string | null } | null;\n36:   graphQualitySummary?: unknown;\n37:   graphState: 'ready' | 'stale' | 'empty' | 'missing';\n38:   startupSurface: string;\n39:   sharedPayloadTransport?: string | null;\n40: };\n41: \n42: const buildStartupBrief = (_highlightCount?: number, _stateScope?: { specFolder?: string; claudeSessionId?: string }): StartupBrief =>\n43:   getStartupBriefFromMarker();\n44: \n45: /** Handle source=compact: inject cached PreCompact payload (from 3-source merger) */\n46: function handleCompact(sessionId: string): OutputSection[] {\n47:   const stateResult = loadState(sessionId);\n48:   const state = stateResult.ok ? stateResult.state : null;\n49:   const pendingCompactPrime = readCompactPrime(sessionId);\n50:   if (!pendingCompactPrime) {\n51:     hookLog('warn', 'session-prime', `No cached compact payload for session ${sessionId}`);\n52:     return [{\n53:       title: 'Context Recovery',\n54:       content: 'Context was compacted. Call `memory_context({ mode: \"resume\", profile: \"resume\" })` to recover session state.',\n55:     }];\n56:   }\n57: \n58:   const { payload, cachedAt } = pendingCompactPrime;\n59:   const cachedAtMs = new Date(cachedAt).getTime();\n60:   const cacheAgeMs = Date.now() - cachedAtMs;\n61:   if (Number.isNaN(cachedAtMs) || cacheAgeMs >= CACHE_TTL_MS) {\n62:     hookLog('warn', 'session-prime', `Rejecting stale compact cache for session ${sessionId} (cached at ${cachedAt})`);\n63:     return [{\n64:       title: 'Context Recovery',\n65:       content: 'Context was compacted. Call `memory_context({ mode: \"resume\", profile: \"resume\" })` to recover session state.',\n66:     }];\n67:   }\n68:   const semanticValidation = validatePendingCompactPrimeSemantics(pendingCompactPrime);\n69:   if (!semanticValidation.ok) {\n70:     hookLog('warn', 'session-prime', `Rejecting compact cache for session ${sessionId}: ${semanticValidation.reason}`);\n71:     clearCompactPrime(sessionId, {\n72:       cachedAt: pendingCompactPrime.cachedAt,\n73:       opaqueId: pendingCompactPrime.opaqueId ?? null,\n74:     });\n75:     return [{\n76:       title: 'Context Recovery',\n77:       content: 'Context was compacted, but the cached compact brief was quarantined by semantic validation. Call `memory_context({ mode: \"resume\", profile: \"resume\" })` to recover session state.',\n78:     }];\n79:   }\n80: \n81:   const sanitizedPayload = sanitizeRecoveredPayload(payload);\n82:   const wrappedPayload = wrapRecoveredCompactPayload(payload, cachedAt, {\n83:     producer: pendingCompactPrime.payloadContract?.provenance.producer,\n84:     trustState: pendingCompactPrime.payloadContract?.provenance.trustState,\n85:     sourceSurface: pendingCompactPrime.payloadContract?.provenance.sourceSurface,\n86:     sanitizerVersion: pendingCompactPrime.payloadContract?.provenance.sanitizerVersion,\n87:     runtimeFingerprint: pendingCompactPrime.payloadContract?.provenance.runtimeFingerprint,\n88:   });\n89:   hookLog('info', 'session-prime', `Injecting cached compact brief (${sanitizedPayload.length} chars after sanitization, cached at ${cachedAt})`);\n90: \n91:   const sections: OutputSection[] = [\n92:     { title: 'Recovered Context (Post-Compaction)', content: wrappedPayload },\n93:     {\n94:       title: 'Recovery Instructions',\n95:       content: 'Context was compacted and auto-recovered from the cached compact brief. For full session state, call `memory_context({ mode: \"resume\", profile: \"resume\" })`.',\n96:     },\n97:   ];\n98: \n99:   // Add last spec folder if known\n100:   if (state?.lastSpecFolder) {\n101:     sections.push({\n102:       title: 'Active Spec Folder',\n103:       content: `Last active: ${state.lastSpecFolder}`,\n104:     });\n105:   }\n106: \n107:   return sections;\n108: }\n109: \n110: function readCompactPrimeIdentity(sessionId: string): { cachedAt: string; opaqueId?: string | null } | null {\n111:   const pendingCompactPrime = readCompactPrime(sessionId);\n112:   if (!pendingCompactPrime) {\n113:     return null;\n114:   }\n115:   return {\n116:     cachedAt: pendingCompactPrime.cachedAt,\n117:     opaqueId: pendingCompactPrime.opaqueId ?? null,\n118:   };\n119: }\n120: \n121: /**\n122:  * Map rejection reasons to distinct short-form status labels so startup surface\n123:  * no longer collapses schema-mismatch, transcript-identity-mismatch,\n124:  * stale-summary, and ordinary missing-state into the same \"startup summary\n125:  * only\" string. Depends on HookState schema-version plumbing, which guarantees\n126:  * the upstream rejection reason is actually populated with the right\n127:  * discriminator.\n128:  */\n129: function describeMemoryStatus(\n130:   hasCachedContinuity: boolean,\n131:   rejectionReason: string | null,\n132: ): string {\n133:   if (hasCachedContinuity) {\n134:     return 'session continuity available';\n135:   }\n136:   if (!rejectionReason) {\n137:     return 'startup summary only (resume on demand)';\n138:   }\n139:   const reasonMap: Record<string, string> = {\n140:     missing_state: 'startup summary only (no cached continuity; resume on demand)',\n141:     schema_mismatch: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: schema version mismatch)',\n142:     missing_summary: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: missing session summary)',\n143:     missing_producer_metadata: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: producer metadata missing)',\n144:     missing_required_fields: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: required fields missing)',\n145:     transcript_unreadable: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: transcript unreadable)',\n146:     transcript_identity_mismatch: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: transcript identity mismatch)',\n147:     stale_summary: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: stale summary)',\n148:     summary_precedes_producer_turn: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: summary predates latest producer turn)',\n149:     scope_mismatch: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: scope mismatch)',\n150:     unknown_scope: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: scope unknown)',\n151:   };\n152:   return reasonMap[rejectionReason] ?? `startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: ${rejectionReason})`;\n153: }\n154: \n155: function buildFallbackStartupSurface(\n156:   hasCachedContinuity: boolean,\n157:   rejectionReason: string | null = null,\n158: ): string {\n159:   return [\n160:     'Session context received. Current state:',\n161:     '',\n162:     `- Memory: ${describeMemoryStatus(hasCachedContinuity, rejectionReason)}`,\n163:     '- Code Graph: unavailable',\n164:     '',\n165:     'What would you like to work on?',\n166:   ].join('\\n');\n167: }\n168: \n169: function rewriteStartupMemoryLine(\n170:   startupSurface: string,\n171:   hasCachedContinuity: boolean,\n172:   rejectionReason: string | null = null,\n173: ): string {\n174:   return startupSurface.replace(\n175:     /^- Memory: .*$/m,\n176:     `- Memory: ${describeMemoryStatus(hasCachedContinuity, rejectionReason)}`,\n177:   );\n178: }\n179: \n180: /** Handle source=startup: prime new session with constitutional memories + overview */\n181: export function handleStartup(\n182:   input: Pick<HookInput, 'session_id'> & { specFolder?: string } = {},\n183: ): OutputSection[] {\n184:   const sessionId = typeof input.session_id === 'string' ? input.session_id : undefined;\n185:   const requestedSpecFolder = typeof input.specFolder === 'string' ? input.specFolder : undefined;\n186:   let startupBrief: StartupBrief | null = null;\n187:   let startupBriefWarning: string | null = null;\n188:   try {\n189:     startupBrief = buildStartupBrief(undefined, {\n190:       claudeSessionId: sessionId,\n191:       specFolder: requestedSpecFolder,\n192:     });\n193:   } catch (err: unknown) {\n194:     startupBriefWarning = `buildStartupBrief threw: ${err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err)}`;\n195:     hookLog('error', 'session-prime', startupBriefWarning);\n196:   }\n197:   if (!startupBrief) {\n198:     startupBriefWarning = 'buildStartupBrief returned null';\n199:     hookLog('warn', 'session-prime', `${startupBriefWarning} — possible startup-brief regression`);\n200:   } else if (!startupBrief.startupSurface) {\n201:     startupBriefWarning = 'startupBrief.startupSurface is empty';\n202:     hookLog('warn', 'session-prime', `${startupBriefWarning} — possible startup-brief regression`);\n203:   }\n204:   const cachedSummaryDecision = getCachedSessionSummaryDecision({\n205:     specFolder: requestedSpecFolder,\n206:     claudeSessionId: sessionId,\n207:   });\n208:   if (cachedSummaryDecision.status !== 'accepted') {\n209:     logCachedSummaryDecision('session-prime', cachedSummaryDecision);\n210:   }\n211: \n212:   const sessionContinuity = cachedSummaryDecision.status === 'accepted'\n213:     ? cachedSummaryDecision.cachedSummary?.startupHint ?? null\n214:     : null;\n215:   // Forward the rejection reason so the startup surface can\n216:   // differentiate schema_mismatch / transcript_identity_mismatch / stale_summary\n217:   // / missing_state instead of collapsing them all into \"startup summary only\".\n218:   const rejectionReason = cachedSummaryDecision.status === 'rejected'\n219:     ? cachedSummaryDecision.reason\n220:     : null;\n\n(Showing lines 1-220 of 394. Use offset=221 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// MODULE: SessionStart Hook — Session Prime\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// Runs on Claude Code SessionStart event. Injects context via stdout\n// based on the session source (compact, startup, resume, clear).\n\nimport { resolve } from 'node:path';\nimport { fileURLToPath } from 'node:url';\nimport {\n  parseHookStdin, hookLog, formatHookOutput, truncateToTokenBudget,\n  withTimeout, HOOK_TIMEOUT_MS, COMPACTION_TOKEN_BUDGET, SESSION_PRIME_TOKEN_BUDGET,\n  calculatePressureAdjustedBudget, sanitizeRecoveredPayload, wrapRecoveredCompactPayload,\n  getRequiredSessionId,\n  type HookInput,\n  type OutputSection,\n} from './shared.js';\nimport {\n  ensureStateDir,\n  loadState,","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/hooks/claude/session-prime.ts","text":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// MODULE: SessionStart Hook — Session Prime\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// Runs on Claude Code SessionStart event. Injects context via stdout\n// based on the session source (compact, startup, resume, clear).\n\nimport { resolve } from 'node:path';\nimport { fileURLToPath } from 'node:url';\nimport {\n  parseHookStdin, hookLog, formatHookOutput, truncateToTokenBudget,\n  withTimeout, HOOK_TIMEOUT_MS, COMPACTION_TOKEN_BUDGET, SESSION_PRIME_TOKEN_BUDGET,\n  calculatePressureAdjustedBudget, sanitizeRecoveredPayload, wrapRecoveredCompactPayload,\n  getRequiredSessionId,\n  type HookInput,\n  type OutputSection,\n} from './shared.js';\nimport {\n  ensureStateDir,\n  loadState,\n  readCompactPrime,\n  clearCompactPrime,\n  validatePendingCompactPrimeSemantics,\n} from './hook-state.js';\nimport { getCachedSessionSummaryDecision, logCachedSummaryDecision } from '../../handlers/session-resume.js';\nimport { getStartupBriefFromMarker } from '../../lib/code-graph-boundary.js';\n\nconst CACHE_TTL_MS = 30 * 60 * 1000;\nconst IS_CLI_ENTRY = process.argv[1]\n  ? resolve(process.argv[1]) === fileURLToPath(import.meta.url)\n  : false;\ntype StartupBrief = {\n  graphOutline: string | null;\n  sessionContinuity: string | null;\n  graphSummary: { files: number; nodes: number; edges: number; lastScan: string | null } | null;\n  graphQualitySummary?: unknown;\n  graphState: 'ready' | 'stale' | 'empty' | 'missing';\n  startupSurface: string;\n  sharedPayloadTransport?: string | null;\n};\n\nconst buildStartupBrief = (_highlightCount?: number, _stateScope?: { specFolder?: string; claudeSessionId?: string }): StartupBrief =>\n  getStartupBriefFromMarker();\n\n/** Handle source=compact: inject cached PreCompact payload (from 3-source merger) */\nfunction handleCompact(sessionId: string): OutputSection[] {\n  const stateResult = loadState(sessionId);\n  const state = stateResult.ok ? stateResult.state : null;\n  const pendingCompactPrime = readCompactPrime(sessionId);\n  if (!pendingCompactPrime) {\n    hookLog('warn', 'session-prime', `No cached compact payload for session ${sessionId}`);\n    return [{\n      title: 'Context Recovery',\n      content: 'Context was compacted. Call `memory_context({ mode: \"resume\", profile: \"resume\" })` to recover session state.',\n    }];\n  }\n\n  const { payload, cachedAt } = pendingCompactPrime;\n  const cachedAtMs = new Date(cachedAt).getTime();\n  const cacheAgeMs = Date.now() - cachedAtMs;\n  if (Number.isNaN(cachedAtMs) || cacheAgeMs >= CACHE_TTL_MS) {\n    hookLog('warn', 'session-prime', `Rejecting stale compact cache for session ${sessionId} (cached at ${cachedAt})`);\n    return [{\n      title: 'Context Recovery',\n      content: 'Context was compacted. Call `memory_context({ mode: \"resume\", profile: \"resume\" })` to recover session state.',\n    }];\n  }\n  const semanticValidation = validatePendingCompactPrimeSemantics(pendingCompactPrime);\n  if (!semanticValidation.ok) {\n    hookLog('warn', 'session-prime', `Rejecting compact cache for session ${sessionId}: ${semanticValidation.reason}`);\n    clearCompactPrime(sessionId, {\n      cachedAt: pendingCompactPrime.cachedAt,\n      opaqueId: pendingCompactPrime.opaqueId ?? null,\n    });\n    return [{\n      title: 'Context Recovery',\n      content: 'Context was compacted, but the cached compact brief was quarantined by semantic validation. Call `memory_context({ mode: \"resume\", profile: \"resume\" })` to recover session state.',\n    }];\n  }\n\n  const sanitizedPayload = sanitizeRecoveredPayload(payload);\n  const wrappedPayload = wrapRecoveredCompactPayload(payload, cachedAt, {\n    producer: pendingCompactPrime.payloadContract?.provenance.producer,\n    trustState: pendingCompactPrime.payloadContract?.provenance.trustState,\n    sourceSurface: pendingCompactPrime.payloadContract?.provenance.sourceSurface,\n    sanitizerVersion: pendingCompactPrime.payloadContract?.provenance.sanitizerVersion,\n    runtimeFingerprint: pendingCompactPrime.payloadContract?.provenance.runtimeFingerprint,\n  });\n  hookLog('info', 'session-prime', `Injecting cached compact brief (${sanitizedPayload.length} chars after sanitization, cached at ${cachedAt})`);\n\n  const sections: OutputSection[] = [\n    { title: 'Recovered Context (Post-Compaction)', content: wrappedPayload },\n    {\n      title: 'Recovery Instructions',\n      content: 'Context was compacted and auto-recovered from the cached compact brief. For full session state, call `memory_context({ mode: \"resume\", profile: \"resume\" })`.',\n    },\n  ];\n\n  // Add last spec folder if known\n  if (state?.lastSpecFolder) {\n    sections.push({\n      title: 'Active Spec Folder',\n      content: `Last active: ${state.lastSpecFolder}`,\n    });\n  }\n\n  return sections;\n}\n\nfunction readCompactPrimeIdentity(sessionId: string): { cachedAt: string; opaqueId?: string | null } | null {\n  const pendingCompactPrime = readCompactPrime(sessionId);\n  if (!pendingCompactPrime) {\n    return null;\n  }\n  return {\n    cachedAt: pendingCompactPrime.cachedAt,\n    opaqueId: pendingCompactPrime.opaqueId ?? null,\n  };\n}\n\n/**\n * Map rejection reasons to distinct short-form status labels so startup surface\n * no longer collapses schema-mismatch, transcript-identity-mismatch,\n * stale-summary, and ordinary missing-state into the same \"startup summary\n * only\" string. Depends on HookState schema-version plumbing, which guarantees\n * the upstream rejection reason is actually populated with the right\n * discriminator.\n */\nfunction describeMemoryStatus(\n  hasCachedContinuity: boolean,\n  rejectionReason: string | null,\n): string {\n  if (hasCachedContinuity) {\n    return 'session continuity available';\n  }\n  if (!rejectionReason) {\n    return 'startup summary only (resume on demand)';\n  }\n  const reasonMap: Record<string, string> = {\n    missing_state: 'startup summary only (no cached continuity; resume on demand)',\n    schema_mismatch: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: schema version mismatch)',\n    missing_summary: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: missing session summary)',\n    missing_producer_metadata: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: producer metadata missing)',\n    missing_required_fields: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: required fields missing)',\n    transcript_unreadable: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: transcript unreadable)',\n    transcript_identity_mismatch: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: transcript identity mismatch)',\n    stale_summary: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: stale summary)',\n    summary_precedes_producer_turn: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: summary predates latest producer turn)',\n    scope_mismatch: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: scope mismatch)',\n    unknown_scope: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: scope unknown)',\n  };\n  return reasonMap[rejectionReason] ?? `startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: ${rejectionReason})`;\n}\n\nfunction buildFallbackStartupSurface(\n  hasCachedContinuity: boolean,\n  rejectionReason: string | null = null,\n): string {\n  return [\n    'Session context received. Current state:',\n    '',\n    `- Memory: ${describeMemoryStatus(hasCachedContinuity, rejectionReason)}`,\n    '- Code Graph: unavailable',\n    '',\n    'What would you like to work on?',\n  ].join('\\n');\n}\n\nfunction rewriteStartupMemoryLine(\n  startupSurface: string,\n  hasCachedContinuity: boolean,\n  rejectionReason: string | null = null,\n): string {\n  return startupSurface.replace(\n    /^- Memory: .*$/m,\n    `- Memory: ${describeMemoryStatus(hasCachedContinuity, rejectionReason)}`,\n  );\n}\n\n/** Handle source=startup: prime new session with constitutional memories + overview */\nexport function handleStartup(\n  input: Pick<HookInput, 'session_id'> & { specFolder?: string } = {},\n): OutputSection[] {\n  const sessionId = typeof input.session_id === 'string' ? input.session_id : undefined;\n  const requestedSpecFolder = typeof input.specFolder === 'string' ? input.specFolder : undefined;\n  let startupBrief: StartupBrief | null = null;\n  let startupBriefWarning: string | null = null;\n  try {\n    startupBrief = buildStartupBrief(undefined, {\n      claudeSessionId: sessionId,\n      specFolder: requestedSpecFolder,\n    });\n  } catch (err: unknown) {\n    startupBriefWarning = `buildStartupBrief threw: ${err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err)}`;\n    hookLog('error', 'session-prime', startupBriefWarning);\n  }\n  if (!startupBrief) {\n    startupBriefWarning = 'buildStartupBrief returned null';\n    hookLog('warn', 'session-prime', `${startupBriefWarning} — possible startup-brief regression`);\n  } else if (!startupBrief.startupSurface) {\n    startupBriefWarning = 'startupBrief.startupSurface is empty';\n    hookLog('warn', 'session-prime', `${startupBriefWarning} — possible startup-brief regression`);\n  }\n  const cachedSummaryDecision = getCachedSessionSummaryDecision({\n    specFolder: requestedSpecFolder,\n    claudeSessionId: sessionId,\n  });\n  if (cachedSummaryDecision.status !== 'accepted') {\n    logCachedSummaryDecision('session-prime', cachedSummaryDecision);\n  }\n\n  const sessionContinuity = cachedSummaryDecision.status === 'accepted'\n    ? cachedSummaryDecision.cachedSummary?.startupHint ?? null\n    : null;\n  // Forward the rejection reason so the startup surface can\n  // differentiate schema_mismatch / transcript_identity_mismatch / stale_summary\n  // / missing_state instead of collapsing them all into \"startup summary only\".\n  const rejectionReason = cachedSummaryDecision.status === 'rejected'\n    ? cachedSummaryDecision.reason\n    : null;","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":220,"totalLines":394,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/hooks/claude/session-prime.ts","time":{"start":1780738196954,"end":1780738196968}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0850f20a74e32d69016a23e894d9648191ad51f8663fd7a0c0"}},"id":"prt_e9c4485d8001s5vLa5nYR22CzL","sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeuERCb2AlX2T5Je","messageID":"msg_e9c4461320011YuE7wXipq34LO"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780738196970,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeuERCb2AlX2T5Je","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_L91NloWHD1YaqnEh0ERFC1eT","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/hooks/claude/user-prompt-submit.ts","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/hooks/claude/user-prompt-submit.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: #!/usr/bin/env node\n2: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n3: // MODULE: Claude User Prompt Submit Shim\n4: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n5: // Thin process-boundary shim. The advisor implementation lives in\n6: // system-skill-advisor; this path stays for existing runtime settings.\n7: \n8: import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n9: import { spawnSync } from 'node:child_process';\n10: \n11: const TARGET = '.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/dist/hooks/claude/user-prompt-submit.js';\n12: \n13: const result = spawnSync(process.execPath, [TARGET, ...process.argv.slice(2)], {\n14:   cwd: process.cwd(),\n15:   input: readFileSync(0),\n16:   encoding: 'utf8',\n17:   env: process.env,\n18: });\n19: \n20: if (result.stdout) process.stdout.write(result.stdout);\n21: if (result.stderr) process.stderr.write(result.stderr);\n22: if (result.error || result.status !== 0) process.stdout.write('{}\\n');\n23: \n24: process.exit(0);\n\n(End of file - total 24 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// MODULE: Claude User Prompt Submit Shim\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// Thin process-boundary shim. The advisor implementation lives in\n// system-skill-advisor; this path stays for existing runtime settings.\n\nimport { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\nimport { spawnSync } from 'node:child_process';\n\nconst TARGET = '.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/dist/hooks/claude/user-prompt-submit.js';\n\nconst result = spawnSync(process.execPath, [TARGET, ...process.argv.slice(2)], {\n  cwd: process.cwd(),\n  input: readFileSync(0),\n  encoding: 'utf8',\n  env: process.env,\n});\n\nif (result.stdout) process.stdout.write(result.stdout);","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/hooks/claude/user-prompt-submit.ts","text":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// MODULE: Claude User Prompt Submit Shim\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// Thin process-boundary shim. The advisor implementation lives in\n// system-skill-advisor; this path stays for existing runtime settings.\n\nimport { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\nimport { spawnSync } from 'node:child_process';\n\nconst TARGET = '.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/dist/hooks/claude/user-prompt-submit.js';\n\nconst result = spawnSync(process.execPath, [TARGET, ...process.argv.slice(2)], {\n  cwd: process.cwd(),\n  input: readFileSync(0),\n  encoding: 'utf8',\n  env: process.env,\n});\n\nif (result.stdout) process.stdout.write(result.stdout);\nif (result.stderr) process.stderr.write(result.stderr);\nif (result.error || result.status !== 0) process.stdout.write('{}\\n');\n\nprocess.exit(0);","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":24,"totalLines":24,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/hooks/claude/user-prompt-submit.ts","time":{"start":1780738196957,"end":1780738196969}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0850f20a74e32d69016a23e894d978819197e91bf85598597a"}},"id":"prt_e9c4485db001nJvK522f7p711J","sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeuERCb2AlX2T5Je","messageID":"ms