{"type":"text","timestamp":1780738218466,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeuERCb2AlX2T5Je","part":{"id":"prt_e9c44c51c001YfrqsP1Mdy07t3","messageID":"msg_e9c44acde0010YLxDURgxmYWE4","sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeuERCb2AlX2T5Je","type":"text","text":"Doctor already has a route manifest that exposes mutation class and trigger phrases, plus read-only memory diagnostics and a mutating full-update orchestrator; new checks should plug into `/doctor memory`, `/doctor skill-budget` or a parallel tool-surface audit rather than requiring operators to remember standalone scripts.","time":{"start":1780738213148,"end":1780738218465},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0c601e52070a3cd5016a23e8a51a508191b3d86469ba60bd3c","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780738218678,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeuERCb2AlX2T5Je","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_egRA8VB58coqc97glb8Op9oo","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"postMutationHooks|runPostMutationHooks|buildMutationHookFeedback|memory_validate|memory_update|memory_delete|memory_save\\(|handleMemorySave|governance|source","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers","include":"*.ts"},"output":"Found 311 matches (showing first 100)\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/causal-graph.ts:\n  Line 26: import { createScopeFilterPredicate } from '../lib/governance/scope-governance.js';\n\n  Line 34: import { runPostMutationHooks } from './mutation-hooks.js';\n\n  Line 98:   sourceId: string | number;\n\n  Line 236:         WHERE ce.source_id = CAST(m.id AS TEXT)\n\n  Line 278:  * for 'forward' direction: parent=source, child=target.\n\n  Line 279:  * For 'backward' direction: parent=target, child=source.\n\n  Line 592:       // Fail-closed scope authorization on the source memory. Done independently\n\n  Line 595:         const sourceScopeRow = db.prepare(`\n\n  Line 600:         if (!sourceScopeRow || !scopeMatches(sourceScopeRow)) {\n\n  Line 614:         const sourceMemory = db.prepare(`\n\n  Line 621:         if (sourceMemory) {\n\n  Line 622:           memoryDetails = sourceMemory;\n\n  Line 680:     // Fail-closed: the source memory is outside the supplied governed scope.\n\n  Line 779:     sourceId,\n\n  Line 792:   if ((sourceId === undefined || sourceId === null) || (targetId === undefined || targetId === null) || !relation) {\n\n  Line 794:     if (sourceId === undefined || sourceId === null) missing.push('sourceId');\n\n  Line 809:           'sourceId: Memory ID that is the cause/source',\n\n  Line 860:     const sourceRow = lookupEndpoint(String(s